target_text: e ratou sa sauma mai, "na nomuni tamata na tamai keitou e se bula vinaka tiko ka bulabula talega. " era sa cuva sobu ka vakarokoroko.

source_text: and he lifted up his eyes, and saw his brother benjamin, his mother's son, and said, is this your younger brother, of whom ye spake unto me? and he said, god be gracious unto thee, my son.
target_text: sa rai cake ka raici penijamini, na luvei tinana ka taroga, "oqo beka na tacimudou gone dou a tukuna vei au? " sa tukuna tale, "me yalololoma vei iko na kalou na luvequ. "

source_text: and joseph made haste; for his bowels did yearn upon his brother: and he sought where to weep; and he entered into his chamber, and wept there.
target_text: sa luluvu na yalona ena vukui tacina, sa lako tani yani vakatotolo ka tagi e na nona rumu.

source_text: and he washed his face, and went out, and refrained himself, and said, set on bread.
target_text: sa tavoya na matana ka lako tale mai, sa tauri koya vinaka ka tukuna, "me soli yani na madrai. "

source_text: and they set on for him by himself, and for them by themselves, and for the egyptians, which did eat with him, by themselves: because the egyptians might not eat bread with the hebrews; for that is an abomination unto the egyptians.
target_text: sa vakarautaki ga na teveli taudua nei joseva, na tikina ga me ra kana kina na tacina, na nodra tikina na ijipita era veiqaravi “ni o ira na ijipita era sega ni rawa ni kana vata kei ira na iperiu, ni oqo na ka toro sobu vei ira na kai ijipita.

source_text: and they sat before him, the firstborn according to his birthright, and the youngest according to his youth: and the men marvelled one at another.
target_text: era dabe tuvai e matai joseva, mai vei koya e qaseduadua ki vei koya sara e gone duadua. e ratou sa veiraici mada ga ena kidroa na veitacini.

source_text: and he took and sent messes unto them from before him: but benjamin's mess was five times so much as any of theirs. and they drank, and were merry with him.
target_text: sa kauta yani o koya na veiqaravi vei ira, mai matana. sa vakalimataki na ka vei penijamini. era sa gunu ka marau vata tiko kei joseva.

source_text: and he commanded the steward of his house, saying, fill the men's sacks with food, as much as they can carry, and put every man's money in his sack's mouth.
target_text: sa vakaroti ira na veiqaravi ena nona vale ka tukuna, "vakatawana na kakana ena nodra taga na tamata, na kena levu ga e rawa ni ra kauta, me biu tale na nodra i lavo ena gusu ni nodra taga.

source_text: and put my cup, the silver cup, in the sack's mouth of the youngest, and his corn money. and he did according to the word that joseph had spoken.
target_text: "me biu na noqu bilo siliva ena gusu ni nona taga o koya e gone duadua kei na nona i lavo talega ni sila. " sa caka me vaka na vosa sa tukuna o joseva.

source_text: as soon as the morning was light, the men were sent away, they and their asses.
target_text: ni sa kida na mataka, era sa vakatalai yani na tamata kei na nodra asa.

source_text: and when they were gone out of the city, and not yet far off, joseph said unto his steward, up, follow after the men; and when thou dost overtake them, say unto them, wherefore have ye rewarded evil for good?
target_text: ni ra sa lako tani yani mai na koro, ka e se bera sara na nodra lako yani vakayawa, sa tukuna o joseva vua na dauveiqaravi "tu cake, cici muri ira na tamata, ni o sa toboki ira, tukuna vaka oqo, 'na cava dou sa caka ca kina ena vuku ni vinaka?

source_text: is not this it in which my lord drinketh, and whereby indeed he divineth? ye have done evil in so doing.
target_text: 'sa sega beka ni oqo na nona ka ni gunu na noqu turaga “oqo talega sa dau caka i sausau kina o koya, dou sa caka ca sara ena vuku ni ka oqo. '"

source_text: and he overtook them, and he spake unto them these same words.
target_text: sa toboki ira sara ka cavuta na veivosa oqori.

source_text: and they said unto him, wherefore saith my lord these words? god forbid that thy servants should do according to this thing:
target_text: era sa tukuna vua, "na cava na vuna sa cavuta kina na vosa oqori na noqu turaga? me kua sara vei keimami na nomuni tamata na cakava na veika oqori.

source_text: behold, the money, which we found in our sacks' mouths, we brought again unto thee out of the land of canaan: how then should we steal out of thy lord's house silver or gold?
target_text: "raica keimami sa kauta lesu tale mai, mai na vanua o kenani nai lavo sa kune ena neimami taga, kila rawa vakacava me keimami butakoca na siliva se koula mai na vale ni neimami turaga?

source_text: with whomsoever of thy servants it be found, both let him die, and we also will be my lord's bondmen.
target_text: "vei koya ena kune vua, me na vakamatei, ka keimami na wili me nona bobula na noqu turaga. "

source_text: and he said, now also let it be according unto your words: he with whom it is found shall be my servant; and ye shall be blameless.
target_text: sa tukuna na tamata, "sa na yaco me vaka na nomudou vosa, o koya sa na kune vua, ena noqu bobula, o kemudou dou na sega ni beitaki. "

source_text: then they speedily took down every man his sack to the ground, and opened every man his sack.
target_text: era sa vakatotolo sara ka biuta kece ki ra na nodra dui usausa, ka dolava na nodra dui taga.

source_text: and he searched, and began at the eldest, and left at the youngest: and the cup was found in benjamin's sack.
target_text: sa tekivu mai vua sa qase ki vua sara sa gone: na bilo sa kune ena taga nei penijamini.

source_text: then they rent their clothes, and laded every man his ass, and returned to the city.
target_text: era sa basuraka na nodra i sulu, ka era sa vakavodoka tale na nodra dui asa ka lesu ki na koro.

source_text: and judah and his brethren came to joseph's house; for he was yet there: and they fell before him on the ground.
target_text: o juta kei ira na tacina, era sa lako mai ki na vale nei joseva, (ni se tiko ga e vale) era sa cuva vua ki na qele.

source_text: and joseph said unto them, what deed is this that ye have done? wot ye not that such a man as i can certainly divine?
target_text: sa tukuna vei ira o joseva. "na cava dou sa cakava oqo? dou sa sega beka ni kila ni tamata vakataki au, sa dau caka i sausau? "

source_text: and judah said, what shall we say unto my lord? what shall we speak? or how shall we clear ourselves? god hath found out the iniquity of thy servants: behold, we are my lord's servants, both we, and he also with whom the cup is found.
target_text: sa tukuna yani o juta, "na cava me keitou tukuna vua na neitou turaga? na vosa cava? se me keitou vakagalalataki keitou vakacava? na kalou sa raica na neitou cala, sai keitou oqo “keitou sa nona bobula na noqu turaga, oi keitou kei koya talega sa kune vua na bilo nei koya na noqu turaga. "

source_text: and he said, god forbid that i should do so: but the man in whose hand the cup is found, he shall be my servant; and as for you, get you up in peace unto your father.
target_text: sa tukuna mai o joseva: "me kua sara vei au oqori, me'u cakava na ka vaka oqori, o koya ga sa kune vua na bilo, ena noqu bobula “vei kemudou, dou lako ena vakacegu vei tamamudou. "

source_text: then judah came near unto him, and said, oh my lord, let thy servant, i pray thee, speak a word in my lord's ears, and let not thine anger burn against thy servant: for thou art even as pharaoh.
target_text: sa toso voleka o juta vei joseva ka tukuna, "noqu turaga, me'u vosa mada ka mo ni vakarorogo, me kua ni katakata na nomuni cudru vua na nomuni tamata; ni kemuni sa vakataki fero ga.

source_text: my lord asked his servants, saying, have ye a father, or a brother?
target_text: "na noqu turaga sa taroga na nomuni tamata ka vaka, 'edua tiko na tamamudou, e dua tiko na tacimudou? '

source_text: and we said unto my lord, we have a father, an old man, and a child of his old age, a little one; and his brother is dead, and he alone is left of his mother, and his father loveth him.
target_text: "keitou sa sauma vua na turaga, 'sa tiko na tamai keitou ka sa qase sara, sa tiko talega na taci keitou, e luvei tamai keitou ni sa qase sara, e gone sara, sa mate o tacina, o koya ga na luvei tinana ka sa rui lomani koya vakalevu o tamana. '

source_text: and thou saidst unto thy servants, bring him down unto me, that i may set mine eyes upon him.
target_text: "o ni sa tukuna vei ira na nomuni tamata, 'me kau sobu mai me raici koya na matamuni. '

source_text: and we said unto my lord, the lad cannot leave his father: for if he should leave his father, his father would die.
target_text: "keimami sa tukuna vua na neimami turaga, 'na gone sa sega ni rawa ni biuti tamana, ena mate o tamana kevaka sa biuti koya na gone. '

source_text: and thou saidst unto thy servants, except your youngest brother come down with you, ye shall see my face no more.
target_text: "o ni sa tukuna vei ira na nomuni tamata, 'kevaka sa sega ni lako mai na gone, keimami na sega ni raici kemuni. '

source_text: and it came to pass when we came up unto thy servant my father, we told him the words of my lord.
target_text: "ni keimami sa lako vei tamai keimami, keimami sa tukuna vua na vosa nei koya na neimami turaga.

source_text: and our father said, go again, and buy us a little food.
target_text: "sa tukuna o tamai keimami, 'me keimami mai volia tale mada vakalailai na kakana. '

source_text: and we said, we cannot go down: if our youngest brother be with us, then will we go down: for we may not see the man's face, except our youngest brother be with us.
target_text: "keimami sa tukuna, 'keimami na sega ni lako na sobu, vakavo kevaka sa lako vata kei keimami na gone. '

source_text: and thy servant my father said unto us, ye know that my wife bare me two sons:
target_text: "na tamadra na nomuni tamata sa tukuna, 'dou sa kila, na watiqu sa vakasucuma vei au e rua na luvequ tagane;

source_text: and the one went out from me, and i said, surely he is torn in pieces; and i saw him not since:
target_text: 'o koya sa lako tani mai vei au, "sa dina sara, sa basubasuki vakalalai"“au sa sega ni raici koya tale mai na siga o ya.

source_text: and if ye take this also from me, and mischief befall him, ye shall bring down my gray hairs with sorrow to the grave.
target_text: 'kevaka dou sa kauti koya tale oqo, ka yacovi koya na leqa, dou sa kauta sobu na ulu sika oqo ki nai bulubulu. '

source_text: now therefore when i come to thy servant my father, and the lad be not with us; seeing that his life is bound up in the lad's life;
target_text: "o koya oqo, ni'u na lako vua na nomuni tamata na tamaqu, ka sa sega ni tiko vata kei keitou na gone, na nona bula sa vesuki vata tiko kei na nona bula na gone,

source_text: it shall come to pass, when he seeth that the lad is not with us, that he will die: and thy servants shall bring down the gray hairs of thy servant our father with sorrow to the grave.
target_text: "ena yaco ni sa raica sa sega vei keitou na gone, ena mate o koya. o keitou sa na beitaki ni kauta sobu ki nai bulubulu ena rarawa na ulu sika “na tamai keitou.

source_text: for thy servant became surety for the lad unto my father, saying, if i bring him not unto thee, then i shall bear the blame to my father for ever.
target_text: "o au, na nomuni tamata, sa yalayala mei vakadei me baleta na gone vei tamana. 'kevaka, au na sega ni kauta lesu mai na gone “sa na noqu na kena bili me sega ni mudu. '

source_text: now therefore, i pray thee, let thy servant abide instead of the lad a bondman to my lord; and let the lad go up with his brethren.
target_text: "o koya oqo, me'u tiko o au na nomuni tamata ka me lako na gone, me'u nona bobula na noqu turaga “me lako ga yani na gone vata kei ira na tacina.

source_text: for how shall i go up to my father, and the lad be not with me? lest peradventure i see the evil that shall come on my father.
target_text: "me'u lako rawa vaka-cava vei tamaqu kevaka sa sega na gone, de, au na qai raica na rarawa levu ena lako mai vei tamaqu? "

source_text: then joseph could not refrain himself before all them that stood by him; and he cried, cause every man to go out from me. and there stood no man with him, while joseph made himself known unto his brethren.
target_text: sa sega ni rawa ni vosoti koya tiko o joseva e matadra sa tu vata kei koya, ka sa kaci yani, "mera lako kece i tuba na tamata mai vei au! " sa sega e tu vata kei koya ni sa tukuni koya tiko vei ira na tacina.

source_text: and he wept aloud: and the egyptians and the house of pharaoh heard.
target_text: sa tagi vakadomoi levu o koya, o ira na ijipita kei ira na vuvale nei fero, era sa rogoca.

source_text: and joseph said unto his brethren, i am joseph; doth my father yet live? and his brethren could not answer him; for they were troubled at his presence.
target_text: sa tukuna o joseva vei ira na tacina, "o au o joseva, e se bula tiko o tamaqu? " era sa sega ni sauma rawa na tacina, ni ra sa kidacala e matana.

source_text: and joseph said unto his brethren, come near to me, i pray you. and they came near. and he said, i am joseph your brother, whom ye sold into egypt.
target_text: sa tukuna o joseva vei ira na tacina, "dou toso voleka mai vei au. " sa qai tukuna tale, "o au o joseva na tacimudou, o koya dou a volitaka mai ki ijipita.

source_text: now therefore be not grieved, nor angry with yourselves, that ye sold me hither: for god did send me before you to preserve life.
target_text: "dou kua ni rarawa se cudruvi kemudou kina ni dou volitaki au mai ki ke; na kalou sa talai au mai e liu vei kemudou, me maroroi kina na bula.

source_text: for these two years hath the famine been in the land: and yet there are five years, in the which there shall neither be earing nor harvest.
target_text: "ena rua na yabaki oqo sa sega kina na kakana ena vanua, ka sa tiko tale oqo e lima na yabaki ena sega kina na cukicuki se na tatamusuki.

source_text: and god sent me before you to preserve you a posterity in the earth, and to save your lives by a great deliverance.
target_text: "na kalou sa talai mai liu vei kemudou me maroroi na sautu ena vuravura, ka me vakabulai kemudou ena veisereki levu.

source_text: so now it was not you that sent me hither, but god: and he hath made me a father to pharaoh, and lord of all his house, and a ruler throughout all the land of egypt.
target_text: "ia, oqo sa sega ni oi kemudou sa talai au mai, na kalou ga, o koya sa cakava me'u tama vei fero, ka turaga ena nona vale taucoko ka lewa ena vanua taucoko o ijipita.

source_text: haste ye, and go up to my father, and say unto him, thus saith thy son joseph, god hath made me lord of all egypt: come down unto me, tarry not:
target_text: "dou totolo ka lako cake vei tamaqu ka tukuna vua, 'sa tukuna vaka oqo o joseva na luvemu: "na kalou sa cakava me'u turaga levu duadua e ijipita taucoko, lako sobu mai vakatotolo “kua ni wawa tale.

source_text: and thou shalt dwell in the land of goshen, and thou shalt be near unto me, thou, and thy children, and thy children's children, and thy flocks, and thy herds, and all that thou hast:
target_text: "dou na mai tiko ena vanua o koseni, dou na mai tiko volekati au, o kemudou kei ira na luvemudou kei ira na luvena na luvemudou, na nomudou manumanu kei na ka kecega sa nomudou.

source_text: and there will i nourish thee; for yet there are five years of famine; lest thou, and thy household, and all that thou hast, come to poverty.
target_text: "mai kea au na vakarautaka vei kemudou, de o ni na qai dravudravua o kemuni kei na nomuni vuvale kece, ni se vo tiko oqo e lima na yabaki ni dausiga. "'

source_text: and, behold, your eyes see, and the eyes of my brother benjamin, that it is my mouth that speaketh unto you.
target_text: "mo dou kila, na matamudou kei na matai penijamini na taciqu, sa raica na gusuqu ni sa vosa tiko.

source_text: and ye shall tell my father of all my glory in egypt, and of all that ye have seen; and ye shall haste and bring down my father hither.
target_text: "dou tukuna vei tamaqu na noqu cecere e ijipita kei na veika kecega dou sa raica; mo dou vakatotolo kina ka kauta sobu mai na tamaqu e ke. "

source_text: and he fell upon his brother benjamin's neck, and wept; and benjamin wept upon his neck.
target_text: rau sa veimokomokoti kei penijamini na tacina ka veitagicaki.

source_text: moreover he kissed all his brethren, and wept upon them: and after that his brethren talked with him.
target_text: sa reguci iratou kece na tacina ka veitagici, ni sa oti o ya, era sa veivosaki.

source_text: and the fame thereof was heard in pharaoh's house, saying, joseph's brethren are come: and it pleased pharaoh well, and his servants.
target_text: nai rogorogo ni veika oqo sa yaco sara ki na loma ni vale nei fero ka vaka: "o ira na taci joseva, era sa lako mai. " sa taleitaka o fero kei ira na nona tamata na ka oqo.

source_text: and pharaoh said unto joseph, say unto thy brethren, this do ye; lade your beasts, and go, get you unto the land of canaan;
target_text: sa tukuna o fero vei joseva, "tukuna vei ira na tacimu, 'dou vakatawana nai lakolako, ka lako ki kenani.

source_text: and take your father and your households, and come unto me: and i will give you the good of the land of egypt, and ye shall eat the fat of the land.
target_text: 'dou kauti tamamudou mai kei na nomudou vuvale ka lako mai vei au; au na soli vei kemuni na tikina vinaka duadua ena vanua o ijipita, o ni na kania na uro ni vanua.

source_text: now thou art commanded, this do ye; take you wagons out of the land of egypt for your little ones, and for your wives, and bring your father, and come.
target_text: 'o ni sa vakaroti mo ni cakava oqo o mo ni kauta na qiqi vakavale me ra kau mai kina na gone kei tinadra ka mo ni kauti tamamuni talega mai.

source_text: also regard not your stuff; for the good of all the land of egypt is yours.
target_text: 'mo ni kua ni leqataka na veika e nomuni, baleta, ni na soli vei kemuni na vanua vinaka duadua e ijipita me nomuni. '"

source_text: and the children of israel did so: and joseph gave them wagons, according to the commandment of pharaoh, and gave them provision for the way.
target_text: o ira na luvei isireli era sa cakava oqo, me vaka sa tukuni vei ira, sa soli vei ira na qiqi vakavale me vaka nai vakaro i fero, sa soli talega vei ira na i vaqa ni lakolako.

source_text: to all of them he gave each man changes of raiment; but to benjamin he gave three hundred pieces of silver, and five changes of raiment.
target_text: sa solia vei ira kece, vei ira vakayadua na veisau ni nodra i sulu; vei penijamini ga sa solia kina e tolu na drau na tiki ni siliva kei na lima nai sulu ni veisau.

source_text: and to his father he sent after this manner; ten asses laden with the good things of egypt, and ten she asses laden with corn and bread and meat for his father by the way.
target_text: sa vakauta vei tamana na veika oqo, e tina na asa sa vakavodoki kina na veika vivinaka e ijipita, e tini na asa yalewa sa vakavodoki kina na sila, na madrai, kei na veikakana ni lakolako mai.

source_text: so he sent his brethren away, and they departed: and he said unto them, see that ye fall not out by the way.
target_text: sa vakatalai ira yani na tacina, ka era sa lako yani, ka sa tukuna vei ira, "dou raica me kua na leqa ena sala. "

source_text: and they went up out of egypt, and came into the land of canaan unto jacob their father,
target_text: era sa lako cake tani yani mai ijipita ka lako mai kina vanua o kenani vei jekope na tamadra.

source_text: and told him, saying, joseph is yet alive, and he is governor over all the land of egypt. and jacob's heart fainted, for he believed them not.
target_text: era sa tukuna vua, "o joseva e se bula tiko, e sa lewa tiko ena vanua taucoko o ijipita. " sa kidacala o jekope baleta ni sa sega ni vakabauti ira.

source_text: and they told him all the words of joseph, which he had said unto them: and when he saw the wagons which joseph had sent to carry him, the spirit of jacob their father revived:
target_text: ia, ni ra sa tukuna vua na vosa kece i joseva, ka sa raica talega na qiqi vakavale sa soli mai me mai vodo kina, sa vakabulabulataki tale na yaloi jekope na tamadra.

source_text: and israel said, it is enough; joseph my son is yet alive: i will go and see him before i die.
target_text: sa qai tukuna o isireli, "sa rauta, e se bula tiko o joseva na luvequ. au na lako ka raici koya ni bera ni'u mate. "

source_text: and israel took his journey with all that he had, and came to beersheba, and offered sacrifices unto the god of his father isaac.
target_text: sa kauta o isireli na nona veika kece ena nona i lakolako ka sa lako mai ki perisepa ka vakacabora nai soro vua na kalou i aisake na tamana.

source_text: and god spake unto israel in the visions of the night, and said, jacob, jacob. and he said, here am i.
target_text: na kalou sa qai vosa vei isireli ena raivotu ena bogi ka tukuna: "jekope, jekope, " sa sauma mai o jekope, "sai au oqo. "

source_text: and he said, i am god, the god of thy father: fear not to go down into egypt; for i will there make of thee a great nation:
target_text: sa tukuna mai, "oi au na kalou, na kalou i tamamu, kua ni rere ni lako sobu i ijipita, au na vakayacora mo matanitu levu mai kea.

source_text: i will go down with thee into egypt; and i will also surely bring thee up again: and joseph shall put his hand upon thine eyes.
target_text: "au na lako sobu vata kei iko ki ijipita, au na kauti iko lesu tale mai vakaidina. o joseva ena biuta na ligana e mataqu. "

source_text: and jacob rose up from beersheba: and the sons of israel carried jacob their father, and their little ones, and their wives, in the wagons which pharaoh had sent to carry him.
target_text: sa tucake o jekope mai perisepa, o ira na luvei isireli era sa kauti jekope, ira na nodra lalai, kei ira na watidra ena qiqi vakavale ea solia mai o fero me ra mai vodo kina.

source_text: and they took their cattle, and their goods, which they had gotten in the land of canaan, and came into egypt, jacob, and all his seed with him:
target_text: era sa kauta na nodra manumanu kei na nodra i yaya, era sa rawata ena vanua o kenani, ka lako sobu ki ijipita, o jekope kei ira kecega na nona kawa.

source_text: his sons, and his sons' sons with him, his daughters, and his sons' daughters, and all his seed brought he with him into egypt.
target_text: o ira na luvena tagane kei na luvedra tagane na luvena, na luvedra yalewa kei na luvedra yalewa na luvena tagane, kei ira kece na nona kawa, sa kauti ira kece ki ijipita.

source_text: and these are the names of the children of israel, which came into egypt, jacob and his sons: reuben, jacob's firstborn.
target_text: sai ira oqo na yacadra na luvei isireli, jekope kei na luvena tagane, o ira sa lako sobu ki ijipita. o rupeni na ulumatua nei jekope.

source_text: and the sons of reuben; hanoch, and phallu, and hezron, and carmi.
target_text: o ira na luvei rupeni tagane, o anoki, o palu, o esironi kei kami.

source_text: and the sons of simeon; jemuel, and jamin, and ohad, and jachin, and zohar, and shaul the son of a canaanitish woman.
target_text: o ira na luvei simione tagane: o jemueli, o jamini, o qada, o jakini, o soara, o saula na luveni dua na yalewa ni kenani.

source_text: and the sons of levi; gershon, kohath, and merari.
target_text: o ira na luvei livai tagane: o kerisoni, o koata, kei merari.

source_text: and the sons of judah; er, and onan, and shelah, and pharez, and zerah: but er and onan died in the land of canaan. and the sons of pharez were hezron and hamul.
target_text: o ira na luvei juta tagane: o eri, o onani, o sela, o veresi, kei sera. (o eri kei onani e rau sa mate ena vanua o kenani). na luvei veresi o esironi kei amulu.

source_text: and the sons of issachar; tola, and phuvah, and job, and shimron.
target_text: o ira na luvei isakari tagane: o tola, o pura, o jope, o simironi.

source_text: and the sons of zebulun; sered, and elon, and jahleel.
target_text: o ira na luvei sevuloni tagane: o sareti, o eloni, kei jaelieli.

source_text: these be the sons of leah, which she bare unto jacob in padanaram, with his daughter dinah: all the souls of his sons and his daughters were thirty and three.
target_text: sai ira oqori na luvei lia tagane, sa vakasucuma vei jekope mai padani-erami kei taina na luvena yalewa. o ira kece oqo sa lewe tolusagavulu ka tolu na tamata.

source_text: and the sons of gad; ziphion, and haggi, shuni, and ezbon, eri, and arodi, and areli.
target_text: o ira na luvei kata tagane: o sifioni, o aqi, o suni, o esiboni, o eri, o arodi, kei areli.

source_text: and the sons of asher; jimnah, and ishuah, and isui, and beriah, and serah their sister: and the sons of beriah; heber, and malchiel.
target_text: o ira na luvei aseri tagane: o jimina, o isua, o beria kei sera na luvena yalewa. o ira na luvei beria tagane, o eba kei malikieli.

source_text: these are the sons of zilpah, whom laban gave to leah his daughter, and these she bare unto jacob, even sixteen souls.
target_text: sai ira oqori na luvei siliva na dauveiqaravi nei lia. o ira kece oqo sa tinikaono na tamata.

source_text: the sons of rachel jacob's wife; joseph, and benjamin.
target_text: na luvei raijeli tagane na wati jekope: o joseva kei penijamini.

source_text: and unto joseph in the land of egypt were born manasseh and ephraim, which asenath the daughter of potipherah priest of on bare unto him.
target_text: vei joseva ena vanua o ijipita sa sucu kina o manasa kei ifereimi, e rau sa vakasucumi mai vei vasemaca na luvei poti-fera na bete.

source_text: and the sons of benjamin were belah, and becher, and ashbel, gera, and naaman, ehi, and rosh, muppim, and huppim, and ard.
target_text: o ira na luvei penijamini tagane: o bela, o bikeri, o asiveli, o qera, o nemani, o ei, o rosi, o mupimi, o upimi kei areti.

source_text: these are the sons of rachel, which were born to jacob: all the souls were fourteen.
target_text: o ira oqori na luvei raijeli tagane, sa vakasucuma vei jekope e tinikava na tamata.

source_text: and the sons of dan; hushim.
target_text: na luvei tani: o usimi.

source_text: and the sons of naphtali; jahzeel, and guni, and jezer, and shillem.
target_text: o ira na luvei navitalai: o jasili, o qani, o jasa kei silemi.

source_text: these are the sons of bilhah, which laban gave unto rachel his daughter, and she bare these unto jacob: all the souls were seven.
target_text: o ira oqori na luvei bila na dauveiqaravi nei raijeli. sa vakasucuma vei jekope e vitu na tamata.

source_text: all the souls that came with jacob into egypt, which came out of his loins, besides jacob's sons' wives, all the souls were threescore and six;
target_text: o ira kece na tamata era sa lako vata kei jekope ki ijipita “o ira kece sa lako mai ena yagona, sa onosagavulu ka ono na tamata.

source_text: and the sons of joseph, which were born him in egypt, were two souls: all the souls of the house of jacob, which came into egypt, were threescore and ten.
target_text: oi rau na luvei joseva sa sucu mai na vanua o ijipita, sa lewe rua. o ira kece na vuvale i jekope sa lako sobu ki ijipita sa vitusagavulu na tamata.

source_text: and he sent judah before him unto joseph, to direct his face unto goshen; and they came into the land of goshen.
target_text: sa vakatalai juta yani e liu o jekope vei joseva, me dusimaka vei ira na sala ki koseni. era sa lako mai ki na vanua o koseni.

source_text: and joseph made ready his chariot, and went up to meet israel his father, to goshen, and presented himself unto him; and he fell on his neck, and wept on his neck a good while.
target_text: sa vakarautaka o joseva na nona qiqi vakavale ka lako cake ki koseni me sota kei isireli na tamana; sa mokoti tamana yani ka rau sa veitagicaki.

source_text: and israel said unto joseph, now let me die, since i have seen thy face, because thou art yet alive.
target_text: o isireli sa tukuna vei joseva, "mo laivi au me'u mate, ni'u sa raica tale na matamu, baleta ni o se bula tiko. "

source_text: and joseph said unto his brethren, and unto his father's house, i will go up, and shew pharaoh, and say unto him, my brethren, and my father's house, which were in the land of canaan, are come unto me;
target_text: o joseva sa tukuna vei ira na tacina kei ira kece na vuvale nei tamana, "au na lako cake vei fero ka tukuna vua, 'ni o ira kece na taciqu kei na vuvale kece nei tamaqu era sa tiko mai na vanua o kenani, era sa lako mai oqo ki vei au.

source_text: and the men are shepherds, for their trade hath been to feed cattle; and they have brought their flocks, and their herds, and all that they have.
target_text: 'era sa dau vakatawana na sipi, me vaka ga ni nodra cakacaka na vakania na sipi; era sa kauta talega mai na nodra manumanu kece. '

source_text: and it shall come to pass, when pharaoh shall call you, and shall say, what is your occupation?
target_text: "ni sa lako mai o fero me tarogi kemuni, 'se cava na nomuni cakacaka? '

source_text: that ye shall say, thy servants' trade hath been about cattle from our youth even until now, both we, and also our fathers: that ye may dwell in the land of goshen; for every shepherd is an abomination unto the egyptians.
target_text: "mo ni qai tukuna, 'na nodra cakacaka na nomuni tamata sa tu vata ga kei ira na manumanu, mai na neimami gone ka yacova na siga oqo, oi keimami kei ira talega na tamai keimami: ' mo ni tiko kina ena vanua o koseni “o ira kece na vakatawa ni manumanu era sa ka vakasisila vei ira na kai ijipita. "

source_text: then joseph came and told pharaoh, and said, my father and my brethren, and their flocks, and their herds, and all that they have, are come out of the land of canaan; and, behold, they are in the land of goshen.
target_text: sa lako o joseva ka tukuna vei fero, "o tamaqu kei ira na taciqu, na nodra manumanu kei na veika kece era taukena “era sa lako mai na vanua o kenani, ka era sa tiko ena vanua o koseni. "

source_text: and he took some of his brethren, even five men, and presented them unto pharaoh.
target_text: sa kauta mai e lima, mai vei ira na tacina ka vakaraitaki ira vei fero.

source_text: and pharaoh said unto his brethren, what is your occupation? and they said unto pharaoh, thy servants are shepherds, both we, and also our fathers.
target_text: sa tarogi iratou na tacina o fero, "na cava na nomudou cakacaka? " e ratou sauma vei fero, "o ira na nomuni tamata sa dau vakatawa sipi, o keimami kei ira talega na neimami qase. "

source_text: they said moreover unto pharaoh, for to sojourn in the land are we come; for thy servants have no pasture for their flocks; for the famine is sore in the land of canaan: now therefore, we pray thee, let thy servants dwell in the land of goshen.
target_text: era sa tukuna talega vei fero, "keimami sa lako curuma mai na vanua, ni sa sega na kakana me kedra na manumanu baleta ni sa rui levu na dausiga e kenani. me ra tiko mada na nomuni tamata ena vanua o koseni. "

source_text: and pharaoh spake unto joseph, saying, thy father and thy brethren are come unto thee:
target_text: sa vosa o fero vei joseva ka vaka: "eera sa lako mai na tamamu kei na tacimu vei iko.

source_text: the land of egypt is before thee; in the best of the land make thy father and brethren to dwell; in the land of goshen let them dwell: and if thou knowest any men of activity among them, then make them rulers over my cattle.
target_text: "sa tu e matamu na vanua o ijipita. me ra tiko na tamamu kei na tacimu ena vanua vinaka duadua e ijipita, me ra tiko e koseni. kevaka, talega o sa raica e dua na tamata vinaka vei ira, me mai qarava na noqu manumanu. "

source_text: and joseph brought in jacob his father, and set him before pharaoh: and jacob blessed pharaoh.
target_text: o joseva sa kauti jekope mai na tamana vei fero, ka me tu ena matai fero. sa vakalouvinakataki fero o jekope.

source_text: and pharaoh said unto jacob, how old art thou?
target_text: sa tarogi jekope o fero ka vaka: "o sa yabaki vica? "

source_text: and jacob said unto pharaoh, the days of the years of my pilgrimage are an hundred and thirty years: few and evil have the days of the years of my life been, and have not attained unto the days of the years of the life of my fathers in the days of their pilgrimage.
target_text: sa sauma o jekope, "na veisiga ni noqu bula sa dua na drau ka mani tolusagavulu na yabaki, sa lailai ka ca na veisiga ni noqu bula, sa sega ni vaka na nodra veisiga ni bula na noqu qase. "

source_text: and jacob blessed pharaoh, and went out from before pharaoh.
target_text: sa vakalouvinakataki fero o jekope ka lako tani mai matana.

source_text: and joseph placed his father and his brethren, and gave them a possession in the land of egypt, in the best of the land, in the land of rameses, as pharaoh had commanded.
target_text: o joseva sa vakatikori ira na tamana kei na tacina ena vanua o ijipita, na tikina vinaka duadua ena vanua e ramisese, me vaka sa vakarota o fero.

source_text: and joseph nourished his father, and his brethren, and all his father's household, with bread, according to their families.
target_text: o joseva sa vakani tamana kei ira na tacina, kei na nodra veivuvale me vaka na kedra i wiliwili.

source_text: and there was no bread in all the land; for the famine was very sore, so that the land of egypt and all the land of canaan fainted by reason of the famine.
target_text: sa sega na madrai ena vanua taucoko, ni sa rui dede sara na dausiga, na vanua o ijipita kei kenani sa sega sara ga kina na ka baleta na balavu ni dausiga.

source_text: and joseph gathered up all the money that was found in the land of egypt, and in the land of canaan, for the corn which they bought: and joseph brought the money into pharaoh's house.
target_text: o joseva sa kumuna kece nai lavo ena vanua o ijipita kei na vanua o kenani, ena vuku ni sila era sa mai volia. sa kauta kece mai na i lavo ki na lololo nei fero.

source_text: and when money failed in the land of egypt, and in the land of canaan, all the egyptians came unto joseph, and said, give us bread: for why should we die in thy presence? for the money faileth.
target_text: ni sa oti kece nai lavo e ijipita kei kenani, era sa lako kece mai na ijipita vei joseva ka tukuna, "solia mai na kakana, me keimami mate beka e matamuni? ni sa oti nai lavo. "

source_text: and joseph said, give your cattle; and i will give you for your cattle, if money fail.
target_text: sa sauma yani o joseva, "ni solia mai na manumanu mei voli ni madrai, kevaka sa sega nai lavo. "

source_text: and they brought their cattle unto joseph: and joseph gave them bread in exchange for horses, and for the flocks, and for the cattle of the herds, and for the asses: and he fed them with bread for all their cattle for that year.
target_text: era sa kauta mai na nodra manumanu vei joseva, o joseva sa solia vei ira na madrai mei sosomi ni manumanu era sa kauta mai ena yabaki o ya.

source_text: when that year was ended, they came unto him the second year, and said unto him, we will not hide it from my lord, how that our money is spent; my lord also hath our herds of cattle; there is not ought left in the sight of my lord, but our bodies, and our lands:
target_text: ni sa oti na yabaki o ya, era sa lako tale mai ena yabaki ka tarava, ka tukuna vua, "keimami na sega ni vunitaka ni sa sega vei keimami nai lavo, na neimami turaga talega sa taura na neimami manumanu. sa sega tale na ka e vo “na yagoi keimami ga kei na neimami vanua.

source_text: wherefore shall we die before thine eyes, both we and our land? buy us and our land for bread, and we and our land will be servants unto pharaoh: and give us seed, that we may live, and not die, that the land be not desolate.
target_text: "na cava me keimami mate kina ena matamuni, oi keimami kei na neimami qele? mo ni voli keimami kei na neimami vanua ena madrai. oi keimami kei na neimami vanua keimami na bobula vei fero; solia vei keimami nai tei. me keimami bula ka sega ni mate, me kua ni lala na vanua. "

source_text: and joseph bought all the land of egypt for pharaoh; for the egyptians sold every man his field, because the famine prevailed over them: so the land became pharaoh's.
target_text: o joseva sa volia na vanua taucoko o ijipita vei fero, ni tamata kecega e ijipita sa volitaka na nona vanua, baleta ni sa rui sivia sara ga na dausiga. sa yaco me nei fero kece na vanua.

source_text: and as for the people, he removed them to cities from one end of the borders of egypt even to the other end thereof.
target_text: vei ira na tamata, o joseva sa tosoi ira na tamata ki na koro lelevu, mai na dua na yasana ki na dua tale na yasai ijipita.

source_text: only the land of the priests bought he not; for the priests had a portion assigned them of pharaoh, and did eat their portion which pharaoh gave them: wherefore they sold not their lands.
target_text: na nodra vanua ga na bete sa sega ni voli, ni o ira na bete, sa tu ga na kedra i votavota sa vakarautaka tu o fero. oqo, era sa sega ni volitaka kina na nodra vanua.

source_text: then joseph said unto the people, behold, i have bought you this day and your land for pharaoh: lo, here is seed for you, and ye shall sow the land.
target_text: sa qai tukuna o joseva vei ira na tamata, "raica au sa voli kemuni kei na vanua vei fero. oqo nai tei, mo ni tea na vanua.

source_text: and it shall come to pass in the increase, that ye shall give the fifth part unto pharaoh, and four parts shall be your own, for seed of the field, and for your food, and for them of your households, and for food for your little ones.

source_text: and joseph returned into egypt, he, and his brethren, and all that went up with him to bury his father, after he had buried his father.
target_text: ni sa buluti tamana oti, sa lesu tale ki ijipita o joseva, o koya kei iratou na tacina, kei ira kecega sa lako vata mai kei koya.

source_text: and when joseph's brethren saw that their father was dead, they said, joseph will peradventure hate us, and will certainly requite us all the evil which we did unto him.
target_text: ni ratou sa raica na taci joseva ni sa mate o tamadratou, e ratou sa veitalanoa ka vaka: "oqo ena cati kedatou o joseva, baleta na veika ca e datou a cakava vua. "

source_text: and they sent a messenger unto joseph, saying, thy father did command before he died, saying,
target_text: e ratou sa vakauta e dua nai tukutuku vei joseva ka vaka: "ni se bera ni mate na tamamu sa vakarota ka tukuna,

source_text: so shall ye say unto joseph, forgive, i pray thee now, the trespass of thy brethren, and their sin; for they did unto thee evil: and now, we pray thee, forgive the trespass of the servants of the god of thy father. and joseph wept when they spake unto him.
target_text: 'mo dou tukuna vei joseva, "mo vosota na nodratou caka cala na tacimu kei na nodratou i valavala ca, ni ratou sa caka cala vei iko. "' mo vosota na nodratou caka cala na tamata ni kalou nei tamamu. " sa tagi o joseva, ni ratou sa tukuna vua na veika oqo.

source_text: and his brethren also went and fell down before his face; and they said, behold, we be thy servants.
target_text: e ratou sa tagi talega na tacina ka cuva e matai joseva ka tukuna, "keitou sa nomuni tamata. "

source_text: and joseph said unto them, fear not: for am i in the place of god?
target_text: sa tukuna vei iratou o joseva, "dou kua ni rere, au kalou beka o au?

source_text: but as for you, ye thought evil against me; but god meant it unto good, to bring to pass, as it is this day, to save much people alive.
target_text: "vei kemudou, dou sa caka ca vei au, ia, na kalou sa nakita na ka vinaka vei kemudou, me yaco kina na bula ena siga oqo, me ra vakabulai kina e levu na tamata.

source_text: now therefore fear ye not: i will nourish you, and your little ones. and he comforted them, and spake kindly unto them.
target_text: "o koya oqo, mo dou kua ni rere kina, ni'u sa tu me'u vakarautaka vei kemudou kei ira na lalai. " sa vakaitaukeitaki iratou; ena nona sa vosa vinaka tikoga vei iratou.

source_text: and joseph dwelt in egypt, he, and his father's house: and joseph lived an hundred and ten years.
target_text: sa tiko ga e ijipita o joseva kei ira na vuvale nei tamana. sa bula tiko o joseva me dua na drau ka tini na yabaki.

source_text: and joseph saw ephraim's children of the third generation: the children also of machir the son of manasseh were brought up upon joseph's knees.
target_text: o joseva sa raica nai katolu ni tabatamata nei ifereimi. o ira talega na luvei makiri na luvei manasa era sa dau kau mai vei joseva.

source_text: and joseph said unto his brethren, i die: and god will surely visit you, and bring you out of this land unto the land which he sware to abraham, to isaac, and to jacob.
target_text: sa tukuna o joseva vei iratou na tacina, "raica au sa na mate, na kalou ena sikovi kemudou mai, ka na kauti kemudou ki na vanua sa bubului kina vei eparaama, vei aisake, kei jekope talega. "

source_text: and joseph took an oath of the children of israel, saying, god will surely visit you, and ye shall carry up my bones from hence.
target_text: sa cakava o joseva vei ra na luvei isireli me ra bubului ka vaka: "ni sa sikovi kemuni mai na kalou, mo ni qai kauta cake na suiqu ki kea. "

source_text: so joseph died, being an hundred and ten years old: and they embalmed him, and he was put in a coffin in egypt. for other languages please go to www. wordproject. org
target_text: sa mate o joseva ni sa yabaki dua na drau ka tini; era vakasuluma na yagona, ka, biuti koya tiko ena dua na kato ni mate mai ijipita. for other languages please go to www. wordproject. org

source_text: na kalou, e nai tekitekivu ni ka kecega, sa vakavuna na veilomalagi kei na vuravura.
target_text: in the beginning god created the heaven and the earth.

source_text: na vuravura sa sega ni vakavotukana tu, qai lala talega; na kena butobuto sa titobu sara. na yalo ni kalou sa vakaraica sobu tu mai na dela ni wai.
target_text: and the earth was without form, and void; and darkness was upon the face of the deep. and the spirit of god moved upon the face of the waters.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna, "me sa rarama mai, " sa qai dua sara na rarama.
target_text: and god said, let there be light: and there was light.

source_text: na kalou sa raica na rarama, ka sa vinaka. na kalou sa wasea na rarama mai na butobuto.
target_text: and god saw the light, that it was good: and god divided the light from the darkness.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna, na rarama me siga, kei na butobuto me bogi. na karobo ni yakavi ki na kida ni mataka, sai matai ni siga.
target_text: and god called the light day, and the darkness he called night. and the evening and the morning were the first day.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna, "me dua mada na kabukabu, me wasea na veiwai mai na veiwai. "
target_text: and god said, let there be a firmament in the midst of the waters, and let it divide the waters from the waters.

source_text: na kalou sa qai cakava na kabukabu, ka sa wasea na wai sa tiko ena ruku ni kabukabu kei na wai ena dela ni kabukabu, sa yaco me vakakina.
target_text: and god made the firmament, and divided the waters which were under the firmament from the waters which were above the firmament: and it was so.

source_text: na kalou sa vakayacana na kabukabu ni maliwa lala, na lomalagi, sa karobo na yakavi ka sa mataka tale, sai karua ni siga.
target_text: and god called the firmament heaven. and the evening and the morning were the second day.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna, "na wai kece ena ruku i lomalagi, me vakasoqoni kece ena dua na vanua, ka me basika mai na vanua mamaca; " sa yaco me vakakina.
target_text: and god said, let the waters under the heaven be gathered together unto one place, and let the dry land appear: and it was so.

source_text: na kalou sa vakayacana na vanua mamaca me vuravura, kei na wai sa vakasoqoni vata tu, me, wasawasa. na kalou sa raica oqo ni sa vinaka.
target_text: and god called the dry land earth; and the gathering together of the waters called he seas: and god saw that it was good.

source_text: na kalou sa qai tukuna, "na vanua me vakatubura mai na veico, na veisenikau kei na botebotekoro sa vakasorena, na veivunikau sa vakavuana ena kena veimataqali sa tiko e loma na sorena, " sa yaco me vakakina.
target_text: and god said, let the earth bring forth grass, the herb yielding seed, and the fruit tree yielding fruit after his kind, whose seed is in itself, upon the earth: and it was so.

source_text: sa tubu mai na veico, na veisenikau, na botebotekoro vakasorena na kena veimataqali, na veivunikau vakavuana sa tiko e loma na sorena ena kena veimataqali. na kalou sa raica ni sa vinaka.
target_text: and the earth brought forth grass, and herb yielding seed after his kind, and the tree yielding fruit, whose seed was in itself, after his kind: and god saw that it was good.

source_text: sa karobo, ka sa mataka tale na i katolu ni siga.
target_text: and the evening and the morning were the third day.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna tale, "me dua na rarama me tiko mai lomalagi, me wasea na siga mai na bogi, me vakatakilakila ni veiveisau ni veitabadraki kei na veitaba-gauna, vakasiga ka vakayabaki talega;
target_text: and god said, let there be lights in the firmament of the heaven to divide the day from the night; and let them be for signs, and for seasons, and for days, and years:

source_text: "me rarama kina na veilomalagi ka me solia mai na rarama e vuravura. " sa yaco me vakakina.
target_text: and let them be for lights in the firmament of the heaven to give light upon the earth: and it was so.

source_text: na kalou sa cakava e rua na rarama levu, na rarama levu me lewa na siga kei na rarama me lewa na bogi. sa bulia talega na veikalokalo.
target_text: and god made two great lights; the greater light to rule the day, and the lesser light to rule the night: he made the stars also.

source_text: na kalou sa vakatikori ira na veirarama oqo ena veiyasana vakalomalagi, me ra solia mai na rarama ki vuravura,
target_text: and god set them in the firmament of the heaven to give light upon the earth,

source_text: ka me ra lewa talega na siga kei na bogi, me ra wasea na rarama mai na butobuto. na kalou, ni sa raica oqo, sa vinaka vua.
target_text: and to rule over the day and over the night, and to divide the light from the darkness: and god saw that it was good.

source_text: oqo na karobo ni yakavi kei na mataka, sa i ka va ni siga.
target_text: and the evening and the morning were the fourth day.

source_text: na kalou sa qai tukuna, "me sa levu mai na wai, ka me levu talega mai na vei manumanu bula, me ra sa vuka mai na manumanu vuka e delai vuravura ka vukaca yani na veiyasana vakalomalagi. "
target_text: and god said, let the waters bring forth abundantly the moving creature that hath life, and fowl that may fly above the earth in the open firmament of heaven.

source_text: na kalou sa qai bulia na veimanumanu levu ni waitui kei na veika bula kecega era sinai tu mai na wailevu ena kena veimataqali, na vei manumanu kece vakatabana ena kena veimataqali. na kalou, ni sa raica oqo sa vinaka vua.
target_text: and god created great whales, and every living creature that moveth, which the waters brought forth abundantly, after their kind, and every winged fowl after his kind: and god saw that it was good.

source_text: na kalou sa qai vosa vakalouvinakataka na veika oqo ka tukuna, "mo ni yagavakalevu ka vakavuqataki kemuni ka vakatawana na wai ni wasawasa kei na manumanu vuka me levu sara e vuravura. "
target_text: and god blessed them, saying, be fruitful, and multiply, and fill the waters in the seas, and let fowl multiply in the earth.

source_text: sa qai karobo na yakavi ka mataka tale ni kalima ni siga.
target_text: and the evening and the morning were the fifth day.

source_text: na kalou sa qai tukuna, "o vuravura me kauta mai na veika bula me vaka na kena veimataqali na manumanu yavai va, na veimanumanu kece sa qasi voli, na veimanumanu kila ni veikau, o ira kece oqo kei na kena veimataqali, " sa yaco me vakakina.
target_text: and god said, let the earth bring forth the living creature after his kind, cattle, and creeping thing, and beast of the earth after his kind: and it was so.

source_text: na kalou sa bulia na veimanumanu ni vuravura me vaka na kena veimataqali, na bulumakau, na veika sa qasi voli, na veimanumanu kila ni vanua, me vaka na kedra dui veimataqali. na kalou ni sa raica oqo, sa vinaka dina.
target_text: and god made the beast of the earth after his kind, and cattle after their kind, and every thing that creepeth upon the earth after his kind: and god saw that it was good.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna, "medatou bulia mada na tamata me vakataki kedatou, me rairai vakataki kedatou, me ra lewa na vei ika kecega mai wai, na veimanumanu vuka e macawa kei na manumanu kecega ni vanua kei na veika kecega sa qasi voli e delai vuravura. "
target_text: and god said, let us make man in our image, after our likeness: and let them have dominion over the fish of the sea, and over the fowl of the air, and over the cattle, and over all the earth, and over every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth.

source_text: na kalou, sa qai bulia na tamata me vakataki koya ga, e nai rairai ga e va-kalou, na kalou sa bulia kina na tamata, na tagane kei na yalewa sa bulia o koya.
target_text: so god created man in his own image, in the image of god created he him; male and female created he them.

source_text: na kalou sa vakalouvinakataki rau, ka sa tukuna vei rau, "mo drau yagavakalevu ka vakalewelevutaki kemudrau, me vakatawai o vuravura ka me vakarorogo vei kemudrau; drau lewa na ika mai wai, na manumanu vuka e macawa, kei na veika kecega sa lako voli e delai vuravura. "
target_text: and god blessed them, and god said unto them, be fruitful, and multiply, and replenish the earth, and subdue it: and have dominion over the fish of the sea, and over the fowl of the air, and over every living thing that moveth upon the earth.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna, "raica, au sa solia vei kemudrau na veico kei na veika sa tubu mai ena qele, ka vakasorena tiko kei na vei vunikau vakavuana sa tiko e loma na sorena, oqori me kakana.
target_text: and god said, behold, i have given you every herb bearing seed, which is upon the face of all the earth, and every tree, in the which is the fruit of a tree yielding seed; to you it shall be for meat.

source_text: "na vei manumanu kece ni veikau kei na manumanu vuka ni macawa kei na veika kecega sa qasi voli e vuravura ka bula tiko, au sa solia vei ira na co kei na botebotekoro kecega sa tubu mai me kedra kakana; " sa yaco me vakakina.
target_text: and to every beast of the earth, and to every fowl of the air, and to every thing that creepeth upon the earth, wherein there is life, i have given every green herb for meat: and it was so.

source_text: na kalou, ni sa raica na veika kece sa cakava oti, io, sa dina, sa vinaka sara. sa qai karobo na yakavi ka mataka ni ka ono ni siga.
target_text: and god saw every thing that he had made, and, behold, it was very good. and the evening and the morning were the sixth day.

source_text: na veilomalagi kei na vuravura, kei na ka kecega sa tiko kina, sa buli oti.
target_text: thus the heavens and the earth were finished, and all the host of them.

source_text: ena i kavitu ni siga, sa mai oti kina na nona cakacaka na kalou. sa vakacegu ena i kavitu ni siga na kalou mai na nona cakacaka kecega ni veibuli sa cakava oti.
target_text: and on the seventh day god ended his work which he had made; and he rested on the seventh day from all his work which he had made.

source_text: na kalou sa qai vakalouvinakataka nai kavitu ni siga ka vakatabuya, baleta ni sa vakacegu mai na nona cakacaka kecega sa cakava ka bulia na kalou.
target_text: and god blessed the seventh day, and sanctified it: because that in it he had rested from all his work which god created and made.

source_text: oqo nai tukutuku ni veigauna kei lomalagi kei vuravura, ena gauna rau sa buli kina, ena siga sa bulia kina na lomalagi kei na vuravura na kalou o jiova,
target_text: these are the generations of the heavens and of the earth when they were created, in the day that the lord god made the earth and the heavens,

source_text: ni se bera ni tubu mai e dua na kau ena vanua se, e dua na co me tubu mai. na kalou o jiova e se bera ni vakavuna me tau mai na uca ki vuravura, ka e se bera ni tiko e dua na tamata me vakarautaka na qele;
target_text: and every plant of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew: for the lord god had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and there was not a man to till the ground.

source_text: sa lako cake ga mai na tegu mai vuravura ka vakasuasuataka na qele taucoko.
target_text: but there went up a mist from the earth, and watered the whole face of the ground.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa bulia na tamata mai na kuvu ni soso mai na qele ka solia nai cegu ni bula ki na ucuna; sa qai yaco me dua na ka bula na tamata.
target_text: and the lord god formed man of the dust of the ground, and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life; and man became a living soul.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa tea e dua nai teitei ena tokalau kei iteni, sa qai vakatikora e kea na tamata sa bulia oti.
target_text: and the lord god planted a garden eastward in eden; and there he put the man whom he had formed.

source_text: mai na qele, na kalou o jiova sa vakatubura mai kina na kau kecega sa vinaka ni laurai, ka sa vinaka talega ni laukana. na vunikau ni bula sa tiko talega ena loma ni teitei kei na vunikau talega sa kilai kina na vinaka kei na ca.
target_text: and out of the ground made the lord god to grow every tree that is pleasant to the sight, and good for food; the tree of life also in the midst of the garden, and the tree of knowledge of good and evil.

source_text: e dua na uciwai sa drodro mai iteni me vakasuasuataka na i teitei. mai iteni ga sa wase va mai kina na uciwai oqo.
target_text: and a river went out of eden to water the garden; and from thence it was parted, and became into four heads.

source_text: nai matai ni uciwai o pisoni, sa drodro yani ena vanua taucoko o avila, na vanua sa tiko kina na koula.
target_text: the name of the first is pison: that is it which compasseth the whole land of havilah, where there is gold;

source_text: na koula ni vanua oqo sa rui vinaka. na vatu talei, na onikisa sa tu e kea.
target_text: and the gold of that land is good: there is bdellium and the onyx stone.

source_text: na yaca ni karua ni uciwai o kioni; oqo e curuma yani na vanua taucoko o kusi.
target_text: and the name of the second river is gihon: the same is it that compasseth the whole land of ethiopia.

source_text: nai katolu ni uciwai o itekeli, na uciwai oqo sa lako yani vaka ki asiria. na i ka va ni uciwai na uferetisi.
target_text: and the name of the third river is hiddekel: that is it which goeth toward the east of assyria. and the fourth river is euphrates.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa kauta na tamata ka biuti koya ena i teitei mai iteni me qarava ka maroroya.
target_text: and the lord god took the man, and put him into the garden of eden to dress it and to keep it.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa vakarota na tamata ka vaka: "na veika kece sa tiko ena i teitei oqo mo kana mai kina;
target_text: and the lord god commanded the man, saying, of every tree of the garden thou mayest freely eat:

source_text: "ia na vunikau ga ni kila na ka vinaka kei na ka ca, mo kua ni kania, na siga o na kania kina na vuana, o na mate dina. "
target_text: but of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil, thou shalt not eat of it: for in the day that thou eatest thereof thou shalt surely die.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa tukuna, "sa sega ni vinaka vua na tamata me tiko duadua. au na cakava e dua na nonai i vukevuke me vakatautauvatataki kei koya. "
target_text: and the lord god said, it is not good that the man should be alone; i will make him an help meet for him.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa bulia mai na qele na manumanu kecega ni vanua kei na manumanu vuka ni macawa ka kauta mai vei atama me raica se ena kacivi ira vakacava. na yaca ga sa kacivi ira kina o atama, sa yacadra sara ga.
target_text: and out of the ground the lord god formed every beast of the field, and every fowl of the air; and brought them unto adam to see what he would call them: and whatsoever adam called every living creature, that was the name thereof.

source_text: o atama sa vakayacani ira kece na manumanu yavai va kei na manumanu vuka kecega kei na manumanu kecega ni vanua. ia me baleti atama, sa sega ni kune e dua me tautauvata kei koya me rawa ni dau veivuke vua.
target_text: and adam gave names to all cattle, and to the fowl of the air, and to every beast of the field; but for adam there was not found an help meet for him.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa vakavuna e dua na moce bi vei atama ka sa moce lutu sara kina. na kalou sa taura mai e dua na sui ni sarisarina ka ubia vinaka tale na lewena.
target_text: and the lord god caused a deep sleep to fall upon adam, and he slept: and he took one of his ribs, and closed up the flesh instead thereof;

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa vakayagataka na sui nei atama me bulia kina na yalewa, ka sa kauta sara mai vua na tamata.
target_text: and the rib, which the lord god had taken from man, made he a woman, and brought her unto the man.

source_text: sa tukuna sara o atama: "oqo na sui mai na suiqu, na lewe mai na lewequ, sa na yalewa o koya, baleta ni a wasei mai vua na tagane. "
target_text: and adam said, this is now bone of my bones, and flesh of my flesh: she shall be called woman, because she was taken out of man.

source_text: oqo, na vuna, ena biuta kina na tamana kei na tinana na tagane ka sema vei yalewa (watina), me rau sa yago vata.
target_text: therefore shall a man leave his father and his mother, and shall cleave unto his wife: and they shall be one flesh.

source_text: e rau sa luvawale ruarua tu na tagane kei na watina, e rau sa sega ni madua kina.
target_text: and they were both naked, the man and his wife, and were not ashamed.

source_text: na gata sa dauveivakaisini sara, mai vei ira kecega na manumanu ni vanua sa bulia na kalou o jiova. na gata sa tukuna vua na yalewa ka vaka: "sa tukuna dina na kalou, 'mo drau kua ni kana mai na vunikau kecega sa tu ena i teitei'? "
target_text: now the serpent was more subtil than any beast of the field which the lord god had made. and he said unto the woman, yea, hath god said, ye shall not eat of every tree of the garden?

source_text: sa tukuna mai na yalewa vua na gata, "keirau na kana mai na kau kecega sa tu ena i teitei;
target_text: and the woman said unto the serpent, we may eat of the fruit of the trees of the garden:

source_text: "ia, na vuanikau mai na vunikau ga sa tiko e na loma donu ni teitei, sa tukuna na kalou, 'mo drau kakua ni kania, se mo drau tara, de drau mate. '"
target_text: but of the fruit of the tree which is in the midst of the garden, god hath said, ye shall not eat of it, neither shall ye touch it, lest ye die.

source_text: sa tukuna mai na gata vua na yalewa, "drau na sega dina ni mate.
target_text: and the serpent said unto the woman, ye shall not surely die:

source_text: "ni sa kila na kalou, mai na siga drau na kania kina, ena rai na matamudrau, drau na vakatalega na kalou ena nomudrau kila na veika vinaka kei na veika ca. "
target_text: for god doth know that in the day ye eat thereof, then your eyes shall be opened, and ye shall be as gods, knowing good and evil.

source_text: na yalewa, ni sa raica na vunikau, ni sa vinaka me kakana, ka sa vinaka talega ki na mata, sa domona talega na vunikau me vuku kina, sa tauca sara na vuana ka kania. sa solia talega vei watina e rau sa tiko vata, sa kana talega o tagane.
target_text: and when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that it was pleasant to the eyes, and a tree to be desired to make one wise, she took of the fruit thereof, and did eat, and gave also unto her husband with her; and he did eat.

source_text: sa qai rai na matadrau, ka rau sa kila ni rau sa luvawale ruarua. e rau sa cula vata na drau ni lolo me nodrau i sulu.
target_text: and the eyes of them both were opened, and they knew that they were naked; and they sewed fig leaves together, and made themselves aprons.

source_text: e rau sa qai rogoca na rorogo ni nona veilakoyaki voli na kalou o jiova ena loma ni teitei ena batabata vinaka ni siga, ka rau sa vunitaki rau mai na mata ni kalou o jiova ena veivunikau ni teitei.
target_text: and they heard the voice of the lord god walking in the garden in the cool of the day: and adam and his wife hid themselves from the presence of the lord god amongst the trees of the garden.

source_text: sa kaci yani na kalou o jiova vei atama ka vaka: "o sa tiko e vei? "
target_text: and the lord god called unto adam, and said unto him, where art thou?

source_text: sa sauma mai o atama ka vaka: "au sa rogoca na domomuni e nai teitei, ka au sa rere vakalevu baleta ni'u sa luvawale tu, au sa qai vuni. "
target_text: and he said, i heard thy voice in the garden, and i was afraid, because i was naked; and i hid myself.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa taro tale mai, "o cei e tukuna ni o sa luvawale tu? o sa kana beka mai na vunikau, au a vakarota vei iko mo kua ni kana mai kina? "
target_text: and he said, who told thee that thou wast naked? hast thou eaten of the tree, whereof i commanded thee that thou shouldest not eat?

source_text: sa sauma mai na tamata, "na yalewa ga o ni a solia mai vei au me keirau tiko vata, o koya ga sa solia mai vei au na vua ni vunikau oqo, au sa kania sara. "
target_text: and the man said, the woman whom thou gavest to be with me, she gave me of the tree, and i did eat.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa tukuna vua na yalewa, "na cava sara mada oqo, o sa cakava? " sa sauma na yalewa ka vaka: "sa vakaisini au na gata, ka, au sa kana sara. "
target_text: and the lord god said unto the woman, what is this that thou hast done? and the woman said, the serpent beguiled me, and i did eat.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa tukuna vua na gata: "baleta na veika o sa cakava oqo, o sa rukaki vakalevu cake kina mai vei ira na manumanu ni vanua; o na lako voli e ketemu, o na kania na kuvu ni qele ena veisiga kece o sa bula kina.
target_text: and the lord god said unto the serpent, because thou hast done this, thou art cursed above all cattle, and above every beast of the field; upon thy belly shalt thou go, and dust shalt thou eat all the days of thy life:

source_text: au na vaka veimecakitaki iko kei na yalewa, o ira na nomu kawa kei na nona kawa; o koya ena vakamavoataka na ulumu, ka o na vakamavoataka na bukubuku ni yavana. "
target_text: and i will put enmity between thee and the woman, and between thy seed and her seed; it shall bruise thy head, and thou shalt bruise his heel.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa tukuna talega vua na yalewa; "au na vakalevutaka vei iko na rarawa ena gauna ni nomu kunekune; ena mosi levu, o na vakasucuma mai kina na gone; na nomu gagadre sa na tiko ga vua na watimu, ka ena vakatulewa tiko ga vei iko o koya. "
target_text: unto the woman he said, i will greatly multiply thy sorrow and thy conception; in sorrow thou shalt bring forth children; and thy desire shall be to thy husband, and he shall rule over thee.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa tukuna vakaoqo vei atama, "baleta ni o sa vakarorogo ki na domo i watimu, ka o sa kana mai na vunikau au a vakarota vei iko ka vaka, 'mo kua ni kana mai kina': "sa rukaki na qele ena vukumu; o na buno ka oca ni o sa kana mai kina, ena veisiga kece ni nomu bula.
target_text: and unto adam he said, because thou hast hearkened unto the voice of thy wife, and hast eaten of the tree, of which i commanded thee, saying, thou shalt not eat of it: cursed is the ground for thy sake; in sorrow shalt thou eat of it all the days of thy life;

source_text: na co kei na kau vakavotona sa na basika mai ena vukumu, o na kania na botebotekoro era na tubu mai.
target_text: thorns also and thistles shall it bring forth to thee; and thou shalt eat the herb of the field;

source_text: ena buno ni yadremu, o na qai kana madrai kina me yacova ni o sa lesu tale ki na qele, baleta ni o a kau ga mai na qele. ni o a kuvu ni soso ga, o na lesu tale ki na kuvu ni soso. "
target_text: in the sweat of thy face shalt thou eat bread, till thou return unto the ground; for out of it wast thou taken: for dust thou art, and unto dust shalt thou return.

source_text: o atama sa kacivi na watina me o ivi, ni sa tinadra na bula.
target_text: and adam called his wife's name eve; because she was the mother of all living.

source_text: vei atama kei watina talega, sa cakava kina na kalou o jiova na kuli ni manumanu ka vakaisulutaki rau kina.
target_text: unto adam also and to his wife did the lord god make coats of skins, and clothed them.

source_text: na kalou o jiova sa tukuna, "raica na tamata sa vakataki kedatou, me kila na vinaka kei na ca. oqo de qai taura talega na vua ni kau ni bula, ka kania, ena qai bula ka sega ni mudu"
target_text: and the lord god said, behold, the man is become as one of us, to know good and evil: and now, lest he put forth his hand, and take also of the tree of life, and eat, and live for ever:

source_text: o koya oqo, sa vakatalai koya tani kina na kalou mai na nona i teitei mai iteni, me la'ki cukicuki ka teitei ki na vanua sa kau kina.
target_text: therefore the lord god sent him forth from the garden of eden, to till the ground from whence he was taken.

source_text: sa vakatalai tani na tamata mai iteni ka sa vakatikora na jerupi ena tokalau ni teitei mai iteni kei na seleiwau yameyame ni bukawaqa sa veigoleyaki voli me rau yadrava na vunikau ni bula.
target_text: so he drove out the man; and he placed at the east of the garden of eden cherubims, and a flaming sword which turned every way, to keep the way of the tree of life.

source_text: o atama sa curumi ivi, ka sa mani kunekune sara o ivi, ka vakasucumi keni ka tukuna, "au sa rawata e dua na tagane mai vei jiova. "
target_text: and adam knew eve his wife; and she conceived, and bare cain, and said, i have gotten a man from the lord.

source_text: sa vakasucu tale, oqo sa sucu o epeli na tacina. o epeli sa dau vakaraici ira na sipi, o keni sa dau teitei ena vanua.
target_text: and she again bare his brother abel. and abel was a keeper of sheep, but cain was a tiller of the ground.

source_text: ni sa toso tiko na gauna, sa qai yaco me kauta mai o keni e so na i soro vuata ni vanua vei jiova.
target_text: and in process of time it came to pass, that cain brought of the fruit of the ground an offering unto the lord.

source_text: o epeli talega sa kauta mai na ulumatua ni nona sipi kei na kedra uro me i soro. o jiova, sa doka vakalevu nai soro nei epeli,
target_text: and abel, he also brought of the firstlings of his flock and of the fat thereof. and the lord had respect unto abel and to his offering:

source_text: sa sega ni taleitaki keni kei na nona i soro. sa cudru sara vakalevu o keni ka sa duatani mai na kena i rairai.
target_text: but unto cain and to his offering he had not respect. and cain was very wroth, and his countenance fell.

source_text: o jiova sa qai vosa vei keni ka vaka: "na cava o via cudru kina? na cava na vuna sa duatani kina nai rairai ni matamu?
target_text: and the lord said unto cain, why art thou wroth? and why is thy countenance fallen?

source_text: "kevaka o sa caka vinaka, o na sega beka ni ciqomi? ia, kevaka o sega ni caka vinaka, sa wawa tiko nai valavala ca mai na mata ni katuba. sa tiko na nona gagadre vei iko, ia, mo lewa vinaka ga ena vukuna. "
target_text: if thou doest well, shalt thou not be accepted? and if thou doest not well, sin lieth at the door. and unto thee shall be his desire, and thou shalt rule over him.

source_text: e rau sa dau veivosaki o keni kei epeli na tacina; sa yaco na gauna ni rau sa tiko e na vanua, sa tucake o keni ka sa yalocataki epeli na tacina ka vakamatei koya.
target_text: and cain talked with abel his brother: and it came to pass, when they were in the field, that cain rose up against abel his brother, and slew him.

source_text: sa taro mai o jiova vei keni, "e vei o epeli na tacimu? " sa sauma mai, "au sa sega ni kila, oi au beka na nonai vakatawa? "
target_text: and the lord said unto cain, where is abel thy brother? and he said, i know not: am i my brother's keeper?

source_text: sa tukuna mai o jiova, "na cava o sa cakava, na domo ni dra i tacimu sa tagi tiko mai vei au mai na qele.
target_text: and he said, what hast thou done? the voice of thy brother's blood crieth unto me from the ground.

source_text: "oqo o sa vakaloucataki mai vuravura, ni sa dolava na gusuna me ciqoma na dra i tacimu mai na ligamu.
target_text: and now art thou cursed from the earth, which hath opened her mouth to receive thy brother's blood from thy hand;

source_text: "ni o sa tea na qele, ena sega ni solia na nona taucoko vei iko. o na tamata dauvakacudrui rawarawa ka o na dau veilakoyaki tu ga e vuravura. "
target_text: when thou tillest the ground, it shall not henceforth yield unto thee her strength; a fugitive and a vagabond shalt thou be in the earth.

source_text: sa tukuna mai o keni vei jiova, "na kequ i totogi sa rui levu sara ka sa rui bibi!
target_text: and cain said unto the lord, my punishment is greater than i can bear.

source_text: "sa dina sara, o ni sa vakasavi au ena siga oqo mai na matamuni; au na tamata sevaki ka dauveitosoyaki tu ga e vuravura, ena yaco na tamata kecega sa raici au ena via vakamatei au. "
target_text: behold, thou hast driven me out this day from the face of the earth; and from thy face shall i be hid; and i shall be a fugitive and a vagabond in the earth; and it shall come to pass, that every one that findeth me shall slay me.

source_text: sa tukuna vua o jiova, "o koya sa vakamatei keni, ena vakasukai vua me vakavitu tale. " o jiova sa vakatakilakilataki keni, de qai dua e kunei koya ka vakamatea.
target_text: and the lord said unto him, therefore whosoever slayeth cain, vengeance shall be taken on him sevenfold. and the lord set a mark upon cain, lest any finding him should kill him.

source_text: sa lako tani o keni mai na mata i jiova, ka la'ki tiko ena vanua o noti, ena ra kei iteni.
target_text: and cain went out from the presence of the lord, and dwelt in the land of nod, on the east of eden.

source_text: sa curu vei watina o keni, ka sa kunekune sara o watina, ka qai vakasucumi inoke. sa tara sara e dua na koro o keni ka vakayacana na koro o ya vei luvena ga” o inoke.
target_text: and cain knew his wife; and she conceived, and bare enoch: and he builded a city, and called the name of the city, after the name of his son, enoch.

source_text: mai vei inoke, sa basika mai kina o irati, o meujaeli, o lemeki mai vei metuisela.
target_text: and unto enoch was born irad: and irad begat mehujael: and mehujael begat methusael: and methusael begat lamech.

source_text: o lemeki sa rua na watina, e dua o ada kei na kena i karua o sila.
target_text: and lamech took unto him two wives: the name of the one was adah, and the name of the other zillah.

source_text: o ada sa vakasucumi jabali, o koya oqo na tamadra na dau vakavale laca tuga ka ra dau susu manumanu talega.
target_text: and adah bare jabal: he was the father of such as dwell in tents, and of such as have cattle.

source_text: na tacina o jubali. o koya oqo na tamadra na dauvakatagi api kei na bitu uvuci.
target_text: and his brother's name was jubal: he was the father of all such as handle the harp and organ.

source_text: vei sila sa sucu kina o tubale-keni na kena dau ni matai ni varasa kei na kaukamea. sa dua na gane i tubale-keni, na yacana o naema.
target_text: and zillah, she also bare tubalcain, an instructer of every artificer in brass and iron: and the sister of tubalcain was naamah.

source_text: sa tukuna o lemeki vei rau na watina, "kemudrau o ada kei sila, drau rogoci au na wati lemeki, drau rogoca na domoqu! au sa vakamatea e dua na tamata ni a vakamavoataki au, io, e dua na cauravou ni a vakararawataki au.
target_text: and lamech said unto his wives, adah and zillah, hear my voice; ye wives of lamech, hearken unto my speech: for i have slain a man to my wounding, and a young man to my hurt.

source_text: kevaka sa saumi vei keni me vakavitu, vei lemeki me vakavitusagavulu na vitu. "
target_text: if cain shall be avenged sevenfold, truly lamech seventy and sevenfold.

source_text: sa curumi watina tale o atama, ka sa vakasucuma vua e dua na gone e tagane, ka sa vakayacani koya me o seci, "ni o jiova na kalou sa solia tale vei au e dua mei sosomi kei epeli, o koya sa vakamatea o keni. "
target_text: and adam knew his wife again; and she bare a son, and called his name seth: for god, said she, hath appointed me another seed instead of abel, whom cain slew.

source_text: mai vei seci, sa vakasucumi vua e dua na gone ka tagane na yacana o inosi. oqo na vanua sa vakatekivu kina vei ira na tamata me ra kaciva kina na yaca i jiova.
target_text: and to seth, to him also there was born a son; and he called his name enos: then began men to call upon the name of the lord.

source_text: oqo nai vola i tukutuku ni kawa vaka-atama. na kalou, ena siga sa bulia kina na tamata, sa cakava me veiucui vata kei na kalou.
target_text: this is the book of the generations of adam. in the day that god created man, in the likeness of god made he him;

source_text: sa bulia na tagane kei na yalewa na kalou ka vosa vakalouvinakataki rau ka vakatokai rau me tamata mai na siga rau sa buli kina.
target_text: male and female created he them; and blessed them, and called their name adam, in the day when they were created.

source_text: sa bula tiko o atama me dua na drau tolusagavulu na yabaki ka sa vakasucumi vua e dua na gone, e tagane sa vakataki koya ga, me rau veiucui, na yacana o seci.
target_text: and adam lived an hundred and thirty years, and begat a son in his own likeness, after his image; and called his name seth:

source_text: ni sa sucu oti o seci, sa bula tale tiko o atama me walu na drau na yabaki. sa qai sucu tale eso na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and the days of adam after he had begotten seth were eight hundred years: and he begat sons and daughters:

source_text: na veisiga kece nei atama, sa ciwa na drau tolusagavulu na yabaki, ka sa qai mate yani.
target_text: and all the days that adam lived were nine hundred and thirty years: and he died.

source_text: sa yabaki dua na drau ka lima o seci, sa qai vakasucumi vua o inosi.
target_text: and seth lived an hundred and five years, and begat enos:

source_text: ni oti na sucu nei inosi, sa bula tale tiko o seci me walu na drau ka vitu na yabaki. sa vakasucumi tale eso na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and seth lived after he begat enos eight hundred and seven years, and begat sons and daughters:

source_text: na veisiga taucoko nei seci sa ciwa na drau tinikarua na yabaki, ka sa qai mate yani.
target_text: and all the days of seth were nine hundred and twelve years: and he died.

source_text: sa yabaki ciwasagavulu o inosi qai vakasucumi vua o keinana.
target_text: and enos lived ninety years, and begat cainan:

source_text: ni sa sucu oti o keinana, sa bula tiko o inosi me walu na drau tinikalima na yabaki, ka sa sucu talega eso na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and enos lived after he begat cainan eight hundred and fifteen years, and begat sons and daughters:

source_text: sa mate o inosi, ni sa ciwa na drau kalima na yabaki ni nona bula.
target_text: and all the days of enos were nine hundred and five years: and he died.

source_text: sa yabaki vitusagavulu o keinana, ni sa sucu o maelalieli.
target_text: and cainan lived seventy years, and begat mahalaleel:

source_text: sa vakasucumi vei keinana o maelalieli, sa yabaki walu na drau vasagavulu o keinana ka sa vakasucumi talega vua e so na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and cainan lived after he begat mahalaleel eight hundred and forty years, and begat sons and daughters:

source_text: na yabaki ni bula taucoko nei keinani sa ciwa na drau ka tini na yabaki ka sa qai mate yani.
target_text: and all the days of cainan were nine hundred and ten years: and he died.

source_text: sa yabaki onosagavulu ka lima tiko o maelalieli, sa qai vakasucumi vua o jareti.
target_text: and mahalaleel lived sixty and five years, and begat jared:

source_text: ni sa sucu oti o jareti, sa bula tiko o maelalieli me walu na drau tolusagavulu na yabaki ka sa sucu tale eso na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and mahalaleel lived after he begat jared eight hundred and thirty years, and begat sons and daughters:

source_text: na yabaki ni bula nei maelalieli e walu nadrau ciwasagavulu ka lima na yabaki, ka sa qai mate yani.
target_text: and all the days of mahalaleel were eight hundred ninety and five years: and he died.

source_text: sa bula o jareti me yabaki dua na drau onosagavulu ka rua sa qai sucu o inoke na luvena.
target_text: and jared lived an hundred sixty and two years, and he begat enoch:

source_text: ni sa sucu oti o inoke sa bula tale tiko o jareti me walu na drau na yabaki ka sa sucu tale eso na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and jared lived after he begat enoch eight hundred years, and begat sons and daughters:

source_text: na veisiga kece nei jareti sa ciwa na drau onosagavulu karua na yabaki ka sa qai mate yani.
target_text: and all the days of jared were nine hundred sixty and two years: and he died.

source_text: o inoke, sa yabaki onosagavulu ka lima ni sa vakasucumi vua o mecusela.
target_text: and enoch lived sixty and five years, and begat methuselah:

source_text: ni sa vakasucumi oti vua o mecusela, sa kune vua, ni rau sa daulako vata kei na kalou me tolu na drau na yabaki, ka sa vakasucumi talega vua na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and enoch walked with god after he begat methuselah three hundred years, and begat sons and daughters:

source_text: na veisiga kece nei inoke sa tolu na drau onosagavulu ka lima na yabaki.
target_text: and all the days of enoch were three hundred sixty and five years:

source_text: sa daulako vata kei na kalou o inoke; ka sa yali eke, ni sa kauti koya na kalou.
target_text: and enoch walked with god: and he was not; for god took him.

source_text: sa yabaki dua na drau walusagavulu ka vitu o mecusela ni sa vakasucumi vua o lemeki.
target_text: and methuselah lived an hundred eighty and seven years, and begat lamech:

source_text: ni sa sucu oti o lemeki, sa bula tale tiko o mecusela me vitu na drau walusagavulu ka rua na yabaki, ka sa sucu tale e so na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and methuselah lived after he begat lamech seven hundred eighty and two years, and begat sons and daughters:

source_text: na veisiga kece ni bula nei mecusela sa ciwa na drau onosagavulu ka ciwa na yabaki, ka sa qai mate yani.
target_text: and all the days of methuselah were nine hundred sixty and nine years: and he died.

source_text: o lemeki sa yabaki dua na drau walusagavulu karua ni sa vakasucumi vua e dua na luvena tagane.
target_text: and lamech lived an hundred eighty and two years, and begat a son:

source_text: sa vakayacani koya me o noa, ni sa tukuni, "o koya oqo ena vakacegui keda mai na noda oca kei na cakacaka ni ligada, ena vuku ni qele sa rukaka oti o jiova. "
target_text: and he called his name noah, saying, this same shall comfort us concerning our work and toil of our hands, because of the ground which the lord hath cursed.
