source_text: ni sa sucu oti o noa, sa bula tale tiko o lemeki me lima na drau ciwasagavulu ka lima na yabaki, ka sa sucu tale kina eso na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and lamech lived after he begat noah five hundred ninety and five years, and begat sons and daughters:

source_text: na veisiga kece nei lemeki sa vitu na drau vitusagavulu kavitu na yabaki ka sa qai mate yani.
target_text: and all the days of lamech were seven hundred seventy and seven years: and he died.

source_text: sa yabaki lima na drau o noa, ni ratou sa sucu o semi, o ame, kei jevica.
target_text: and noah was five hundred years old: and noah begat shem, ham, and japheth.

source_text: sa qai yaco ni ra sa lewe levu mai na tamata e dela i vuravura, sa levu talega na luvedra yalewa,
target_text: and it came to pass, when men began to multiply on the face of the earth, and daughters were born unto them,

source_text: o ira na luve ni kalou, ni ra sa raici ira na luvedra yalewa na tamata, ni ra sa rui totoka; era sa tauri ira me watidra, o ira kecega era sa digitaka.
target_text: that the sons of god saw the daughters of men that they were fair; and they took them wives of all which they chose.

source_text: sa qai tukuna o jiova, "na yaloqu ena sega ni veicoqacoqa tikoga kei na tamata me sega ni mudu, baleta ni sa vakayago na tamata; na nona veisiga sa na dua na drau ruasagavulu ga na yabaki. "
target_text: and the lord said, my spirit shall not always strive with man, for that he also is flesh: yet his days shall be an hundred and twenty years.

source_text: era sa tu e vuravura ena gauna o ya, na tuwawa, era sa dau lako mai na luve ni kalou ka veidauci kei ira na luvedra yalewa na tamata, era sa mani sucu kina na gone. oqo, o ira na tamata kaukauwa ka kilai ena gauna o ya.
target_text: there were giants in the earth in those days; and also after that, when the sons of god came in unto the daughters of men, and they bare children to them, the same became mighty men which were of old, men of renown.

source_text: o jiova, ni sa qai raica na vakasisila ni tamata ni sa rui sivia e vuravura, na nakinaki kei na vakanananu ni yalo ni tamata, sa caca tikotikoga.
target_text: and god saw that the wickedness of man was great in the earth, and that every imagination of the thoughts of his heart was only evil continually.

source_text: sa veivutunitaka sara ga o jiova ena nona a bulia na tamata e vuravura, ka sa rarawa vakalevu kina na yalona.
target_text: and it repented the lord that he had made man on the earth, and it grieved him at his heart.

source_text: sa tukuna kina vaka oqo, o jiova, "au na vakarusa na tamata mai na delai vuravura, o koya au a bulia, kecekece, na tamata, na manumanu, na veika era qasi voli kei na manumanu vuka ni macawa, ni'u sa rarawataka sara ga, na noqu a buli ira. "
target_text: and the lord said, i will destroy man whom i have created from the face of the earth; both man, and beast, and the creeping thing, and the fowls of the air; for it repenteth me that i have made them.

source_text: o noa duaduaga sa kune loloma ena mata i jiova.
target_text: but noah found grace in the eyes of the lord.

source_text: oqo nai tukutuku ni bula nei noa. o noa sa tamata dodonu ka sega ni cala ena nona i tabatamata. sa dau lako vata kei na kalou o noa.
target_text: these are the generations of noah: noah was a just man and perfect in his generations, and noah walked with god.

source_text: sa vakasucumi vei noa e tolu na luvena tagane: o semi kei ame kei jevica.
target_text: and noah begat three sons, shem, ham, and japheth.

source_text: sa ca ka vakacacani vakalevu o vuravura ena mata i jiova, o vuravura sa sinai talega ena i valavala kaukauwa e ca sara.
target_text: the earth also was corrupt before god, and the earth was filled with violence.

source_text: na kalou sa rai yani ki vuravura, ka raica, ni sa ca dina na kena i tuvaki, ni ra sa ca na tamata kecega kei na nodra i valavala kecega, e delai vuravura.
target_text: and god looked upon the earth, and, behold, it was corrupt; for all flesh had corrupted his way upon the earth.

source_text: na kalou sa qai tukuna vei noa, "nai tinitini ni ka kecega e vakayago, sa lako cake mai vei au oqo, ni ra sa vakasinaiti vuravura ena veika e kaukauwa ca; raica, au na vakarusai ira vata kei na vuravura.
target_text: and god said unto noah, the end of all flesh is come before me; for the earth is filled with violence through them; and, behold, i will destroy them with the earth.

source_text: "mo cakava vei iko e dua na waqa kau, cakava e loma ni waqa na veirumu, botana na loma ni waqa ena kuluta, e tuba talega.
target_text: make thee an ark of gopher wood; rooms shalt thou make in the ark, and shalt pitch it within and without with pitch.

source_text: "mo cakava vaka oqo: na balavu ni waqa me va na drau limasagavulu na fiti, na kena raraba me vitusagavulu ka lima na fiti kei na kena cere me vasagavulu ka lima na fiti.
target_text: and this is the fashion which thou shalt make it of: the length of the ark shall be three hundred cubits, the breadth of it fifty cubits, and the height of it thirty cubits.

source_text: "mo kila, oi au na kauta mai na waluvu levu e vuravura, me vakarusai kina na yago vakalewe kece e ruku i lomalagi, sa tiko vei ira na i cegu ni bula, kei na ka kecega sa bula e vuravura, e na mate.
target_text: and, behold, i, even i, do bring a flood of waters upon the earth, to destroy all flesh, wherein is the breath of life, from under heaven; and every thing that is in the earth shall die.

source_text: "ia, au na tekivuna na noqu veiyalayalati kei iko “o na curu ki waqa, o iko, o iratou na luvemu tagane, o na watimu, kei iratou na dui watina na luvemu.
target_text: but with thee will i establish my covenant; and thou shalt come into the ark, thou, and thy sons, and thy wife, and thy sons' wives with thee.

source_text: "na veika bula kece, me kau mai e rua na kena mataqali ki na waqa, me ra bula tiko vata kei iko, me dua e ka tagane kei na dua na ka yalewa.
target_text: and of every living thing of all flesh, two of every sort shalt thou bring into the ark, to keep them alive with thee; they shall be male and female.

source_text: "o ira na manumanu vuka na kena veimataqali, na manumanu yavaiva ena kena veimataqali, na veika sa qasi voli ena kena veimataqali, me ra lako yaya rua mai, me ra maroroi me ra bula.
target_text: of fowls after their kind, and of cattle after their kind, of every creeping thing of the earth after his kind, two of every sort shall come unto thee, to keep them alive.

source_text: "mo kauta mai vei iko na kakana kecega e laukana, mo kumuna vei iko na kakana kei na kedra talega na manumanu. "
target_text: and take thou unto thee of all food that is eaten, and thou shalt gather it to thee; and it shall be for food for thee, and for them.

source_text: sa cakava o noa, me vaka sa vakarota vua o jiova, sa cakava vaka kina.
target_text: thus did noah; according to all that god commanded him, so did he.

source_text: o jiova, sa qai vosa vei noa ka vaka: "curu mai ki waqa, o iko, kei iratou na nomu vuvale, baleta ni, au sa raica ni o sa yalododonu e mataqu e na i tabatamata oqo.
target_text: and the lord said unto noah, come thou and all thy house into the ark; for thee have i seen righteous before me in this generation.

source_text: "mo kauta vata kei iko e vitu na manumanu savasava mai na veimanumanu kecega, na ka tagane kei na ka yalewa, me rua na kena mataqali sa sega ni savasava, na ka tagane kei na ka yalewa;
target_text: of every clean beast thou shalt take to thee by sevens, the male and his female: and of beasts that are not clean by two, the male and his female.

source_text: "me vakatalega kina na manumanu vuka, na kena ka tagane kei na kena ka yalewa, me rawa ni ra bula tiko na kena kawa e delai vuravura.
target_text: of fowls also of the air by sevens, the male and the female; to keep seed alive upon the face of all the earth.

source_text: "sa vo tale tiko oqo e vitu na siga, me'u na vakavuna na uca ki vuravura me vasagavulu na siga ka vasagavulu na bogi; ka au na vakawabokotaka kina mai vuravura na ka bula kecega au a bulia. "
target_text: for yet seven days, and i will cause it to rain upon the earth forty days and forty nights; and every living substance that i have made will i destroy from off the face of the earth.

source_text: sa cakava kecega o noa me vaka sa vakarota vua o jiova.
target_text: and noah did according unto all that the lord commanded him.

source_text: sa yabaki ono na drau o noa ena gauna sa waluvu kina o vuravura.
target_text: and noah was six hundred years old when the flood of waters was upon the earth.

source_text: o noa kei iratou na luvena tagane, kei na watina, kei iratou na vugona yalewa, era sa lako kece ki loma ni waqa, baleta ni sa levu mai na wai ni waluvu.
target_text: and noah went in, and his sons, and his wife, and his sons' wives with him, into the ark, because of the waters of the flood.

source_text: na manumanu savasava kei na kena e sega ni savasava, na manumanu vuka talega kei na kena era qasi voli,
target_text: of clean beasts, and of beasts that are not clean, and of fowls, and of every thing that creepeth upon the earth,

source_text: era sa curu yarurua ki na waqa vei noa, na ka yalewa kei na ka tagane, me vaka sa vakarota o
target_text: there went in two and two unto noah into the ark, the male and the female, as god had commanded noah.

source_text: ni sa oti e vitu na siga na wai ni waluvu sa robota tu na vuravura.
target_text: and it came to pass after seven days, that the waters of the flood were upon the earth.

source_text: e nai ka ono na drau ni yabaki ni bula nei noa, e nai karua ni vula, nai ka tinikavitu ni siga, ena siga o ya sa kabasu mai kina nai vurevure ni wai titobu kecega, kei na katuba lalai kecega ni lomalagi sa tadola mai.
target_text: in the six hundredth year of noah's life, in the second month, the seventeenth day of the month, the same day were all the fountains of the great deep broken up, and the windows of heaven were opened.

source_text: sa tau tiko na uca e vuravura me vasagavulu na siga ka vasagavulu na bogi.
target_text: and the rain was upon the earth forty days and forty nights.

source_text: oqori, na siga sara ga e ratou sa curu kina ki waqa, o noa kei iratou na luvena tagane, kei watina kei iratou na vugona -
target_text: in the selfsame day entered noah, and shem, and ham, and japheth, the sons of noah, and noah's wife, and the three wives of his sons with them, into the ark;

source_text: o iratou, kei ira kece na manumanu na kena veimataqali, na bulumakau kece kei na kena veimataqali, na veika kece sa qasi voli e delai vuravura kei na veimataqali manumanu vuka kecega.
target_text: they, and every beast after his kind, and all the cattle after their kind, and every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth after his kind, and every fowl after his kind, every bird of every sort.

source_text: era sa lako ki na waqa vei noa, yarurua kei na ka kecega sa tiko e ucuna nai cegu ni bula.
target_text: and they went in unto noah into the ark, two and two of all flesh, wherein is the breath of life.

source_text: o ira kece sa curu ki waqa, na ka tagane kei na ka yalewa “era sa curu ki waqa me vaka sa vakarota vei noa na kalou; o jiova sa sogolati noa talega e loma.
target_text: and they that went in, went in male and female of all flesh, as god had commanded him: and the lord shut him in.

source_text: na waluvu sa tiko e vuravura me vasagavulu na siga. sa tubu cake tikoga na wai ka sa ciri na waqa, sa ciri sara tiko e cake mai na delai vuravura.
target_text: and the flood was forty days upon the earth; and the waters increased, and bare up the ark, and it was lift up above the earth.

source_text: sa tubu cake tikoga vakalevu na wai ena delai vuravura, ka sa veitosoyaki tiko na waqa ena dela ni wai.
target_text: and the waters prevailed, and were increased greatly upon the earth; and the ark went upon the face of the waters.

source_text: sa tubu cake tikoga na wai, ka sa vakalevu sara ni ra sa luvu kece na vei delana cecere ena ruku i lomalagi.
target_text: and the waters prevailed exceedingly upon the earth; and all the high hills, that were under the whole heaven, were covered.

source_text: sa tubu tikoga na wai me sivia e ruasagavulu ka rua na fiti na dela ni veiulunivanua cecere.
target_text: fifteen cubits upward did the waters prevail; and the mountains were covered.

source_text: era sa mate na ka bula kecega era sa veilakoyaki voli e vuravura: na manumanu vuka, na bulumakau, na manumanu kila tale e so, na veika kece era qasi voli, kei na tamata kecega.
target_text: and all flesh died that moved upon the earth, both of fowl, and of cattle, and of beast, and of every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth, and every man:

source_text: na veika kecega sa tiko kina nai cegu ni bula ena ucudra, na veika kece sa tiko ena vanua mamaca, era sa mate.
target_text: all in whose nostrils was the breath of life, of all that was in the dry land, died.

source_text: na kalou sa vakarusa na ka bula kecega era sa tiko e delai vuravura: na tamata, na manumanu, na veika sa qasi voli, kei na manumanu vuka ni macawa. era sa vakarusai kece mai vuravura. o noa ga, kei ira kece sa tiko ena loma ni waqa, sai ira ga sa bula tiko.
target_text: and every living substance was destroyed which was upon the face of the ground, both man, and cattle, and the creeping things, and the fowl of the heaven; and they were destroyed from the earth: and noah only remained alive, and they that were with him in the ark.

source_text: sa tiko ga na wai e vuravura me dua na drau limasagavulu na siga.
target_text: and the waters prevailed upon the earth an hundred and fifty days.

source_text: na kalou sa qai nanumi noa kei na veika bula kecega, na manumanu kecega era sa tiko vata kei noa e waqa. sa vakavuna na kalou me liwa e dua na cagi e vuravura, ka sa lutu sobu nai vakarau ni wai.
target_text: and god remembered noah, and every living thing, and all the cattle that was with him in the ark: and god made a wind to pass over the earth, and the waters asswaged;

source_text: nai vurevure mai na vei wai titobu kei na veikatuba lalai mai lomalagi era sa tasogo. sa tu vakadua na uca mai lomalagi.
target_text: the fountains also of the deep and the windows of heaven were stopped, and the rain from heaven was restrained;

source_text: sa drodro tani tiko ga yani na wai mai vuravura. nai otioti ni ka dua na drau limasagavulu ni siga, sa lailai sara na wai.
target_text: and the waters returned from off the earth continually: and after the end of the hundred and fifty days the waters were abated.

source_text: ena i ka tinikavitu ni siga, ni kavitu ni vula, sa mai kasa toka na waqa ena dela ni ulunivanua mai ararata.
target_text: and the ark rested in the seventh month, on the seventeenth day of the month, upon the mountains of ararat.

source_text: sa lutu sobu tikoga na wai ni waluvu me yacova na i katini ni vula. ena matai ni siga ni katini ni vula, era sa laurai mai na dela ni veiulunivanua.
target_text: and the waters decreased continually until the tenth month: in the tenth month, on the first day of the month, were the tops of the mountains seen.

source_text: sa qai yaco, ni sa yacova mai na mua ni ka vakasagavulu ni siga, sa dolava o noa na vei katuba lalai ni waqa, ea tara ga o koya.
target_text: and it came to pass at the end of forty days, that noah opened the window of the ark which he had made:

source_text: sa vakatala yani o noa e dua na reveni, ka sa veivukayaki tiko ga, me yacova ni sa mamaca mai na vanua.
target_text: and he sent forth a raven, which went forth to and fro, until the waters were dried up from off the earth.

source_text: sa vakatala talega mai vua, e dua na ruve, me raica se sa maca dina na wai mai na delai vuravura.
target_text: also he sent forth a dove from him, to see if the waters were abated from off the face of the ground;

source_text: na ruve sa sega ni raica e dua na vanua me ro kina, ka sa vuka lesu tale ki waqa vei noa, ni se luvu tiko ga o vuravura. sa dodoka yani o noa na ligana ka taura mai na ruve, sa kauta mai na ruve ki vei koya e waqa.
target_text: but the dove found no rest for the sole of her foot, and she returned unto him into the ark, for the waters were on the face of the whole earth: then he put forth his hand, and took her, and pulled her in unto him into the ark.

source_text: sa wawa tale me vitu na siga, sa qai vakatala tale yani na ruve mai na waqa.
target_text: and he stayed yet other seven days; and again he sent forth the dove out of the ark;

source_text: sa lesu tale mai vua na ruve ena yakavi, ka sa kauta tiko mai e dua na drau ni olive e se qai beti vou, ena gusuna; oqo sa kila kina o noa ni sa oti na waluvu.
target_text: and the dove came in to him in the evening; and, lo, in her mouth was an olive leaf pluckt off: so noah knew that the waters were abated from off the earth.

source_text: sa wawa tale me vitu na siga ka vakatala tale yani na ruve, na ruve oqo sa sega tale ni lesu mai vua.
target_text: and he stayed yet other seven days; and sent forth the dove; which returned not again unto him any more.

source_text: ena i ka ono na drau ka dua ni yabaki, ena i matai ni siga ni matai ni vula, sa maca vakadua na wai mai na delai vuravura; sa cecega o noa na i ubi ni waqa ka rai yani, sa dina sara, sa mamaca tu o vuravura.
target_text: and it came to pass in the six hundredth and first year, in the first month, the first day of the month, the waters were dried up from off the earth: and noah removed the covering of the ark, and looked, and, behold, the face of the ground was dry.

source_text: ena i ka ruasagavulu ka vitu ni siga ni karua ni vula, sa mamaca sara na qele.
target_text: and in the second month, on the seven and twentieth day of the month, was the earth dried.

source_text: na kalou sa vosa vei noa ka vaka,
target_text: and god spake unto noah, saying,

source_text: "lako tani mai na waqa, o iko, kei iratou na luvemu tagane, o watimu kei iratou na vugomu.
target_text: go forth of the ark, thou, and thy wife, and thy sons, and thy sons' wives with thee.

source_text: "me ra lako tani mai vata kei iko na veika bula kece sa vakalewe, na manumanu vuka, na bulumakau kei na veika kece sa qasi voli e delai vuravura, me ra mai vakalewelevutaki ira e vuravura, me ra mai yaga vakalevu ka tubu talega me levu. "
target_text: bring forth with thee every living thing that is with thee, of all flesh, both of fowl, and of cattle, and of every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth; that they may breed abundantly in the earth, and be fruitful, and multiply upon the earth.

source_text: sa curu ki tuba o noa kei iratou na luvena tagane, o watina kei iratou na vugona.
target_text: and noah went forth, and his sons, and his wife, and his sons' wives with him:

source_text: na manumanu kece, na veika kece e qasi voli e delai vuravura, na manumanu vuka, me vaka na nodra dui kawa, era sa lako tani mai na waqa.
target_text: every beast, every creeping thing, and every fowl, and whatsoever creepeth upon the earth, after their kinds, went forth out of the ark.

source_text: sa tara o noa e dua nai cabocabo ni soro vei jiova, ka taura mai na veimanumanu savasava kei na veimanumanu vuka e savasava, ka vakacabora me i soro kama ena i cabocabo ni soro.
target_text: and noah builded an altar unto the lord; and took of every clean beast, and of every clean fowl, and offered burnt offerings on the altar.

source_text: o jiova, sa boica nai boi kamikamica. sa qai tukuna ga e lomana, "au na sega tale ni rukaka na qele ena vuku ni tamata, e dina mada ga ni sa cala tu na vakanananu ni yalo ni tamata mai na gauna e se cauravou kina. au na sega ni vakarusa tale e dua na ka bula me vaka au sa vakayacora oti.
target_text: and the lord smelled a sweet savour; and the lord said in his heart, i will not again curse the ground any more for man's sake; for the imagination of man's heart is evil from his youth; neither will i again smite any more every thing living, as i have done.

source_text: "baleta ni se tiko ga na vuravura, na kakaburaki kei na tatamusuki, na batabata kei na katakata, na vulai liliwa kei na vulai katakata, na siga kei na bogi ena sega ni oti. "
target_text: while the earth remaineth, seedtime and harvest, and cold and heat, and summer and winter, and day and night shall not cease.

source_text: na kalou sa vakalouvinakataki noa kei iratou na luvena, ka tukuna vei iratou, "mo dou yagavakalevu ka vuavuai, mo dou vakalevutaki kemudou ka vakatawai vuravura.
target_text: and god blessed noah and his sons, and said unto them, be fruitful, and multiply, and replenish the earth.

source_text: "na manumanu kece ni vanua kei na manumanu vuka kece kei na ka kecega sa yavavala e delai vuravura, kei na ika kece ni loma ni wai, era na rerevaki kemudou ka taqayataki kemudou. era sa soli kece ki na ligamudou.
target_text: and the fear of you and the dread of you shall be upon every beast of the earth, and upon every fowl of the air, upon all that moveth upon the earth, and upon all the fishes of the sea; into your hand are they delivered.

source_text: "na veika kecega e bula ka yavavala era na kakana vei kemudou. au sa solia vei kemudou na ka kecega wili kina na veimataqali co.
target_text: every moving thing that liveth shall be meat for you; even as the green herb have i given you all things.

source_text: "mo dou kua ga ni kania vata na lewena kei na bula, oqori na kena dra.
target_text: but flesh with the life thereof, which is the blood thereof, shall ye not eat.

source_text: "ena vuku ni nomu drabula, au na vakataroga; mai na ligadra na manumanu kila, mai na ligadra talega na tamata. mai na ligadra kecega na veitacini, au na taroga mai kina na bula ni dua na tamata.
target_text: and surely your blood of your lives will i require; at the hand of every beast will i require it, and at the hand of man; at the hand of every man's brother will i require the life of man.

source_text: "o koya sa vakadavea na dra ni tamata, na tamata talega ena vakadavea na nona dra; ena veiucui e vakalou, na kalou sa bulia kina na tamata.
target_text: whoso sheddeth man's blood, by man shall his blood be shed: for in the image of god made he man.

source_text: io, veikemudou, mo dou yaga ga vakalevu ka vuavuai ka tubu me lewe levu; me sega o vuravura ka tubu tikoga kina. "
target_text: and you, be ye fruitful, and multiply; bring forth abundantly in the earth, and multiply therein.

source_text: na kalou sa qai vosa vei noa kei iratou na luvena ka vaka:
target_text: and god spake unto noah, and to his sons with him, saying,

source_text: "ena vukuqu, au sa tauyavutaka oqo na noqu veiyalayalati vata kei iko kei ira na nomu kawa era na muri mai,
target_text: and i, behold, i establish my covenant with you, and with your seed after you;

source_text: "kei na ka bula kecega sa tiko vata kei iko, na manumanu vuka, na bulumakau, na manumanu kecega ni vanua era sa tiko vata kei iko, o ira kecega sa lako tani mai waqa.
target_text: and with every living creature that is with you, of the fowl, of the cattle, and of every beast of the earth with you; from all that go out of the ark, to every beast of the earth.

source_text: "au na vakatauyavutaka na noqu veiyalayalati vata kei iko: ena sega tale, sa na sega ni vakarusai tale o vuravura ena waluvu. "
target_text: and i will establish my covenant with you; neither shall all flesh be cut off any more by the waters of a flood; neither shall there any more be a flood to destroy the earth.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna: "oqo nai vakatakilakila ni veiyalayalati au sa cakava vei kedaru, kei na veika bula kecega sa tiko vata kei iko, ki nai tabatamata e sega ni mudu:
target_text: and god said, this is the token of the covenant which i make between me and you and every living creature that is with you, for perpetual generations:

source_text: "au sa na tuvana na noqu drodrolagi ena vei o, mei vakatakilakila ni veiyalayalati mai vei au kei vuravura.
target_text: i do set my bow in the cloud, and it shall be for a token of a covenant between me and the earth.

source_text: "ni sa yaco, me'u kauta mai na vei o e delai vuravura, ka sa raici na drodrolagi ena vei o;
target_text: and it shall come to pass, when i bring a cloud over the earth, that the bow shall be seen in the cloud:

source_text: "au na nanuma na noqu veiyalayalati ena kedaru maliwa kei na veika bula kece sa vakalewe; na wai ena sega tale ni waluvu me vakarusa na veikabula e vuravura.
target_text: and i will remember my covenant, which is between me and you and every living creature of all flesh; and the waters shall no more become a flood to destroy all flesh.

source_text: "na drodrolagi ena tiko ga ena vei o, au na vakaraica yani me'u vakananuma kina na veiyalayalati e sega ni mudu nona na kalou kei na veika bula kecega e vuravura. "
target_text: and the bow shall be in the cloud; and i will look upon it, that i may remember the everlasting covenant between god and every living creature of all flesh that is upon the earth.

source_text: na kalou sa qai tukuna vei noa, "oqo nai vakatakilakila ni veiyalayalati au sa tauyavutaka vei au kei na ka bula kecega era sa tiko e vuravura. "
target_text: and god said unto noah, this is the token of the covenant, which i have established between me and all flesh that is upon the earth.

source_text: o iratou na luvei noa sa lako tani mai na waqa, o semi, ame kei jevica. o ame sa tamadra na kai kenani.
target_text: and the sons of noah, that went forth of the ark, were shem, and ham, and japheth: and ham is the father of canaan.

source_text: o iratou oqo na luve i noa, sa vakatawani kina o vuravura taucoko.
target_text: these are the three sons of noah: and of them was the whole earth overspread.

source_text: o noa, sa tekivu me teivaka na vanua, sa vaka veivaini o koya.
target_text: and noah began to be an husbandman, and he planted a vineyard:

source_text: sa gunu waini o koya, sa mateni kina ka sa luvawale ni sa davo moce tu ena nona valelaca.
target_text: and he drank of the wine, and was drunken; and he was uncovered within his tent.

source_text: o ame na tamadra na kai kenani, sa raici tamana ni sa luvawale tu, sa qai tukuna veirau na tacina e tautuba.
target_text: and ham, the father of canaan, saw the nakedness of his father, and told his two brethren without.

source_text: o semi kei jevica, e rau sa taura e dua nai sulu ka biuta e tabadrau, e rau sa lako vakanadaku ka ubia na luvawale nei tamadrau. e rau sa rai tani tuga “me rau kua ni raica kina na luvawale nei tamadrau.
target_text: and shem and japheth took a garment, and laid it upon both their shoulders, and went backward, and covered the nakedness of their father; and their faces were backward, and they saw not their father's nakedness.

source_text: ni sa oti na nona mateni o noa, sa qai kila na veika sa cakava o ame vua.
target_text: and noah awoke from his wine, and knew what his younger son had done unto him.

source_text: sa qai tukuna: "me rukaki o kenani; na nodra dauveiqaravi na dauveiqaravi, oqo o koya vei ira na tacina. "
target_text: and he said, cursed be canaan; a servant of servants shall he be unto his brethren.

source_text: sa qai tukuna tale, "me kalouvinaka o jiova na kalou i semi, ka me nona dauveiqaravi o kenani.
target_text: and he said, blessed be the lord god of shem; and canaan shall be his servant.

source_text: na kalou talega me vakalevutaki jevica, ka me tiko e vale nei semi, me nona dauveiqaravi o kenani. "
target_text: god shall enlarge japheth, and he shall dwell in the tents of shem; and canaan shall be his servant.

source_text: sa bula tale tiko o noa ni sa oti na waluvu me tolu na drau limasagavulu na yabaki.
target_text: and noah lived after the flood three hundred and fifty years.

source_text: na veisiga kece ni bula nei noa sa ciwa na drau limasagavulu na yabaki, ka sa qai mate yani.
target_text: and all the days of noah were nine hundred and fifty years: and he died.

source_text: oqo na veikawa nodratou na luvei noa: o semi, o ame kei jevica. o ira oqo sa sucu ni oti na waluvu.
target_text: now these are the generations of the sons of noah, shem, ham, and japheth: and unto them were sons born after the flood.

source_text: o ira na luvei jevica tagane oqo: o qoma, mekoki, madai, javana, tubali, mesake, kei tirasa.
target_text: the sons of japheth; gomer, and magog, and madai, and javan, and tubal, and meshech, and tiras.

source_text: o iratou na luvei qoma tagane oqo: o asakenasa, rifaci, kei toqama.
target_text: and the sons of gomer; ashkenaz, and riphath, and togarmah.

source_text: o iratou na luvei javana tagane oqo: o ilaisa, tasisi, kitimi, kei dodanimi.
target_text: and the sons of javan; elishah, and tarshish, kittim, and dodanim.

source_text: mai vei ira oqo, o ira na tamata ni veibaravi ni kai matanitu tani, era sa wasei tani mai na nodra vanua, o ira vakayadua me vaka na nodra dui vosavosa, me vaka na nodra dui vuvale kei na nodra dui vanua.
target_text: by these were the isles of the gentiles divided in their lands; every one after his tongue, after their families, in their nations.

source_text: o ira na luvei ame tagane oqo: o kusi, misirami, puti kei kenani.
target_text: and the sons of ham; cush, and mizraim, and phut, and canaan.

source_text: o ira na luvei kusi tagane oqo: o seba, avila, sebata, raema kei sabeteka; kei na luvei raema tagane, o seba kei didani.
target_text: and the sons of cush; seba, and havilah, and sabtah, and raamah, and sabtecha: and the sons of raamah; sheba, and dedan.

source_text: o kusi sa vakasucumi vua, o nimirote; sa tekivu me tamata qaqa mai e vuravura.
target_text: and cush begat nimrod: he began to be a mighty one in the earth.

source_text: sa tamata qaqa ni vakasasa ena mata i jiova; oqo sa tukuni kina, "me vakataki nimirote ena mata i jiova. "
target_text: he was a mighty hunter before the lord : wherefore it is said, even as nimrod the mighty hunter before the lord.

source_text: nai tekitekivu ni nona matanitu sai pepeli, o ereki, o akadi kei kalanei, ena vanua o sina.
target_text: and the beginning of his kingdom was babel, and erech, and accad, and calneh, in the land of shinar.

source_text: mai kea, sa lako yani ki asiria ka tarai ninive cake, o reopoci uri, kela,
target_text: out of that land went forth asshur, and builded nineveh, and the city rehoboth, and calah,

source_text: kei riseni, ena kedrau maliwa o ninive kei kela (na koro levu).
target_text: and resen between nineveh and calah: the same is a great city.

source_text: o misirami sa vakasucumi vua o ladimi, ananimi, o leabimi, o navitaimi,
target_text: and mizraim begat ludim, and anamim, and lehabim, and naphtuhim,

source_text: o pacurusimi, kei kasuluimi (era sa basika mai vei koya na filisitia kei na kapatorimi).
target_text: and pathrusim, and casluhim, (out of whom came philistim, ) and caphtorim.

source_text: o kenani sa vakasucumi vua o saitoni na nona ulumatua kei eci;
target_text: and canaan begat sidon his firstborn, and heth,

source_text: na jepusaiti, na amoraiti, kei na kirikisaiti;
target_text: and the jebusite, and the amorite, and the girgasite,

source_text: na ivaiti, na arakaiti kei na sainaiti;
target_text: and the hivite, and the arkite, and the sinite,

source_text: na arivadaiti, na semaraiti kei na ametaiti. era sa qai tawase na vuvale nei kenani, ni oti oqo.
target_text: and the arvadite, and the zemarite, and the hamathite: and afterward were the families of the canaanites spread abroad.

source_text: nai yalayala nei kenani, sa tekivu mai saitoni, ni o sa lako yani ki kerari, me yaco sara i qasa, ka lako sara i sotoma, komora, adama kei seboimi me yaco sara ki lasa.
target_text: and the border of the canaanites was from sidon, as thou comest to gerar, unto gaza; as thou goest, unto sodom, and gomorrah, and admah, and zeboim, even unto lasha.

source_text: oqo o ira na luve i ame, me vaka na nodra veivuvale, me vaka na nodra i vosavosa ena nodra vanua, ena nodra matanitu.
target_text: these are the sons of ham, after their families, after their tongues, in their countries, and in their nations.

source_text: era sa vakasucumi talega na gone vei semi, na tamadra na luvei eba, na taci jevica na qase.
target_text: unto shem also, the father of all the children of eber, the brother of japheth the elder, even to him were children born.

source_text: o ira na luvei semi oqo: o ilama, asuri, afakisati, ladi kei erami.
target_text: the children of shem; elam, and asshur, and arphaxad, and lud, and aram.

source_text: o ira na luvei erami oqo: o usi, uli, qesa kei masi.
target_text: and the children of aram; uz, and hul, and gether, and mash.

source_text: o afakisati sa vakasucumi vua o sala kei eba sa vakasucumi vei sala.
target_text: and arphaxad begat salah; and salah begat eber.

source_text: sa vakasucumi vei eba e rua na luvena tagane na yacana e dua o veleki (ni nona gauna sa tawase kina o vuravura) kei joketani na tacina.
target_text: and unto eber were born two sons: the name of one was peleg; for in his days was the earth divided; and his brother's name was joktan.

source_text: sa vakasucumi vei joketani o alemodidi, selefa, asemaveci, jera,
target_text: and joktan begat almodad, and sheleph, and hazarmaveth, and jerah,
and hadoram, and uzal, and diklah,
and obal, and abimael, and sheba,

source_text: o ofiri, avila kei jobaba. o ira kece oqo na luvei joketani.
target_text: and ophir, and havilah, and jobab: all these were the sons of joktan.

source_text: na vanua era tiko kina mai mesa, ena vanua vaka ki sefara, na ulunivanua mai na tokalau.
target_text: and their dwelling was from mesha, as thou goest unto sephar a mount of the east.

source_text: o ira oqo na luvei semi, me vaka na nodra dui vuvale, me vaka na nodra dui vosavosa, ena nodra vanua, me vaka na nodra veimatanitu.
target_text: these are the sons of shem, after their families, after their tongues, in their lands, after their nations.

source_text: sai ira oqo na vuvale nei noa, me vaka na nodra dui taba-tamata ena nodra dui yasana, eke era sa dui wasei kina na veimatanitu e vuravura ni oti na waluvu.
target_text: these are the families of the sons of noah, after their generations, in their nations: and by these were the nations divided in the earth after the flood.

source_text: na vuravura taucoko sa dua ga na kena vosa ka sa dua talega na kena i vosavosa.
target_text: and the whole earth was of one language, and of one speech.

source_text: sa qai yaco, ni ra sa lako tiko mai na tokalau, era sa kunea sara e dua na buca ena vanua o sina, ka era sa tiko sara kina.
target_text: and it came to pass, as they journeyed from the east, that they found a plain in the land of shinar; and they dwelt there.

source_text: era sa veivosaki vakai ira ka vaka, "me da sa buli vatutuva mada ka kuvuya vakavinaka. " sa tu vei ira na veika me buli kina na vatutuva oqo.
target_text: and they said one to another, go to, let us make brick, and burn them throughly. and they had brick for stone, and slime had they for morter.

source_text: era sa tukuna sara, "ni lako mai, meda tara mada e dua na noda koro kei na dua na vale vakaitaba, na delana me tiko mai lomalagi; me kilai kina na yacada, de, eda na qai vakasesei yani ena matai vuravura taucoko. "
target_text: and they said, go to, let us build us a city and a tower, whose top may reach unto heaven; and let us make us a name, lest we be scattered abroad upon the face of the whole earth.

source_text: sa lako sobu mai o jiova me raica na koro kei na vale vakaitaba, o koya era sa tara tiko na tamata.
target_text: and the lord came down to see the city and the tower, which the children of men builded.

source_text: sa tukuna o jiova, "era sa dua ga na tamata, ka sa dua ga na nodra vosa. raica oqo na veika era sa tekivu mera cakava, sa sega na veika e tiko tale, me na tarova na veika era sa nakita.
target_text: and the lord said, behold, the people is one, and they have all one language; and this they begin to do: and now nothing will be restrained from them, which they have imagined to do.

source_text: "mai, medatou lako sobu ka vakasesea na nodra vosa, me ra kakua ni veikilai vosavosa kina. "
target_text: go to, let us go down, and there confound their language, that they may not understand one another's speech.

source_text: o jiova sa vakacemuri ira tani mai kea ki na veiyasai vuravura kece, sa mai tu vakadua na tarai cake ni koro.
target_text: so the lord scattered them abroad from thence upon the face of all the earth: and they left off to build the city.

source_text: sa vakayacani na koro o ya me pepeli, baleta, ni o jiova sa vakasesea na nodra vosa kecega e vuravura. mai kea talega sa wasewasei ira yani kina ki vuravura taucoko.
target_text: therefore is the name of it called babel; because the lord did there confound the language of all the earth: and from thence did the lord scatter them abroad upon the face of all the earth.

source_text: oqo na kawa tamata i semi. o semi sa yabaki dua na drau ni sa vakasucumi vua o afakisati, oqori ni sa oti e rua na yabaki mai na waluvu.
target_text: these are the generations of shem: shem was an hundred years old, and begat arphaxad two years after the flood:

source_text: ni sa sucu oti o afakisati, sa bula tale tiko o semi me lima na drau na yabaki, ka sa so tale na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and shem lived after he begat arphaxad five hundred years, and begat sons and daughters.

source_text: o afakisati sa yabaki tolusagavulu ka lima ni sa sucu o sala.
target_text: and arphaxad lived five and thirty years, and begat salah:

source_text: sa sucu oti o sala, sa bula tale tiko o afakisati me yabaki va na drau ka tolu, ka sa so tale na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and arphaxad lived after he begat salah four hundred and three years, and begat sons and daughters.

source_text: sa yabaki tolusagavulu o sala ni sa sucu o eba.
target_text: and salah lived thirty years, and begat eber:

source_text: sa bula tiko o eba me va na drau ka tolu tale na yabaki ka sa so tale na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and salah lived after he begat eber four hundred and three years, and begat sons and daughters.

source_text: sa yabaki tolusagavulu ka va o eba ni sa sucu o veleki.
target_text: and eber lived four and thirty years, and begat peleg:

source_text: ni sa sucu oti o veleki, sa bula tale tiko o eba me va na drau tolusagavulu na yabaki ka sa so talega na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and eber lived after he begat peleg four hundred and thirty years, and begat sons and daughters.

source_text: sa yabaki tolusagavulu o veleki ni sa sucu o reu.
target_text: and peleg lived thirty years, and begat reu:

source_text: ni sa sucu oti o reu, sa bula tale tiko o veleki me rua na drau ka ciwa na yabaki ka sa sucu tale eso na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and peleg lived after he begat reu two hundred and nine years, and begat sons and daughters.

source_text: o reu sa yabaki tolusagavulu ni sa sucu o seruki.
target_text: and reu lived two and thirty years, and begat serug:

source_text: ni sa sucu oti o seruki, sa bula tale tiko o reu me rua na drau ka vitu na yabaki ka sa sucu tale eso na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and reu lived after he begat serug two hundred and seven years, and begat sons and daughters.

source_text: sa yabaki tolusagavulu o seruki ni sa sucu o neori.
target_text: and serug lived thirty years, and begat nahor:

source_text: ni sa sucu oti o neori, sa bula tale tiko o seruki me rua na drau na yabaki, era sa sucu talega eso na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and serug lived after he begat nahor two hundred years, and begat sons and daughters.

source_text: sa yabaki ruasagavulu ka ciwa o neori, ni sa sucu o tera.
target_text: and nahor lived nine and twenty years, and begat terah:

source_text: ni sa sucu oti o tera, sa bula tale tiko o neori me dua na drau tinikaciwai ka sa so tale na luvena tagane kei na luvena yalewa.
target_text: and nahor lived after he begat terah an hundred and nineteen years, and begat sons and daughters.

source_text: sa yabaki vitusagavulu o tera ni ratou sa sucu o eparama, neori kei arana.
target_text: and terah lived seventy years, and begat abram, nahor, and haran.

source_text: oqo na kawa nei tera: sa vakasucumi vei tera o eparama, neori kei arana. mai vei arana sa kune kina o loti.
target_text: now these are the generations of terah: terah begat abram, nahor, and haran; and haran begat lot.

source_text: sa mate o arana ena mata i tamana o tera, ena nona vanua mai uri e kalitia.
target_text: and haran died before his father terah in the land of his nativity, in ur of the chaldees.

source_text: e rau sa vakawati o eparama kei neori, na yaca ni wati eparama o serai kei na wati neori o milika, na luvei arana yalewa, na tamai milika, kei isika.
target_text: and abram and nahor took them wives: the name of abram's wife was sarai; and the name of nahor's wife, milcah, the daughter of haran, the father of milcah, and the father of iscah.

source_text: sa yava o serai ka sega na luvena.
target_text: but sarai was barren; she had no child.

source_text: o tera sa kauti rau na luvena o eparama kei makubuna o loti na luvei arana, o na vugona o serai na wati eparama. e ratou sa lako tani mai kea, ka lako ki na vanua o kenani, ka e ratou sa mai tiko e arana.
target_text: and terah took abram his son, and lot the son of haran his son's son, and sarai his daughter in law, his son abram's wife; and they went forth with them from ur of the chaldees, to go into the land of canaan; and they came unto haran, and dwelt there.

source_text: na veisiga taucoko nei tera sa rua na drau ka lima na yabaki, ka sa mate mai arana o tera.
target_text: and the days of terah were two hundred and five years: and terah died in haran.

source_text: o jiova sa tukuna vei eparama: "mo lako tani mai na nomu vanua, mai vei ira na wekamu, mai na vale nei tamamu, ki na vanua au na vakaraitaka vei iko.
target_text: now the lord had said unto abram, get thee out of thy country, and from thy kindred, and from thy father's house, unto a land that i will shew thee:

source_text: "au na cakava mo matanitu levu; o iko talega na veivakalouvinakataki.
target_text: and i will make of thee a great nation, and i will bless thee, and make thy name great; and thou shalt be a blessing:

source_text: "au na vakalouvinakataki ira sa vakalouvinakataki iko, au na rukaki ira sa rukaki iko; mai vei iko na veivuvale kecega e vuravura era na vakalouvinakataki. "
target_text: and i will bless them that bless thee, and curse him that curseth thee: and in thee shall all families of the earth be blessed.

source_text: sa lako o eparama me vaka sa vosa kina vua o jiova, sa lako vata kei koya o loti. sa yabaki vitusagavulu ka lima o eparama ni sa lako tani mai arana.
target_text: so abram departed, as the lord had spoken unto him; and lot went with him: and abram was seventy and five years old when he departed out of haran.

source_text: sa kauti serai o eparama kei loti na luvei tacina kei na veika kece e taukena era sa soqona mai kei ira na tamata era sa nona mai arana. era sa lako ki na vanua o kenani. era sa yaco mai kenani.
target_text: and abram took sarai his wife, and lot his brother's son, and all their substance that they had gathered, and the souls that they had gotten in haran; and they went forth to go into the land of canaan; and into the land of canaan they came.

source_text: sa lako curuma mai na vanua o eparama me yaco sara i sikemi ena vuni teribinici e more. era sa tiko ena vanua na kai kenani.
target_text: and abram passed through the land unto the place of sichem, unto the plain of moreh. and the canaanite was then in the land.

source_text: o jiova sa basika mai vei eparama ka tukuna vua, "ki vei ira na nomu kawa, au sa solia kina na vanua oqo. " sa tara mai kea o eparama e dua nai cabocabo ni soro vei jiova, o koya e a basika mai vua.
target_text: and the lord appeared unto abram, and said, unto thy seed will i give this land: and there builded he an altar unto the lord, who appeared unto him.

source_text: sa lako mai kea ki na veiulunivanua ena tokalau kei peceli, sa vakaduria mai kea na nona vale-laca, e peceli ena ra kei ai ena tokalau; mai kea sa tara kina e dua nai cabocabo ni soro ka kaciva na yaca i jiova.
target_text: and he removed from thence unto a mountain on the east of bethel, and pitched his tent, having bethel on the west, and hai on the east: and there he builded an altar unto the lord, and called upon the name of the lord.

source_text: sa lako tikoga o eparama, ka lako vakadodonu tikoga ki na ceva.
target_text: and abram journeyed, going on still toward the south.

source_text: sa dua na lauqa levu sa yaco ena vanua, o eparama sa lako sobu ki ijipita me la'ki tiko kina ni sa rui levu na lauqa ena vanua.
target_text: and there was a famine in the land: and abram went down into egypt to sojourn there; for the famine was grievous in the land.

source_text: sa qai yaco ni sa voleka yani ki ijipita, sa tukuna vei serai na watina, "raica, au sa kila ni o sa rui yalewa rairai totoka.
target_text: and it came to pass, when he was come near to enter into egypt, that he said unto sarai his wife, behold now, i know that thou art a fair woman to look upon:

source_text: "ena yaco ni ra sa raici iko na ijipita, era na tukuna ka vaka, 'oqo na watina, ' era na qai vakamatei au ka mo bula ga o iko.
target_text: therefore it shall come to pass, when the egyptians shall see thee, that they shall say, this is his wife: and they will kill me, but they will save thee alive.

source_text: "au kerea mo tukuna ni o iko na ganequ, me vinaka kina vei au ena vukumu, me'u bula kina baleti iko. "
target_text: say, i pray thee, thou art my sister: that it may be well with me for thy sake; and my soul shall live because of thee.

source_text: sa vaka kina ni sa yaco yani ki ijipita o eparama, era sa raica na yalewa na kai ijipita ni sa rui totoka dina.
target_text: and it came to pass, that, when abram was come into egypt, the egyptians beheld the woman that she was very fair.

source_text: o ira na sauturaga nei fero era sa raici serai talega ka vakatututaki koya sara vei fero. sa mai kau sara yani na yalewa oqo ki na vale nei fero.
target_text: the princes also of pharaoh saw her, and commended her before pharaoh: and the woman was taken into pharaoh's house.

source_text: sa qaravi vinaka o eparama ena vuku ni yalewa. sa tu talega na nona sipi, na bulumakau, na asa tagane, o ira na nona dauveiqaravi tagane kei na yalewa kei na kameli.
target_text: and he entreated abram well for her sake: and he had sheep, and oxen, and he asses, and menservants, and maidservants, and she asses, and camels.

source_text: o jiova, sa vakatubura vei fero kei na nona vuvale ena mate ca levu baleti serai na wati eparama.
target_text: and the lord plagued pharaoh and his house with great plagues because of sarai abram's wife.

source_text: sa kacivi eparama mai o fero ka taroga, "na cava o sa cakava oqo vei au? na cava o sega ni tukuna kina vei au ni o koya e watimu?
target_text: and pharaoh called abram, and said, what is this that thou hast done unto me? why didst thou not tell me that she was thy wife?

source_text: "na cava o tukuna kina ni 'o koya na ganemu? voleka sara ni'u kauti koya me watiqu. oqo, tauri koya yani ka lako ena nomu i lakolako. "
target_text: why saidst thou, she is my sister? so i might have taken her to me to wife: now therefore behold thy wife, take her, and go thy way.

source_text: sa solia nai vakaro o fero me baleti koya, era sa vakatalai koya yani kei serai na watina kei na ka kecega e nona.
target_text: and pharaoh commanded his men concerning him: and they sent him away, and his wife, and all that he had.

source_text: sa lako tani mai ijipita o eparama, kei watina kei na veika kece e nona, kei loti, mai na ceva.
target_text: and abram went up out of egypt, he, and his wife, and all that he had, and lot with him, into the south.

source_text: sa vutuniyau sara o eparama ena manumanu susu, ena siliva kei na koula.
target_text: and abram was very rich in cattle, in silver, and in gold.

source_text: sa lako yani ena nona i lakolako mai na ceva me yaco sara ki peceli “sa yaco sara yani ena vanua ea tiko kina e liu, o ya ena kedrau maliwa o peceli kei ai,
target_text: and he went on his journeys from the south even to bethel, unto the place where his tent had been at the beginning, between bethel and hai;

source_text: ki na vanua e a cakava kina nai cabocabo ni soro. e kea sa kaciva kina o eparama na yaca i jiova.
target_text: unto the place of the altar, which he had made there at the first: and there abram called on the name of the lord.

source_text: o loti talega “ni rau a lako vata kei eparama, sa levu sara na nona manumanu susu kei na nona bulumakau kei na nona veivale laca.
target_text: and lot also, which went with abram, had flocks, and herds, and tents.

source_text: sa sega ni levu na vanua me rau tiko kina, baleta ni sa rui levu na veika e rau taukena.
target_text: and the land was not able to bear them, that they might dwell together: for their substance was great, so that they could not dwell together.

source_text: era sa veiqati talega na dauqaravi ira na nodrau manumanu, na nei eparama kei na nei loti. o ira na kai kenani kei ira na perisaiti era sa tiko ena vanua.
target_text: and there was a strife between the herdmen of abram's cattle and the herdmen of lot's cattle: and the canaaniteand the perizzite dwelled then in the land.

source_text: sa tukuna o eparama vei loti, "raica, me daru kua ni veiqati, se o ira na nodaru dauqaravi manumanu, ni da sa veiwekani voleka.
target_text: and abram said unto lot, let there be no strife, i pray thee, between me and thee, and between my herdmen and thy herdmen; for we be brethren.

source_text: "sa sega beka ni tu oqori e matamu na vanua taucoko? au kerea, me daru sa tawase, kevaka o sa lako ki nai mawi, au na lako ki nai matau, se o lako ki nai matau, au na lako ki nai mawi. "
target_text: is not the whole land before thee? separate thyself, i pray thee, from me: if thou wilt take the left hand, then i will go to the right; or if thou depart to the right hand, then i will go to the left.

source_text: sa rai cake o loti ka raica na buca ena joritani, ni sa tu na wai e na veiyasana kecega (oqo ni se bera ni vakarusai kina o sotoma kei komora) ka sa vaka na were nei jiova, sa vaka na vanua mai ijipita ni o lako yani vaka ki soa.
target_text: and lot lifted up his eyes, and beheld all the plain of jordan, that it was well watered every where, before the lord destroyed sodom and gomorrah, even as the garden of the lord, like the land of egypt, as thou comest unto zoar.

source_text: sa digitaka o loti na buca ni joritani “sa lako ki na tokalau o loti. e rau sa veitawasei.
target_text: then lot chose him all the plain of jordan; and lot journeyed east: and they separated themselves the one from the other.

source_text: sa tiko e kenani o eparama, ka sa tiko ena veikoro mai na buca o loti, sa la'ki birika sara na nona vale-laca e sotoma.
target_text: abram dwelled in the land of canaan, and lot dwelled in the cities of the plain, and pitched his tent toward sodom.

source_text: o ira na tamata mai sotoma, era sa tamata i valavala vakasisila sara ka sinai e nai valavala ca vei jiova.
target_text: but the men of sodom were wicked and sinners before the lord exceedingly.

source_text: o jiova sa qai tukuna vei eparama ni sa lako tani mai vua o loti: "mo rai cake mai na vanua o sa tu kina oqori “ki na vualiku “ki na ceva “ki na tokalau - ki na ra;
target_text: and the lord said unto abram, after that lot was separated from him, lift up now thine eyes, and look from the place where thou art northward, and southward, and eastward, and westward:

source_text: "na vanua kece o sa raica oqori, au sa solia vei iko kei ira kece na nomu kawa me sega ni mudu.
target_text: for all the land which thou seest, to thee will i give it, and to thy seed for ever.

source_text: "au na cakava vei ira na nomu kawa me ra vaka na kuvu ni soso e vuravura; kevaka e dua na tamata e wilika rawa na kuvu ni soso “ena qai wiliki rawa na nomu kawa.
target_text: and i will make thy seed as the dust of the earth: so that if a man can number the dust of the earth, then shall thy seed also be numbered.

source_text: "oqo mo tu cake, ka lakova na balavu kei na kena raraba ni vanua au sa solia vei iko. "
target_text: arise, walk through the land in the length of it and in the breadth of it; for i will give it unto thee.

source_text: sa tucake o eparama ka lobika na nona valelaca ka lako yani ka la'ki tiko ena vuniterebinici e mamire, oqori e epironi, sa tara maikea e dua nai cabocabo ni soro vei jiova.
target_text: then abram removed his tent, and came and dwelt in the plain of mamre, which is in hebron, and built there an altar unto the lord.

source_text: sa qai yaco ena veisiga nei emarafeli na tui sina, arioki na tui elasa, jadorilaoma na tui ilama, kei tidala na tui ni veimatanitu,
target_text: and it came to pass in the days of amraphel king of shinar, arioch king of ellasar, chedorlaomer king of elam, and tidal king of nations;

source_text: era sa vala kei bera na tui sotoma “birisa na tui komora, o sinabe na tui atama, semeba na tui seboimi kei na tui bila (oqori o soa).
target_text: that these made war with bera king of sodom, and with birsha king of gomorrah, shinab king of admah, and shemeber king of zeboiim, and the king of bela, which is zoar.

source_text: o ira kece oqo era sa mai sotasota ena buca mai sidimi (oqori na waitui masima).
target_text: all these were joined together in the vale of siddim, which is the salt sea.

source_text: e tinikarua na yabaki era sa qaravi jadorilaoma, ena i ka tinikatolu ni yabaki, era sa via veicoqa ka talaidredre.
target_text: twelve years they served chedorlaomer, and in the thirteenth year they rebelled.

source_text: ena i katinikava ni yabaki, o jadorilaoma kei ira na tui era sa tiko vata era sa lako mai ka valuti refaimi e esitaroci karenaimi, o ira na susimi e ame, o ira na emimi e savei kiriacaimi,
target_text: and in the fourteenth year came chedorlaomer, and the kings that were with him, and smote the rephaims in ashteroth karnaim, and the zuzims in ham, and the emims in shaveh kiriathaim,

source_text: kei ira na oraite ena veiulunivanua e sairi, me yaco sara ki eli-perana o ya ena vanua liwa.
target_text: and the horites in their mount seir, unto elparan, which is by the wilderness.

source_text: era sa vuki lesu tale ka lako mai ki misifata (o ya o kadesi) ka valuti ira kece na amalekaiti kei ira na amoraiti, o ira sa vakaitikotiko e asesoni tamari.
target_text: and they returned, and came to enmishpat, which is kadesh, and smote all the country of the amalekites, and also the amorites, that dwelt in hazezontamar.

source_text: na tui sotoma, na tui komora, na tui atama, na tui seboimi kei tui bela (oqori o soa) era sa lako yani ka duavata ena i valu mai na buca o sidimi
target_text: and there went out the king of sodom, and the king of gomorrah, and the king of admah, and the king of zeboiim, and the king of bela (the same is zoar; ) and they joined battle with them in the vale of siddim;

source_text: me valuti jodarilaoma na tui ilama, tidala na tui ni veimatanitu, amarafaele na tui saina, kei arioki na tui elasa “e va na tui kei ira na lima na tui.
target_text: with chedorlaomer the king of elam, and with tidal king of nations, and amraphel king of shinar, and arioch king of ellasar; four kings with five.

source_text: na buca mai sidimi sa sinai kina na qara dregadregata; o ira na tui ni sotoma kei komora era sa dui dro, eso era sa lutu ki na qara ka so era dro ki na veiulunivanua.
target_text: and the vale of siddim was full of slimepits; and the kings of sodom and gomorrah fled, and fell there; and they that remained fled to the mountain.

source_text: era sa taura kece nai yaya vinaka mai sotoma kei komora kei na nodra i votavota ka era sa lako yani.
target_text: and they took all the goods of sodom and gomorrah, and all their victuals, and went their way.

source_text: era sa kauti loti talega “na luvei taci eparama, o koya sa tiko mai sotoma, kei na veika kece e nona, ka lako.
target_text: and they took lot, abram's brother's son, who dwelt in sodom, and his goods, and departed.

source_text: e dua vei ira sa dro mai, ka mai tukuna vei eparama na iperiu, ni sa tiko o koya mai mamire ena veivunikau e amoraiti, na taci esekoli, na taci ena, era sa duavata kei eparama.
target_text: and there came one that had escaped, and told abram the hebrew; for he dwelt in the plain of mamre the amorite, brother of eshcol, and brother of aner: and these were confederate with abram.

source_text: ni sa rogoca o eparama, sa kau vakavesu na tacina, sa vakayaragitaki ira na tolu na drau tinikalima na nona dauveiqaravi sa vakavulici oti, o ira oqo, era sa sucu ga ena nona loma ni vale, era sa cici muri yani vaka ki tani.
target_text: and when abram heard that his brother was taken captive, he armed his trained servants, born in his own house, three hundred and eighteen, and pursued them unto dan.

source_text: sa wasei ira na nona i valu ena bogi. o koya kei ira na nona tamata era cici muri ira na meca me yaco sara ki oba ena vualiku kei tamasiko.
target_text: and he divided himself against them, he and his servants, by night, and smote them, and pursued them unto hobah, which is on the left hand of damascus.

source_text: sa kauta lesu mai na vei ka kece nei loti kei loti talega, o ira na yalewa kei ira kecega na tamata.
target_text: and he brought back all the goods, and also brought again his brother lot, and his goods, and the women also, and the people.

source_text: sa lako yani o tui sotoma me sotavi koya mai na buca o savei (oqori na tui ni buca) ena nona lesu mai ena nona vakadrukai o jadorilaoma kei ira na tui era sa tiko vata.
target_text: and the king of sodom went out to meet him after his return from the slaughter of chedorlaomer, and of the kings that were with him, at the valley of shaveh, which is the king's dale.

source_text: o melekisateki na tui salemi sa kauta mai na madrai kei na waini. o koya oqo na bete nei koya na kalou cecere.
target_text: and melchizedek king of salem brought forth bread and wine: and he was the priest of the most high god.

source_text: sa vosa vakalouvinakataki eparama ka vaka: "me kalouvinaka o eparama ni kalou cecere, na i taukei, ka lewa na lomalagi kei vuravura;
target_text: and he blessed him, and said, blessed be abram of the most high god, possessor of heaven and earth:

source_text: me kalouvinaka talega na kalou sa cecere sara, o koya sa soli ira na kemu meca e ligamu. " sa solia vua o eparaama nai sigana (katini) kecega.
target_text: and blessed be the most high god, which hath delivered thine enemies into thy hand. and he gave him tithes of all.

source_text: sa tukuna na tui sotoma vei eparama, "mo soli ira na tamata mai vei au ka kauta kece na veika sa tu oqori. "
target_text: and the king of sodom said unto abram, give me the persons, and take the goods to thyself.

source_text: sa sauma yani o eparama vei tui sotoma, "au sa laveta oti na ligaqu vei jiova, na kalou cecere, nai taukei kei lomalagi kei vuravura,
target_text: and abram said to the king of sodom, i have lift up mine hand unto the lord, the most high god, the possessor of heaven and earth,

source_text: "ni'u na sega ni kauta e dua na ka, mai nai vesu ni vava, au na sega ni kauta e dua na ka e nomu, de o na tukuna, 'au sa vaka vutuniyautaki eparama'”
target_text: that i will not take from a thread even to a shoelatchet, and that i will not take any thing that is thine, lest thou shouldest say, i have made abram rich:

source_text: "vakavo walega na veika era sa kania na cauravou, nai votavota ni tamata era sa lako vata kei au: o ana, o esikoli, kei mamire; me ratou kauta na nodratou i votavota. "
target_text: save only that which the young men have eaten, and the portion of the men which went with me, aner, eshcol, and mamre; let them take their portion.

source_text: ni sa oti oqo, sa lako mai na vosa i jiova vei eparama ena raivotu ka tukuna, "mo kua ni rere eparama, oi au na nomu i sasabai, kei na nomu i votavota e levu sara. "
target_text: after these things the word of the lord came unto abram in a vision, saying, fear not, abram: i am thy shield, and thy exceeding great reward.

source_text: sa tukuna mai o eparama, "i jiova na noqu kalou, na cava o ni na solia vei au, sa sega na luvequ, na kawa ga ni noqu o iliesa na kai tamasiko? "
target_text: and abram said, lord god, what wilt thou give me, seeing i go childless, and the steward of my house is this eliezer of damascus?

source_text: sa tukuna tale o eparama, "raica o ni sa sega ni solia vei au na kawa: me dua ga e sucu e noqu vale me noqu kawa! "
target_text: and abram said, behold, to me thou hast given no seed: and, lo, one born in my house is mine heir.

source_text: sa qai lako tale mai vua na vosa i jiova ka vaka: "o iliesa ena sega ni nomu kawa, e dua ga ena lako mai ena yagomu dina ena wili me nomu kawa. "
target_text: and, behold, the word of the lord came unto him, saying, this shall not be thine heir; but he that shall come forth out of thine own bowels shall be thine heir.

source_text: o jiova sa qai kauti koya i tuba ka tukuna, "mo rai mada i lomalagi ka wilika mada na veikalokalo, kevaka e rawa ni o wilika ira, " sa tukuna tale vua, "era na vaka oqori na nomu kawa. "
target_text: and he brought him forth abroad, and said, look now toward heaven, and tell the stars, if thou be able to number them: and he said unto him, so shall thy seed be.

source_text: sa vakabauti jiova o eparama, na kalou sa wiliki eparama me yalododonu.
target_text: and he believed in the lord; and he counted it to him for righteousness.

source_text: na kalou sa vosa vei eparama ka vaka, "oi au o jiova, o koya sa kauti iko mai uri e kalitia, me'u solia vei iko na vanua oqo mo taukena. "
target_text: and he said unto him, i am the lord that brought thee out of ur of the chaldees, to give thee this land to inherit it.

source_text: sa sauma yani o eparama, "i jiova na kalou me'u kila vakacava ni'u na taukena? "
target_text: and he said, lord god, whereby shall i know that i shall inherit it?

source_text: na kalou sa sauma vei eparama, "kauta mai vei au e dua na luve ni bulumakau yabaki tolu, e dua na me yalewa yabaki tolu, e dua na luve ni sipi yabaki tolu, e dua na ruve dina kei na dua na ruve kawa vata. "
target_text: and he said unto him, take me an heifer of three years old, and a she goat of three years old, and a ram of three years old, and a turtledove, and a young pigeon.

source_text: sa kauta kece mai oqo o eparama vei jiova musuka wase rua na manumanu kece ka sega ga na ruve e rua oqo.
target_text: and he took unto him all these, and divided them in the midst, and laid each piece one against another: but the birds divided he not.

source_text: ni ra sa vuka sobu mai na tuivucilevu me ra mai kana, sa cemuri ira tikoga o eparama.
target_text: and when the fowls came down upon the carcases, abram drove them away.

source_text: ni sa dromu sobu na siga, sa tarai eparama e dua na via moce levu, sa yaco mai vua e dua na rere kei na butobuto levu.
target_text: and when the sun was going down, a deep sleep fell upon abram; and, lo, an horror of great darkness fell upon him.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna vei eparama, "mo kila oqo “ni o ira na nomu kawa era na vulagi ena vanua oqo, o koya sa sega ni nodra, era na qaravi ira, era na vakararawataki kemuni me va na drau na yabaki.
target_text: and he said unto abram, know of a surety that thy seed shall be a stranger in a land that is not theirs, and shall serve them; and they shall afflict them four hundred years;

source_text: "na matanitu talega era na qarava, au na veilewaitaki ira “ni oti o ya era na qai sereki mai kei na veika era na taukena, ena levu sara.
target_text: and also that nation, whom they shall serve, will i judge: and afterward shall they come out with great substance.

source_text: "o iko, o na lako vei ira na tamamu ena vakacegu. o na buluti ni o sa qase vinaka sara.
target_text: and thou shalt go to thy fathers in peace; thou shalt be buried in a good old age.

source_text: "ena i kava ni tabatamata, era na qai lesu tale mai eke, baleta na nodra talaidredre vakasisila na amoraiti e se bera ni taucoko. "
target_text: but in the fourth generation they shall come hither again: for the iniquity of the amorites is not yet full.

source_text: sa oti oqo, sa qai dromu na matanisiga, sa butobuto sara, sa dua na lovo sa kuvu tiko, kei na yameyame sa caudre tiko, sa lako voli ena kedra maliwa na lewe ni manumanu.
target_text: and it came to pass, that, when the sun went down, and it was dark, behold a smoking furnace, and a burning lamp that passed between those pieces.

source_text: ena siga vata ga o ya, sa cakava kina e dua na veiyalayalati o jiova kei eparama ka vaka: "kivei ira na nomu kawa au sa solia kina na vanua oqo, mai na uciwai mai ijipita ki na uciwai levu na uferetisi”
target_text: in the same day the lord made a covenant with abram, saying, unto thy seed have i given this land, from the river of egypt unto the great river, the river euphrates:

source_text: "na kenaiti, na kenaseraiti kei na kadomonaiti,
target_text: the kenites, and the kenizzites, and the kadmonites,

source_text: "na itaiti, na perisaiti kei na refaimi,
target_text: and the hittites, and the perizzites, and the rephaims,

source_text: "na amoraiti, na kenaninaiti, na qeviqasaiti kei na jepusaiti. "
target_text: and the amorites, and the canaanites, and the girgashites, and the jebusites.

source_text: o serai na wati eparama, e se sega tikoga ni vakasucuma e dua na gone. sa tiko vei koya e dua na yalewa dauveiqaravi ni ijipita, na yacana o eka.
target_text: now sarai abram's wife bare him no children: and she had an handmaid, an egyptian, whose name was hagar.

source_text: sa tukuna o serai vei eparama, "raica o jiova sa tarovi au me'u vakaluveni, au kerea mo curumi koya na noqu dauveiqaravi, me dua kina na noqu gone mai vua. " sa vakaio sara ga o eparama ki na vosa nei serai.
target_text: and sarai said unto abram, behold now, the lord hath restrained me from bearing: i pray thee, go in unto my maid; it may be that i may obtain children by her. and abram hearkened to the voice of sarai.

source_text: o serai na wati eparama sa kauti eka mai ka solia vei eparama me rau veiwatini, oqo ni sa oti e tini na yabaki ena nona tiko e kenani o eparama.
target_text: and sarai abram's wife took hagar her maid the egyptian, after abram had dwelt ten years in the land of canaan, and gave her to her husband abram to be his wife.

source_text: sa curumi eka o eparama, ka sa kunekune sara o eka, sa mani dokadoka kina na matana.
target_text: and he went in unto hagar, and she conceived: and when she saw that she had conceived, her mistress was despised in her eyes.

source_text: sa tukuna o serai vei eparama, "sa baleti au ga na noqu cala, baleta ni'u soli eka ki lomaseremu, ni sa kila o koya ni sa kunekune tiko, sa beci au vakalevu na matana. me qai lewa o jiova ena vukudaru. "
target_text: and sarai said unto abram, my wrong be upon thee: i have given my maid into thy bosom; and when she saw that she had conceived, i was despised in her eyes: the lord judge between me and thee.

source_text: sa tukuna o eparama vei serai, "sa tikoga e ligamu na nomu vada; mo cakava vua na veika ga o vinakata. " ni sa cakacaka vakaukauwa vua o serai, sa qai yaco me sa dro yani na nona vada, mai vua.
target_text: but abram said unto sarai, behold, thy maid is in thy hand; do to her as it pleaseth thee. and when sarai dealt hardly with her, she fled from her face.

source_text: na agilosi i jiova sa raici eka ena dua na mata ni wai ena vanua liwa, oqo, ena sala vaka ki suri.
target_text: and the angel of the lord found her by a fountain of water in the wilderness, by the fountain in the way to shur.

source_text: sa tukuna sara, "i eka na dauveiqaravi nei serai, o lako tu mai vei, o lako tiko i vei? " sa sauma mai, "au sa dro tiko mai vua na noqu marama o serai. "
target_text: and he said, hagar, sarai's maid, whence camest thou? and whither wilt thou go? and she said, i flee from the face of my mistress sarai.

source_text: na agilosi i jiova sa tukuna vua, "mo lesu tale vua na nomu marama ka vakamalumalumutaki iko e ligana. "
target_text: and the angel of the lord said unto her, return to thy mistress, and submit thyself under her hands.

source_text: na agilosi i jiova sa tukuna vua, "au na vakalewevuqataka na nomu kawa me ra na sega ni wili rawa. "
target_text: and the angel of the lord said unto her, i will multiply thy seed exceedingly, that it shall not be numbered for multitude.

source_text: na agilosi i jiova sa tukuna tale vua, "raica, o sa tiko vata kei na gone, o na vakasucuma e dua na gone tagane, mo vakayacani koya o isimeli, baleta ni sa rogoca na nomu vakararawataki o jiova.
target_text: and the angel of the lord said unto her, behold, thou art with child, and shalt bear a son, and shalt call his name ishmael; because the lord hath heard thy affliction.

source_text: ena tamata kila o koya, na ligana ena veivala kei ira na tamata kecega, kei na ligadra na tamata kecega era na veivala kei na ligana. ena tiko o koya e matadra na tacina. "
target_text: and he will be a wild man; his hand will be against every man, and every man's hand against him; and he shall dwell in the presence of all his brethren.

source_text: sa qai masuta na yacai jiova, o koya sa vosa vua, sai-kemuni-na-kalou-sa-rai tiko ni sa tukuna, "au sa raici koya beka, o koya sa raici au talega? "
target_text: and she called the name of the lord that spake unto her, thou god seest me: for she said, have i also here looked after him that seeth me?

source_text: sa vakayacani na mataniwai o ya me bea-laeiroi, oqo ena kedrau maliwa o ketesa kei bereti.
target_text: wherefore the well was called beerlahairoi; behold, it is between kadesh and bered.

source_text: o eka sa vakasucuma vei eparama e dua na gone tagane, na gone sa vakasucuma oqo o eka, sa vakayacani koya o eparama me o isimeli.
target_text: and hagar bare abram a son: and abram called his son's name, which hagar bare, ishmael.

source_text: sa yabaki walusagavulu ka ono o eparama ni sa vakasucuma vua o eka, na gonetagane sa vakayacani o isimeli.
target_text: and abram was fourscore and six years old, when hagar bare ishmael to abram.

source_text: ena gauna sa yabaki ciwasagavulu ka ciwa sa basika vua o jiova ka tukuna vua, "oi au na kalou kaukauwa, mo lako vakadodonu e mataqu ka mo kakua ni cala.
target_text: and when abram was ninety years old and nine, the lord appeared to abram, and said unto him, i am the almighty god; walk before me, and be thou perfect.

source_text: "au na cakava na noqu veiyalayalati, o au kei iko, au na vakalevutaka sara na nomu kawa. "
target_text: and i will make my covenant between me and thee, and will multiply thee exceedingly.

source_text: sa cuva vakatoboicu o eparama, ka rau sa veivosaki kei na kalou ka vaka:
target_text: and abram fell on his face: and god talked with him, saying,

source_text: "mai vei au, raica, na noqu veiyalayalati sa tiko vata kei iko, o na tamadra na veimatanitu.
target_text: as for me, behold, my covenant is with thee, and thou shalt be a father of many nations.

source_text: "ena sega ni yacamu tiko o eparama, oqo sa yacamu o eparaama, ni'u sa vakavuna vei iko mo tamadra na veimatanitu.
target_text: neither shall thy name any more be called abram, but thy name shall be abraham; for a father of many nations have i made thee.

source_text: "au na vakayacora vei iko mo vuavuai; au na vakatubura mai vei iko na veimatanitu, era na tubu mai vei iko na tui.
target_text: and i will make thee exceeding fruitful, and i will make nations of thee, and kings shall come out of thee.

source_text: "au na vakadeitaka na noqu veiyalayalati ena kedaru maliwa kei ira na nomu kawa era na muri mai, ena nodra dui tabatamata, me veiyalayalati e sega ni mudu, me kalou vei iko kei ira kecega era na muri mai vei iko.
target_text: and i will establish my covenant between me and thee and thy seed after thee in their generations for an everlasting covenant, to be a god unto thee, and to thy seed after thee.

source_text: "au sa solia talega vei iko kei ira na nomu kawa era na muri mai na vanua oqo dou sa tiko vulagi kina, na vanua kece o kenani, mo ni taukena me sega ni mudu; oi au, me'u nodra kalou talega. "
target_text: and i will give unto thee, and to thy seed after thee, the land wherein thou art a stranger, all the land of canaan, for an everlasting possession; and i will be their god.

source_text: sa tukuna na kalou vei eparaama, "o iko, mo maroroya na noqu veiyalayalati, o iko kei ira kece na nomu kawa ki na nodra i tabatamata kecega.
target_text: and god said unto abraham, thou shalt keep my covenant therefore, thou, and thy seed after thee in their generations.

source_text: "oqo na noqu veiyalayalati mo na maroroya, ena kedaru maliwa kei ira na nomu kawa era na muri mai: o ira kece na gone era tagane ena kemuni maliwa, me ra cilivi;
target_text: this is my covenant, which ye shall keep, between me and you and thy seed after thee; every man child among you shall be circumcised.

source_text: "me cilivi na yagomuni vakatagane, oqo mei vakatakilakila ni veiyalayalati ena kedaru maliwa.
target_text: and ye shall circumcise the flesh of your foreskin; and it shall be a token of the covenant betwixt me and you.

source_text: sa qai vakatauca o jiova na kuvu kama, kei na bukawaqa e sotoma kei komore, mai vei jiova mai lomalagi.
target_text: then the lord rained upon sodom and upon gomorrah brimstone and fire from the lord out of heaven;

source_text: o jiova sa vuaviritaka na veikoro oqori, na veibuca kei ira kece na lewe ni koro kei na veika sa tubu mai na qele.
target_text: and he overthrew those cities, and all the plain, and all the inhabitants of the cities, and that which grew upon the ground.

source_text: o watina sa rai lesu me raici loti, ka sa yaco me duru vatu (masima).
target_text: but his wife looked back from behind him, and she became a pillar of salt.

source_text: sa lako vaka mataka o eparaama, ena vanua sa tu kina o koya ena mata i jiova.
target_text: and abraham gat up early in the morning to the place where he stood before the lord:

source_text: sa rai yani vaka ki sotoma kei komora, kei na veivanua vaka ki na buca, ka sa raica na kubou ni vanua sa vaka na kubou ni dua na kama levu.
target_text: and he looked toward sodom and gomorrah, and toward all the land of the plain, and beheld, and, lo, the smoke of the country went up as the smoke of a furnace.

source_text: sa qai yaco ni sa vakarusa oti na kalou na veikoro kece mai na buca, na kalou sa qai nanumi eparaama, ka sa qai vakatalai loti tani mai na nona vuaviri oqo, ni sa vuaviritaka na veikoro sa tiko kina o loti.
target_text: and it came to pass, when god destroyed the cities of the plain, that god remembered abraham, and sent lot out of the midst of the overthrow, when he overthrew the cities in the which lot dwelt.

source_text: sa lako tani mai soa o loti ka la'ki tiko ena veiulunivanua vata kei rau na luvena yalewa. ni sa rere ni tiko e soa. e ratou sa la'ki tiko ena veiqaravatu.
target_text: and lot went up out of zoar, and dwelt in the mountain, and his two daughters with him; for he feared to dwell in zoar: and he dwelt in a cave, he and his two daughters.

source_text: sa tukuna o koya e qase veirau na yalewa vei koya e gone, "sa qase o tamadaru, sa sega na tagane me mai curumi kedaru me vaka na kena i valavala e vuravura.
target_text: and the firstborn said unto the younger, our father is old, and there is not a man in the earth to come in unto us after the manner of all the earth:

source_text: "me daru vakamatenitaki tamadaru ena waini, ka me daru curumi kina mai vua, me daru maroroya kina na kawa mai vei tamadaru. "
target_text: come, let us make our father drink wine, and we will lie with him, that we may preserve seed of our father.

source_text: e rau sa vakagunuvi tamadrau ena waini ena bogi o ya, sa lako yani o koya e qase ka vakacurumi tamana vua. sa sega ni kila o tamana na nona lako yani kei na nona lesu mai.
target_text: and they made their father drink wine that night: and the firstborn went in, and lay with her father; and he perceived not when she lay down, nor when she arose.

source_text: ena siga ka tarava, sa tukuna na qase vua na tacina gone, "au sa vakacurumi tamaqu oti vei au ena bogi, oqo me daru cakava tale na waini, me gunu ena bogi oqo, ka mo lako yani, ka vakacurumi koya vei iko me maroroi kina na kawa mai vei tamadaru. "
target_text: and it came to pass on the morrow, that the firstborn said unto the younger, behold, i lay yesternight with my father: let us make him drink wine this night also; and go thou in, and lie with him, that we may preserve seed of our father.

source_text: e rau sa vakagunuvi tamadrau ena bogi o ya. sa tucake yani o koya e gone, ka la'ki vakacurumi tamana vua. sa sega ni kila o tamana na nona lako yani kei na nona lesu mai.
target_text: and they made their father drink wine that night also: and the younger arose, and lay with him; and he perceived not when she lay down, nor when she arose.

source_text: oi rau ruarua na luvei loti yalewa oqo, e rau sa vakagone mai vei tamadrau.
target_text: thus were both the daughters of lot with child by their father.

source_text: sa vakasucuma e dua na gone tagane o koya e qase, ka sa vakayacani me o moape; o koya sa tamadra na moape me yacova na siga oqo.
target_text: and the firstborn bare a son, and called his name moab: the same is the father of the moabites unto this day.

source_text: o koya talega sa gone veirau, sa vakasucuma e dua talega na gone tagane, ka sa vakayacani me peni-ame (peniame). o koya oqo na tamadra na amoni me yacova na siga oqo.
target_text: and the younger, she also bare a son, and called his name benammi: the same is the father of the children of ammon unto this day.

source_text: sa lako yani o eparaama mai kea vaka ki na ceva me tiko ena kedrau maliwa o ketesa kei suri ka lako sara yani ki kerari.
target_text: and abraham journeyed from thence toward the south country, and dwelled between kadesh and shur, and sojourned in gerar.

source_text: sa tukuna o eparaama ena vuku i sera na watina, "ni o koya na ganena. " sa talatala yani o apimeleki na tui kerari, me kau mai vua o sera.
target_text: and abraham said of sarah his wife, she is my sister: and abimelech king of gerar sent, and took sarah.

source_text: na kalou sa lako mai vei apimeleki ena tadra e na bogi ka tukuna vua, "mo kila ni o sa tamata mate ena vuku ni yalewa o sa taura mai; ni sa watina e dua na tagane o koya. "
target_text: but god came to abimelech in a dream by night, and said to him, behold, thou art but a dead man, for the woman which thou hast taken; for she is a man's wife.

source_text: ia, o apimeleki e se bera ni tarai koya, ka sa tukuna kina, "i jiova, o ni na vakarusa talega e dua na matanitu yalododonu?
target_text: but abimelech had not come near her: and he said, lord, wilt thou slay also a righteous nation?

source_text: "e sega beka ni a tukuna vei au, 'o koya na ganequ'? na yalewa mada sa tukuna 'ni o koya o ya na ganena tagane. ' ena dina ni yaloqu kei na savasava ni ligaqu, au sa cakava kina oqo. "
