target_text: said he not unto me, she is my sister? and she, even she herself said, he is my brother: in the integrity of my heart and innocency of my hands have i done this.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna vua ena tadra, "au sa kila ni o cakava oqo ena dina ni yalomu, o au talega talega, au sa tarovi iko mo kua ni valavala ca vei au, oqori na vuna au sega ni vakatara kina mo tarai koya.
target_text: and god said unto him in a dream, yea, i know that thou didst this in the integrity of thy heart; for i also withheld thee from sinning against me: therefore suffered i thee not to touch her.

source_text: "mo vakasuka tale na yalewa vua na watina, ni sa parofita o koya, ena qai masulaki iko; o na qai bula. kevaka o sa sega ni cakava oqo “o na mate vakaidina, o iko kei ira kecega sa nomu. "
target_text: now therefore restore the man his wife; for he is a prophet, and he shall pray for thee, and thou shalt live: and if thou restore her not, know thou that thou shalt surely die, thou, and all that are thine.

source_text: sa sou o apimeleki ka kacivi ira na nona tamata, ka tukuna na veika kece oqo ni ra sa vakarorogo tu, era se rere na nona tamata.
target_text: therefore abimelech rose early in the morning, and called all his servants, and told all these things in their ears: and the men were sore afraid.

source_text: o apimeleki sa kacivi eparaama ka tukuna vua, "na cava o sa cakava vei keimami? na cala cava au cakava vei iko, mo kauta mai kina ki na noqu matanitu, na i valavala ca levu oqo? o sa cakava vei au na veika e sega ni dodonu me caka. "
target_text: then abimelech called abraham, and said unto him, what hast thou done unto us? and what have i offended thee, that thou hast brought on me and on my kingdom a great sin? thou hast done deeds unto me that ought not to be done.

source_text: sa qai tukuna o apimeleki vei eparaama, "na cava o nanuma, ena nomu cakava kina vei au na ka oqo? "
target_text: and abimelech said unto abraham, what sawest thou, that thou hast done this thing?

source_text: sa sauma mai o eparaama, "baleta au sa kila ni sa sega eke na rerevaka na kalou, era na vakamatei au kina ena vuku i watiqu.
target_text: and abraham said, because i thought, surely the fear of god is not in this place; and they will slay me for my wife's sake.

source_text: "o sa dina, e ganequ dina o koya, o koya e luvei tamaqu, ka sega ga ni luvei tinaqu, oqori sa mai watiqu kina.
target_text: and yet indeed she is my sister; she is the daughter of my father, but not the daughter of my mother; and she became my wife.

source_text: "ni sa vakavuna na kalou, me'u lako tani mai na vale i tamaqu, au sa tukuna kina vua, 'oqo na ka vinaka mo cakava vei au; ena vanua kecega daru na lako kina, mo na tukuna ni, "o koya na ganequ. "'"
target_text: and it came to pass, when god caused me to wander from my father's house, that i said unto her, this is thy kindness which thou shalt shew unto me; at every place whither we shall come, say of me, he is my brother.

source_text: sa kauta mai o apimeleki na sipi kei na bulumakau kei ira na dauveiqaravi tagane kei na yalewa, ka soli ira vei eparaama, ka sa soli sera lesu tale vua.
target_text: and abimelech took sheep, and oxen, and menservants, and womenservants, and gave them unto abraham, and restored him sarah his wife.

source_text: sa tukuna o apimeleki, "raica na vanua sa tu oqori e matamu, mo tiko ena vanua o vinakata. "
target_text: and abimelech said, behold, my land is before thee: dwell where it pleaseth thee.

source_text: sa tukuna talega vei sera, "raica au sa solia vei ganemu e dua na udolu na tiki ni siliva, oqo me vakagalalataki iko mai vei ira kecega na tamata" “oqo sa vakadonui kina o sera.
target_text: and unto sarah he said, behold, i have given thy brother a thousand pieces of silver: behold, he is to thee a covering of the eyes, unto all that are with thee, and with all other: thus she was reproved.

source_text: o eparaama sa masu vua na kalou: na kalou sa vakabulai apimeleki, na watina kei ira na nona dauveiqaravi. sa tekivu me ra vakaluveni;
target_text: so abraham prayed unto god: and god healed abimelech, and his wife, and his maidservants; and they bare children.

source_text: ni o jiova, sa sogota kece na kato ni gone ena vuvale kece nei apimeleki, baleti sera na wati eparaama.
target_text: for the lord had fast closed up all the wombs of the house of abimelech, because of sarah abraham's wife.

source_text: o jiova, sa sikovi sera me vaka ga ea tukuna, o jiova, sa cakava vei sera me vaka ga ea tukuna.
target_text: and the lord visited sarah as he had said, and the lord did unto sarah as he had spoken.

source_text: sa kunekune o sera ka vakasucuma vei eparaama e dua na luvena tagane ni sa qase sara, ena gauna lokuci ga sa vosa kina vua na kalou.
target_text: for sarah conceived, and bare abraham a son in his old age, at the set time of which god had spoken to him.

source_text: sa vakayacani koya o eparaama, na luvena tagane” na luvena tagane sa vakasucuma o sera “me o aisake.
target_text: and abraham called the name of his son that was born unto him, whom sarah bare to him, isaac.

source_text: o eparaama sa cilivi na luvena o aisake ni sa bogi walu oti, me vaka sa vakarota vua na kalou.
target_text: and abraham circumcised his son isaac being eight days old, as god had commanded him.

source_text: sa yabaki dua na drau o eparaama ena gauna sa sucu kina o aisake.
target_text: and abraham was an hundred years old, when his son isaac was born unto him.

source_text: sa tukuna o sera, "na kalou sa vakavuna me'u dredre, ni o ira kece era na rogoca, era na dredre vata kei au. "
target_text: and sarah said, god hath made me to laugh, so that all that hear will laugh with me.

source_text: sa tukuna talega, "o cei ena tukuna rawa vei eparaama, ni na mea e dua na gone o sera? ni'u sa vakasucuma vua e dua na gone vua ni sa qase sara o koya. "
target_text: and she said, who would have said unto abraham, that sarah should have given children suck? for i have born him a son in his old age.

source_text: sa tubu cake na gone ka sa kali sara. sa cakava o eparaama e dua na kakana levu ena siga sa kali kina o aisake.
target_text: and the child grew, and was weaned: and abraham made a great feast the same day that isaac was weaned.

source_text: o sera, sa raica na luvei eka na yalewa ni ijipita vei eparaama ni veivakalialiai tiko.
target_text: and sarah saw the son of hagar the egyptian, which she had born unto abraham, mocking.

source_text: sa tukuna kina vei eparaama, "mo vakagalalataki rau na yalewa bobula kei na luvena; na luvena na yalewa bobula ena sega ni mai taukei vata kei na luvequ o aisake. "
target_text: wherefore she said unto abraham, cast out this bondwoman and her son: for the son of this bondwoman shall not be heir with my son, even with isaac.

source_text: na veika oqo sa sega ni taleitaka o eparaama baleta na luvena o isimeli.
target_text: and the thing was very grievous in abraham's sight because of his son.

source_text: ia, na kalou sa tukuna vei eparaama, "me kakua ni vakararawataki iko na veika me baleta na gone se o tinana na yalewa bobula. na veika sa tukuna vei iko o sera, mo rogoca na domona, baleta ena lako mai vei aisake na nomu kawa.
target_text: and god said unto abraham, let it not be grievous in thy sight because of the lad, and because of thy bondwoman; in all that sarah hath said unto thee, hearken unto her voice; for in isaac shall thy seed be called.

source_text: "au na cakava talega e dua na matanitu mai vua na luve ni bobula, baleta ni sa luvemu talega. "
target_text: and also of the son of the bondwoman will i make a nation, because he is thy seed.

source_text: sa sou ena mataka o eparaama ka kauta na madrai kei na wai, ka biuta e domo i eka ka solia na gone vua, sa qai vakatalai rau yani. e rau sa lako yani ka lako voli ena vanua liwa e perisepa.
target_text: and abraham rose up early in the morning, and took bread, and a bottle of water, and gave it unto hagar, putting it on her shoulder, and the child, and sent her away: and she departed, and wandered in the wilderness of beersheba.

source_text: sa maca na wai mai na kena bola, ka sa vakadabera tiko na gone ena dua na veico.
target_text: and the water was spent in the bottle, and she cast the child under one of the shrubs.

source_text: sa lako yani o tinana, ka la'ki dabe veibasai tiko mai vei koya, me vaka e dua nai vana ena dakai titi, ni sa tukuna tikoga e lomana, "me'u kua ni raica na nona mate na gone. " sa dabe tikoga mai vakayawa ka tagi tiko vakadomoilevu.
target_text: and she went, and sat her down over against him a good way off, as it were a bowshot: for she said, let me not see the death of the child. and she sat over against him, and lift up her voice, and wept.

source_text: na kalou sa rogoca na domo ni gone, ka sa kaci yani vei eka na agilosi ni kalou mai lomalagi ka tukuna vua, "na cava o sa tagi kina eka? kua ni rere, na kalou sa rogoca na domona na gone mai na vanua e tiko kina.
target_text: and god heard the voice of the lad; and the angel of god called to hagar out of heaven, and said unto her, what aileth thee, hagar? fear not; for god hath heard the voice of the lad where he is.

source_text: "mo tucake, keveta na gone e ligamu, ni'u na cakava me matanitu levu o koya. "
target_text: arise, lift up the lad, and hold him in thine hand; for i will make him a great nation.

source_text: na kalou sa vakaraitaka na matana, ka sa raica sara e dua na tobu wai. sa la'ki takiva sara na wai ena kena bola, ka solia vua na gone me gunu.
target_text: and god opened her eyes, and she saw a well of water; and she went, and filled the bottle with water, and gave the lad drink.

source_text: na kalou sa tiko vata kei na gone; sa tubu cake na gone ka sa dau tiko ena vanua liwa, sa yaco talega me dauvavana.
target_text: and god was with the lad; and he grew, and dwelt in the wilderness, and became an archer.

source_text: sa dautiko ena vanua liwa mai parana, sa kauta vua o tinana e dua na watina mai na vanua o ijipita. e dua na veiyalayalati vata kei apimeleki
target_text: and he dwelt in the wilderness of paran: and his mother took him a wife out of the land of egypt.

source_text: sa yaco mai e dua na gauna, o apimeleki kei fikoli, (nai liuliu ni mataivalu na apimeleki) e rau sa veivosaki kei eparaama ka vaka: "sa tiko vata kei iko na kalou ena veika kecega o cakava.
target_text: and it came to pass at that time, that abimelech and phichol the chief captain of his host spake unto abraham, saying, god is with thee in all that thou doest:

source_text: "mo yalataka vei au ena kalou, ni o na sega ni cakacaka vaka i lasu vei au, vei ira na noqu kawa kei na veika au taukena; me vaka ga na veika vivinaka au sa cakava vei iko, mo cakava vaka kina vei au, ki na vanua talega o na lako kina. "
target_text: now therefore swear unto me here by god that thou wilt not deal falsely with me, nor with my son, nor with my son's son: but according to the kindness that i have done unto thee, thou shalt do unto me, and to the land wherein thou hast sojourned.

source_text: sa sauma o eparaama, "au na cakava vaka kina. "
target_text: and abraham said, i will swear.

source_text: o eparaama sa vakadodonutaki apimeleki, baleta na mataniwai era sa taura vakaukauwa na dauveiqaravi nei apimeleki.
target_text: and abraham reproved abimelech because of a well of water, which abimelech's servants had violently taken away.

source_text: sa tukuna o apimeleki, "au sega ni kila, se o cei sa cakava na ka oqo: o iko sa sega ni tukuna vei au, se me'u rogoca me yacova na siga oqo. "
target_text: and abimelech said, i wot not who hath done this thing: neither didst thou tell me, neither yet heard i of it, but to day.

source_text: sa taura na sipi kei na bulumakau o eparaama ka solia vei apimeleki, ka ra sa cakava e dua na veiyalayalati.
target_text: and abraham took sheep and oxen, and gave them unto abimelech; and both of them made a covenant.

source_text: sa vakatala yani o eparaama e vitu na luve ni sipi vakataki ira ga.
target_text: and abraham set seven ewe lambs of the flock by themselves.

source_text: sa tarogi eparaama o apimeleki, "na cava na kena i balebale oqo, na lami o sa vakatalai ira oqo? "
target_text: and abimelech said unto abraham, what mean these seven ewe lambs which thou hast set by themselves?

source_text: sa tukuna mai, "mo taura mai ligaqu na lami oqo, me noqu i vakadinadina ni'u sa kelia na tobu oqo. "
target_text: and he said, for these seven ewe lambs shalt thou take of my hand, that they may be a witness unto me, that i have digged this well.

source_text: sa vakayacani kina na vanua me perisepa, baleta ni rau sa bubului ena veiyalayalati e kea.
target_text: wherefore he called that place beersheba; because there they sware both of them.

source_text: e rau sa cakava na veiyalayalati e perisepa, sa tucake o apimeleki kei fikoli (nai liuliu ni mataivalu) ka rau sa lesu tale ki na vanua o filisitia.
target_text: thus they made a covenant at beersheba: then abimelech rose up, and phichol the chief captain of his host, and they returned into the land of the philistines.

source_text: sa tea o eparaama e dua na vu ni tamarisi e perisepa, ka sa kaciva mai kea na yaca i jiova, na kalou sega ni mudu.
target_text: and abraham planted a grove in beersheba, and called there on the name of the lord, the everlasting god.

source_text: sa lako voli o eparaama e lomai filisitia me vica vata na siga.
target_text: and abraham sojourned in the philistines' land many days.

source_text: sa oti kece na veika oqo, na kalou sa vakatovolei eparaama, ka tukuna vua, "i eparaama, " sa sauma mai, "sai au oqo. "
target_text: and it came to pass after these things, that god did tempt abraham, and said unto him, abraham: and he said, behold, here i am.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna tale vua, "mo kauta na luvemu, na luvemu tagane e dua ga o aisake, o koya, o sa daulomana, lako ki na vanua o moraia “la'ki vakacabori koya me i soro kama ena dua na ulunivanua au na tukuna vei iko. "
target_text: and he said, take now thy son, thine only son isaac, whom thou lovest, and get thee into the land of moriah; and offer him there for a burnt offering upon one of the mountains which i will tell thee of.

source_text: sa sou ena mataka o eparaama, sa vakarautaka na nona asa, ka kauta e rua na nona cauravou vata kei koya, kei aisake na luvena; sa taya na buka ni soro kama “sa tucake ka lako ki na vanua sa tukuna vua, na kalou.
target_text: and abraham rose up early in the morning, and saddled his ass, and took two of his young men with him, and isaac his son, and clave the wood for the burnt offering, and rose up, and went unto the place of which god had told him.

source_text: ena i katolu ni siga, sa rai cake o eparaama, sa raica sara na vanua vakayawa.
target_text: then on the third day abraham lifted up his eyes, and saw the place afar off.

source_text: sa tukuna o eparaama vei rau na nona cauravou, "drau tiko eke kei na asa, na gone kei au, keirau na lako yani ka lotu vei jiova ka qai lesu tale mai vei kemudrau. "
target_text: and abraham said unto his young men, abide ye here with the ass; and i and the lad will go yonder and worship, and come again to you.

source_text: o, eparaama sa kauta yani na buka ni soro kama ka vakataqara vei aisake, sa taura mai na buka e waqa kei nai sele, e rau sa lako vata yani.
target_text: and abraham took the wood of the burnt offering, and laid it upon isaac his son; and he took the fire in his hand, and a knife; and they went both of them together.

source_text: sa taro o aisake, vei eparaama na tamana ka vaka: "tamaqu, " sa sauma yani, "sai au oqo na luvequ, " sa tukuna sara mai, "raica na buka e waqa kei na kau me buka sa tu oqo, e vei ga na lami me i soro kama? "
target_text: and isaac spake unto abraham his father, and said, my father: and he said, here am i, my son. and he said, behold the fire and the wood: but where is the lamb for a burnt offering?

source_text: sa sauma yani o eparaama, "na luvequ na kalou ena vakarautaka vei koya ga e dua na lami me i soro kama. " e rau sa lako ruarua vata yani.
target_text: and abraham said, my son, god will provide himself a lamb for a burnt offering: so they went both of them together.

source_text: e rau sa lako mai ki na vanua sa lesia na kalou. sa tara nai cabocabo ni soro o eparaama ka tuva na buka. sa vivigi aisake na luvena ka vakacabora ena i cabocabo ni soro ena dela ni buka sa tuvai tu.
target_text: and they came to the place which god had told him of; and abraham built an altar there, and laid the wood in order, and bound isaac his son, and laid him on the altar upon the wood.

source_text: o eparaama sa dodoka na ligana ka taura nai sele, me vakamatea nai soro (luvena).
target_text: and abraham stretched forth his hand, and took the knife to slay his son.

source_text: na agilosi i jiova sa kaci mai lomalagi ka vaka: "eparaama i eparaama! " sa sauma yani, "sai au oqo. "
target_text: and the angel of the lord called unto him out of heaven, and said, abraham, abraham: and he said, here am i.

source_text: sa tukuna mai na agilosi, "kua ni vakamatea na gone, se cakava vua e dua na ka, ni oqo, au sa kila ni o sa rerevaka na kalou “ni o sa sega ni via maroroya na luvemu, na luvemu tagane e dua ga, mai vei au. "
target_text: and he said, lay not thine hand upon the lad, neither do thou any thing unto him: for now i know that thou fearest god, seeing thou hast not withheld thy son, thine only son from me.

source_text: sa rai cake o eparaama, ka raica e dua na lami sa tacori tu na nona i leu ena dua na veico e dakuna. sa kauta mai o eparaama ka vakacabora mei sosomi kei aisake na luvena mei soro kama.
target_text: and abraham lifted up his eyes, and looked, and behold behind him a ram caught in a thicket by his horns: and abraham went and took the ram, and offered him up for a burnt offering in the stead of his son.

source_text: o eparaama sa vakayacana na vanua o ya me, sa vakarautaka o jiova, me yacova na siga oqo. "ena ulunivanua i jiova, sa vakarautaki kina. "
target_text: and abraham called the name of that place jehovahjireh: as it is said to this day, in the mount of the lord it shall be seen.

source_text: na agilosi i jiova sa kacivi eparaama vakarua mai lomalagi,
target_text: and the angel of the lord called unto abraham out of heaven the second time,

source_text: ka vaka: "vei au ga vakai au, au sa bubului kina, sa tukuna vaka oqo o jiova, ni o sa cakava na ka oqo, ka sa sega ni bureitaka na luvemu tagane e dua ga”
target_text: and said, by myself have i sworn, saith the lord, for because thou hast done this thing, and hast not withheld thy son, thine only son:

source_text: "ena veivakalouvinakataki, au na vakalouvinakataki iko, ena veivakatuburi, au na vakatuburi iko vakalevu sara, me vaka na veikalokalo ni lomalagi, me vaka talega na nuku ni veimatasawa. o ira na nomu kawa era na taukena na nodra matamata na nodra meca.
target_text: that in blessing i will bless thee, and in multiplying i will multiply thy seed as the stars of the heaven, and as the sand which is upon the sea shore; and thy seed shall possess the gate of his enemies;

source_text: "mai vei iko, na matanitu kece e vuravura era na vakalouvinakataki, baleta ni o sa rogoca na domoqu. "
target_text: and in thy seed shall all the nations of the earth be blessed; because thou hast obeyed my voice.

source_text: sa lesu tale o eparaama vei rau na nona cauravou, e rau sa tucake, ka ratou sa lesu vata ki periesepa; ka sa tiko mai periesepa o eparaama.
target_text: so abraham returned unto his young men, and they rose up and went together to beersheba; and abraham dwelt at beersheba.

source_text: sa oti na veika oqo, sa tukuni vei eparaama ka vaka, "o milika talega sa vakasucu gone vei neori na tacimu:
target_text: and it came to pass after these things, that it was told abraham, saying, behold, milcah, she hath also born children unto thy brother nahor;

source_text: "o usi na ulumatua, o buse na tacina, o kemueli na tamai erami,
target_text: huz his firstborn, and buz his brother, and kemuel the father of aram,

source_text: "o keseti, o aso, o pilidosi, o jidafa kei pecueli. "
target_text: and chesed, and hazo, and pildash, and jidlaph, and bethuel.

source_text: o pecueli sa vakasucumi vua o repeka. o ira na lewe walu oqo sa vakasucuma o milika vei neori na taci eparaama.
target_text: and bethuel begat rebekah: these eight milcah did bear to nahor, abraham's brother.

source_text: na watina lailai o reuma, sa vakasucumi teba, qaema, taesi kei maeka.
target_text: and his concubine, whose name was reumah, she bare also tebah, and gaham, and thahash, and maachah.

source_text: sa bula tiko o sera me dua na drau ruasagavulu ka vitu na yabaki; oqo na veiyabaki ni bula nei sera.
target_text: and sarah was an hundred and seven and twenty years old: these were the years of the life of sarah.

source_text: sa mate o sera mai kirijaci araba (oqori o epironi) ena vanua o kenani. sa lako mai o eparaama me lolokutaki sera ka tagicaki koya.
target_text: and sarah died in kirjatharba; the same is hebronin the land of canaan: and abraham came to mourn for sarah, and to weep for her.

source_text: sa tucake o eparaama mai na nona mate; ka vosa ki vei ira na luvei eci ka vaka,
target_text: and abraham stood up from before his dead, and spake unto the sons of heth, saying,

source_text: "o au e dua na vulagi, ka dau veitosoyaki tu ga ena kemuni maliwa. mo ni solia vei au e dua na tikina me noqu i bulubulu ena kemuni maliwa, me'u buluta tani kina na noqu mate mai mataqu. "
target_text: i am a stranger and a sojourner with you: give me a possession of a buryingplace with you, that i may bury my dead out of my sight.

source_text: era sa sauma vei eparaama na luvei eci tagane ka vaka,
target_text: and the children of heth answered abraham, saying unto him,

source_text: "mo rogoci keimami, na neimami turaga, o sa tamata qaqa ena keimami maliwa, buluta na nomu mate ena vanua ga o sa digitaka. ena sega ni dua vei keimami ena bureitaka na nona i bulubulu, mo buluta kina na nomu mate. "
target_text: hear us, my lord: thou art a mighty prince among us: in the choice of our sepulchres bury thy dead; none of us shall withhold from thee his sepulchre, but that thou mayest bury thy dead.

source_text: sa tucake o eparaama ka cuva ni vakarokoroko vei ira na tamata ni vanua, na luvei eci.
target_text: and abraham stood up, and bowed himself to the people of the land, even to the children of heth.

source_text: sa vosa talega vei ira ka vaka: "kevaka sa nomuni gagadre me'u buluta tani na noqu mate mai mataqu “mo ni rogoci au, mo ni sota mada kei efironi na luvei soa ena vukuqu,
target_text: and he communed with them, saying, if it be your mind that i should bury my dead out of my sight; hear me, and intreat for me to ephron the son of zohar,

source_text: "me solia mada vei au na veiqara vatu e makapila, o koya sa tiko vua, sa tiko ena mua ni were oqo. me solia vei au ena kena i sau taucoko. me taukeni kina nai bulubulu oqo ena kemuni maliwa. "
target_text: that he may give me the cave of machpelah, which he hath, which is in the end of his field; for as much money as it is worth he shall give it me for a possession of a buryingplace amongst you.

source_text: o efironi sa tiko ena kedra maliwa na luvei eci; sa sauma o efironi na itaiti vei eparaama ena matadra na luvei eci, o ira kece sa curu mai e nona matamata ka vaka,
target_text: and ephron dwelt among the children of heth: and ephron the hittite answered abraham in the audience of the children of heth, even of all that went in at the gate of his city, saying,

source_text: "e sega noqu turaga, au sa solia vei iko na veiwere kei na qara vatu sa tiko kina. au sa solia vei iko ena matadra kece na noqu tamata, au sa solia vei iko “buluta kina na nomu mate! "
target_text: nay, my lord, hear me: the field give i thee, and the cave that is therein, i give it thee; in the presence of the sons of my people give i it thee: bury thy dead.

source_text: sa cuva sobu o eparaama ena matadra na tamata ni vanua;
target_text: and abraham bowed down himself before the people of the land.

source_text: sa qai vosa vei efironi ena matadra kece na tamata ka vaka: "kevaka o sa solia vei au, mo rogoca talega oqo, au na solia vei iko nai lavo ena vuku ni vanua, taura oqo mai vei au “au na qai buluta na noqu mate e kea. "
target_text: and he spake unto ephron in the audience of the people of the land, saying, but if thou wilt give it, i pray thee, hear me: i will give thee money for the field; take it of me, and i will bury my dead there.

source_text: sa sauma o efironi vei eparama ka vaka,
target_text: and ephron answered abraham, saying unto him,

source_text: "mo rogoci au na noqu turaga, na vanua sa kenai sau e rua na drau onosagavulu na dola, na cava oqori ena kedaru maliwa? buluta ga yani na nomu mate. "
target_text: my lord, hearken unto me: the land is worth four hundred shekels of silver; what is that betwixt me and thee? bury therefore thy dead.

source_text: sa rogoca o eparaama na vosa nei efironi, ka sa vakarautaka na i lavo me vaka sa tukuni ena nodra vakarorogo na luvei eci, e rua na drau onosagavulu na dola, ena i lavo ni veivoli.
target_text: and abraham hearkened unto ephron; and abraham weighed to ephron the silver, which he had named in the audience of the sons of heth, four hundred shekels of silver, current money with the merchant.

source_text: na vanua nei efironi ena vanua e makapila sa tiko ena matai mamire, na vanua kei na qara vatu sa tiko kina, kei na vunikau kece sa tiko kina kei na veika kece sa tiko vakavolivolita, sa tiko ena veivolivoli oqo
target_text: and the field of ephron, which was in machpelah, which was before mamre, the field, and the cave which was therein, and all the trees that were in the field, that were in all the borders round about, were made sure

source_text: vei eparaama me sa kena i taukei ena matadra kece na luvei eci, o ira kece sa lako mai ena matamata ni koro.
target_text: unto abraham for a possession in the presence of the children of heth, before all that went in at the gate of his city.

source_text: ni sa oti oqo, sa buluti sera o eparaama ena qaravatu ni vanua e makapila e mamire (oqori o epironi) ena vanua e kenani.
target_text: and after this, abraham buried sarah his wife in the cave of the field of machpelah before mamre: the same is hebronin the land of canaan.

source_text: na vanua kei na qaravatu sa tiko kina, sa volitaki vei eparaama mai vei ira na luvei eci, me nona i bulubulu.
target_text: and the field, and the cave that is therein, were made sure unto abraham for a possession of a buryingplace by the sons of heth.

source_text: sa qase mai o eparaama ka sa levu sara na nona veiyabaki. o jiova talega sa vakalouvinakataki eparaama ena ka kecega.
target_text: and abraham was old, and well stricken in age: and the lord had blessed abraham in all things.

source_text: sa tukuna o eparaama vua na nona dauveiqaravi qase duadua “o koya sa lewa na nona veika kecega, "daramaka mada mai na ligamu ena ruku ni sagaqu,
target_text: and abraham said unto his eldest servant of his house, that ruled over all that he had, put, i pray thee, thy hand under my thigh:

source_text: "me'u cakava vei iko, mo bubului vei jiova, na kalou ni lomalagi kei na kalou ni vuravura, o ya, mo kua ni taura mai e dua na yalewa ni vanua oqo o kenani, me watina na luvequ;
target_text: and i will make thee swear by the lord, the god of heaven, and the god of the earth, that thou shalt not take a wife unto my son of the daughters of the canaanites, among whom i dwell:

source_text: "mo lako ga ki noqu vanua, vei ira na wekaqu ka kauta mai e dua me watina na luvequ o aisake. "
target_text: but thou shalt go unto my country, and to my kindred, and take a wife unto my son isaac.

source_text: sa tukuna vua na nona dauveiqaravi, "de qai sega ni vinakata, na yalewa me lako mai ki na vanua oqo. me'u kauta lesu beka na luvemu ki na vanua o lako mai kina? "
target_text: and the servant said unto him, peradventure the woman will not be willing to follow me unto this land: must i needs bring thy son again unto the land from whence thou camest?

source_text: sa tukuna vua o eparaama, "mo qarauna mo kua ni kauta na luvequ ki kea.
target_text: and abraham said unto him, beware thou that thou bring not my son thither again.

source_text: "na kalou o jiova, o koya sa kauti au tani mai na vale i tamaqu kei na nodra vanua na wekaqu, o koya sa vosa vei au ka yalataka vei au ka vaka: 'ki vei ira na nomu kawa au na solia kina na vanua oqo. ' ena tala liu na nona agilosi vei iko, o na kauta mai e dua na watina na luvequ mai kea.
target_text: the lord god of heaven, which took me from my father's house, and from the land of my kindred, and which spake unto me, and that sware unto me, saying, unto thy seed will i give this land; he shall send his angel before thee, and thou shalt take a wife unto my son from thence.

source_text: "kevaka sa sega ni via lako mai na yalewa vata kei kemuni, o sa na vakagalalataki mai na bubului oqo; mo kua ga ni kauta na luvequ tagane ki kea. "
target_text: and if the woman will not be willing to follow thee, then thou shalt be clear from this my oath: only bring not my son thither again.

source_text: na dauveiqaravi sa daramaka na ligana ena ruku ni sagai eparaama na nona turaga, ka bubului ena vuku ni veika sa vakamacalataki.
target_text: and the servant put his hand under the thigh of abraham his master, and sware to him concerning that matter.

source_text: na dauveiqaravi sa kauta e tini na kameli ni nona turaga ka lako yani “ni sa tiko e ligana na veika kece ena vuku ni nona turaga. sa lako yani ki mesapotomia na koro nei neori.
target_text: and the servant took ten camels of the camels of his master, and departed; for all the goods of his master were in his hand: and he arose, and went to mesopotamia, unto the city of nahor.

source_text: era sa tekiduru sobu na nona kameli ena taudaku ni koro ena bat ni wai, ni sa yakavi mai “oqo na gauna era sa dau mai taki wai kina na yalewa.
target_text: and he made his camels to kneel down without the city by a well of water at the time of the evening, even the time that women go out to draw water.

source_text: sa tukuna na dauveiqaravi, "i jiova na kalou nei eparaama na noqu turaga, mo ni solia vei au na qaqa e na siga oqo, ka mo ni vakaraitaka na vinaka vua na noqu turaga o eparaama.
target_text: and he said, o lord god of my master abraham, i pray thee, send me good speed this day, and shew kindness unto my master abraham.

source_text: "mo ni raica, au sa tu oqo ena mata ni wai “era sa lako tiko mai oqo na yalewa mai na koro me taki wai.
target_text: behold, i stand here by the well of water; and the daughters of the men of the city come out to draw water:

source_text: "me yaco, vei koya na gone yalewa au sa tukuna vua, 'mo biuta sobu mada na nomu saqa me'u gunu mada, ' ka me tukuna mai oqo, 'gunu, au na vakagunuva talega na nomu kameli, 'me sai koya oqo o ni sa digitaka vua na nomuni tamata o aisake. ena ka oqo au na kila kina ni o ni sa vakaraitaka na loloma vua na noqu turaga. "
target_text: and let it come to pass, that the damsel to whom i shall say, let down thy pitcher, i pray thee, that i may drink; and she shall say, drink, and i will give thy camels drink also: let the same be she that thou hast appointed for thy servant isaac; and thereby shall i know that thou hast shewed kindness unto my master.

source_text: sa yaco ni se bera ni oti na nona vosa, o rapeka na luvei petueli na luvei milika, na wati neori na taci eparaama, sa lako vata tiko mai kei na nona saqa ena vatuvatu ni tabana.
target_text: and it came to pass, before he had done speaking, that, behold, rebekah came out, who was born to bethuel, son of milcah, the wife of nahor, abraham's brother, with her pitcher upon her shoulder.

source_text: na goneyalewa oqo (rapeka), sa ka ga me vakasaravi, baleta ni sa rui goneyalewa totoka ka sega ni kila na tagane. sa lako sobu ki na wai ka vakatawana na nona saqa, ka lako cake mai.
target_text: and the damsel was very fair to look upon, a virgin, neither had any man known her: and she went down to the well, and filled her pitcher, and came up.

source_text: sa cici yani na dauveiqaravi me sotavi koya ka tukuna, "au kerea me'u gunu mada ga mai na nomu saqa wai. "
target_text: and the servant ran to meet her, and said, let me, i pray thee, drink a little water of thy pitcher.

source_text: sa tukuna mai na goneyalewa, "mo gunu na noqu turaga" “sa biuta mai vakatotolo na nona saqa ka solia yani vua me gunu.
target_text: and she said, drink, my lord: and she hasted, and let down her pitcher upon her hand, and gave him drink.

source_text: ni sa solia oti me gunu, sa tukuna tale, "au na la'ki taki wai talega me medra na kameli, me yacova ni ra sa gunu kece. "
target_text: and when she had done giving him drink, she said, i will draw water for thy camels also, until they have done drinking.

source_text: sa vakatotolo yani me taki wai tikotiko ga me yacova ni ra sa gunu kece na kameli.
target_text: and she hasted, and emptied her pitcher into the trough, and ran again unto the well to draw water, and drew for all his camels.

source_text: sa vakaraici koya tikoga na dauveiqaravi, sa galu tiko ni via kila se sa lewa i jiova oqo, se sega.
target_text: and the man wondering at her held his peace, to wit whether the lord had made his journey prosperous or not.

source_text: ena gauna era sa gunu oti kina na kameli, na dauveiqaravi, sa taura mai e dua na mama ni ucu koula, ka dua nai kava na onisi na kena bibi kei na rua na qato ni liga koula, e lima na onisi na kena bibi, ka daramaka vua na yalewa,
target_text: and it came to pass, as the camels had done drinking, that the man took a golden earring of half a shekel weight, and two bracelets for her hands of ten shekels weight of gold;

source_text: ka taroga na goneyalewa, "o luvei cei o iko? tukuna vei au, e tiko beka e so nai cili ena nomudou vale me keitou vakacegu kina? "
target_text: and said, whose daughter art thou? tell me, i pray thee: is there room in thy father's house for us to lodge in?

source_text: sa sauma mai na goneyalewa, "oi au na luvei petueli, na luvei milika, na wati neori. "
target_text: and she said unto him, i am the daughter of bethuel the son of milcah, which she bare unto nahor.

source_text: sa tukuna tale vua, "sa tu vei keitou na ka e veiraurau vei kemudou kei ira na manumanu, kei na i cili mo dou vakacegu kina. "
target_text: she said moreover unto him, we have both straw and provender enough, and room to lodge in.

source_text: sa cuva sobu na dauveiqaravi i eparaama ka lotu vei jiova.
target_text: and the man bowed down his head, and worshipped the lord.

source_text: sa tukuna, "me vakalouvinakataki na kalou o jiova nei eparaama, o koya sa sega ni vakawaletaka na nona loloma kei na nona dina vua na noqu turaga. ni sa tuberi au mai o jiova ki na vale nei koya na taci noqu turaga. "
target_text: and he said, blessed be the lord god of my master abraham, who hath not left destitute my master of his mercy and his truth: i being in the way, the lord led me to the house of my master's brethren.

source_text: sa cici yani na goneyalewa ka tukuna vei ira na vale nei tinana na veika oqo.
target_text: and the damsel ran, and told them of her mother's house these things.

source_text: o rapeka sa dua na ganena, na yacana o lepani, sa cici yani o lepani ki vua na tamata mai na mata ni wai.
target_text: and rebekah had a brother, and his name was laban: and laban ran out unto the man, unto the well.

source_text: sa yaco ni sa raica na mama ni ucu kei na qato e ligana na ganena, ka sa rogoci rapeka talega ni sa tukuna, "sa vosa vei au na tamata o ya, " sa qai lako yani vua na dauveiqaravi i eparaama ni sa tucake tu mai na mataniwai vata kei ira na kameli.
target_text: and it came to pass, when he saw the earring and bracelets upon his sister's hands, and when he heard the words of rebekah his sister, saying, thus spake the man unto me; that he came unto the man; and, behold, he stood by the camels at the well.

source_text: sa tukuna yani, "dou lako mai na veivakalouvinakataki i jiova! na cava dou sa tu ga kina e tuba? au sa vakarautaka oti na vale kei na vanua me ra cegu kina na kameli. "
target_text: and he said, come in, thou blessed of the lord; wherefore standest thou without? for i have prepared the house, and room for the camels.

source_text: sa curu yani na tamata (dauveiqaravi) ki vale, sa sereka nai colacola ni kameli ka solia na kedra kakana. sa savata na yavana kei na yavadra na nona i tokani era sa lako vata mai.
target_text: and the man came into the house: and he ungirded his camels, and gave straw and provender for the camels, and water to wash his feet, and the men's feet that were with him.

source_text: sa biu mai matana na kakana me kana, ia, sa vosa mada e liu ka vaka: "au na sega mada ni kana, me'u tukuna mada e liu na ka au mai cakava. " sa sauma mai o lepani, "mo vosa sara. "
target_text: and there was set meat before him to eat: but he said, i will not eat, until i have told mine errand. and he said, speak on.

source_text: sa tukuna mai, "oi au na tamata dauveiqaravi nei eparaama.
target_text: and he said, i am abraham's servant.

source_text: "o jiova sa vakalouvinakataki koya vakalevu sara, ka sa tamata qaqa sara; na kalou sa solia vua na manumanu, na siliva, na koula, na tagane kei na yalewa dauveiqaravi, na kameli kei na asa e levu sara.
target_text: and the lord hath blessed my master greatly; and he is become great: and he hath given him flocks, and herds, and silver, and gold, and menservants, and maidservants, and camels, and asses.

source_text: "o sera na watina na noqu turaga, sa vakasucuma e dua na gone tagane vua na noqu turaga ni sa qase sara; sa solia vua na luvena tagane oqo na veika kecega; o koya na noqu turaga.
target_text: and sarah my master's wife bare a son to my master when she was old: and unto him hath he given all that he hath.

source_text: "sa cakava na noqu turaga me'u bubului, ka vaka: 'mo kua ni kauta vua na luvequ tagane me watina e dua na yalewa ni vanua oqo, o kenani;
target_text: and my master made me swear, saying, thou shalt not take a wife to my son of the daughters of the canaanites, in whose land i dwell:

source_text: 'mo lako ga ki na vale nei tamaqu, vei ira na wekaqu, ka kauta mai e dua na yalewa me watina. '
target_text: but thou shalt go unto my father's house, and to my kindred, and take a wife unto my son.

source_text: "au sa taroga na noqu turaga, 'de qai sega ni via muri au mai na yalewa. '
target_text: and i said unto my master, peradventure the woman will not follow me.

source_text: "sa sauma mai vei au o jiova, 'o koya au sa lako voli e matana ena tala mai na nona agilosi vei iko, ena vakataucokotaka na nomu i lakolako, ka o na kauta mai e dua na watina na luvequ mai vei ira na wekaqu “mai na vale i tamaqu.
target_text: and he said unto me, the lord, before whom i walk, will send his angel with thee, and prosper thy way; and thou shalt take a wife for my son of my kindred, and of my father's house:

source_text: 'o na vakagalalataki mai na bubului oqo, kevaka o sa yaco yani vei ira na wekaqu, qai o sega ni kauta mai e dua na yalewa. o sa na galala mai na bubului oqo. '
target_text: then shalt thou be clear from this my oath, when thou comest to my kindred; and if they give not thee one, thou shalt be clear from my oath.

source_text: "ena siga oqo, ni'u sa lako mai ki na mata ni wai ka masu, 'i jiova na kalou ni noqu turaga o eparaama, kevaka e dina ni o ni na vakataucokotaka nai lakolako oqo,
target_text: and i came this day unto the well, and said, o lord god of my master abraham, if now thou do prosper my way which i go:

source_text: 'raica, au na tu ena mata ni wai, na goneyalewa ga ena lako mai me takiwai, ka au na tukuna vua “"mo solia mai na wai me'u gunu. "
target_text: behold, i stand by the well of water; and it shall come to pass, that when the virgin cometh forth to draw water, and i say to her, give me, i pray thee, a little water of thy pitcher to drink;

source_text: 'ka me na sauma sara mai, "oqo mo gunu, au na vakagunuvi ira talega na nomu kameli, " me sai koya oqo na yalewa sa digitaka o jiova me watina na luve ni noqu turaga. '
target_text: and she say to me, both drink thou, and i will also draw for thy camels: let the same be the woman whom the lord hath appointed out for my master's son.

source_text: "ni se bera ni'u masu oti, sa lako mai o rapeka vata kei na nona saqa wai e domona “sa lako sobu sara ki na mata ni wai ka taki. 'au sa kerekere sara me'u gunu. '
target_text: and before i had done speaking in mine heart, behold, rebekah came forth with her pitcher on her shoulder; and she went down unto the well, and drew water: and i said unto her, let me drink, i pray thee.

source_text: "sa vakatotolo sara o koya me biuta e ra na nona saqa wai ka solia mai. me'u 'gunu “sa tukuna talega me vakagunuvi ira na kameli. '
target_text: and she made haste, and let down her pitcher from her shoulder, and said, drink, and i will give thy camels drink also: so i drank, and she made the camels drink also.

source_text: "au sa mani tarogi koya, 'o iko na luvei cei? ' sa sauma mai, 'oi au na luvei petueli na luvei neori, sa vakasucuma vua o milika. ' au sa vakadaramaka sara vua na mama ni ucu kei na qato ni liga, e ligana.
target_text: and i asked her, and said, whose daughter art thou? and she said, the daughter of bethuel, nahor's son, whom milcah bare unto him: and i put the earring upon her face, and the bracelets upon her hands.

source_text: "au sa cuva sobu ki na qele ka lotu vei jiova, ka vakalouvinakataka na kalou o jiova, na kalou ni noqu turaga o eparaama, o koya sa tuberi au mai ena sala dina me'u mai kauta na goneyalewa na luvena na tacina na noqu turaga me rau la'ki veiwatini kei na luvena tagane.
target_text: and i bowed down my head, and worshipped the lord, and blessed the lord god of my master abraham, which had led me in the right way to take my master's brother's daughter unto his son.

source_text: "oqo, kevaka dou sa cakacaka vakadodonu vua na noqu turaga, mo dou tukuna vei au, se, me'u gole ki nai matau se ki nai mawi. "
target_text: and now if ye will deal kindly and truly with my master, tell me: and if not, tell me; that i may turn to the right hand, or to the left.

source_text: o lepani kei petueli, e rau sa sauma mai ka vaka: "na veika sa lako mai vei jiova keirau sa sega ni rawa ni tukuna ni vinaka se ca.
target_text: then laban and bethuel answered and said, the thing proceedeth from the lord: we cannot speak unto thee bad or good.

source_text: "sa tu ga oqo o rapeka, tauri koya ka drau lako yani me la'ki watina na luvena tagane na nomu turaga, me vaka sa tukuna o jiova. "
target_text: behold, rebekah is before thee, take her, and go, and let her be thy master's son's wife, as the lord hath spoken.

source_text: ni sa rogoca oqo na dauveiqaravi i eparaama, sa lotu vei jiova ka vakacuva na uluna ki na qele.
target_text: and it came to pass, that, when abraham's servant heard their words, he worshipped the lord, bowing himself to the earth.

source_text: na dauveiqaravi sa kauta mai na i yau talei siliva, nai yau talei koula, na i sulu, ka solia vei rapeka. sa solia talega na yau talei sara vei ganena kei tinana.
target_text: and the servant brought forth jewels of silver, and jewels of gold, and raiment, and gave them to rebekah: he gave also to her brother and to her mother precious things.

source_text: na dauveiqaravi kei ira na tamata era sa kana ka gunu ka vakacegu ena bogi. era sa yadra ena mataka ka tukuna, "laivi au mada me'u lako vua na noqu turaga. "
target_text: and they did eat and drink, he and the men that were with him, and tarried all night; and they rose up in the morning, and he said, send me away unto my master.

source_text: ia, o ganei rapeka kei tinana e rau sa tukuna, "me tiko mada vata kei keitou na goneyalewa me tini tale na siga, ka me qai lako yani. "
target_text: and her brother and her mother said, let the damsel abide with us a few days, at the least ten; after that she shall go.

source_text: sa sauma yani na dauveiqaravi, "dou kua ni vakataotaki au, o jiova sa dolava oti na noqui lakolako; dou laivi au me'u lako “me'u lako yani vua na noqu turaga. "
target_text: and he said unto them, hinder me not, seeing the lord hath prospered my way; send me away that i may go to my master.

source_text: e ratou sa tukuna tale, "me keitou taroga mada na goneyalewa. "
target_text: and they said, we will call the damsel, and enquire at her mouth.

source_text: e ratou sa kacivi rapeka mai ka taroga, "o na lako beka vata kei na dauveiqaravi oqo? " sa sauma mai o rapeka, "au na lako. "
target_text: and they called rebekah, and said unto her, wilt thou go with this man? and she said, i will go.

source_text: era sa vakatalai rapeka yani kei na nona nasi kei na dauveiqaravi nei eparaama kei ira na tamata.
target_text: and they sent away rebekah their sister, and her nurse, and abraham's servant, and his men.

source_text: era sa vosa vakalouvinakataki rapeka ka tukuna vua: "mo yaco mo tinadra na vei udolu kei na vei tini na udolu; kei na nomu kawa mera taukena na nodra veimatamata o ira sa cati kemuni. "
target_text: and they blessed rebekah, and said unto her, thou art our sister, be thou the mother of thousands of millions, and let thy seed possess the gate of those which hate them.

source_text: o rapeka kei ira na nona dauveiqaravi, era sa vodoka na kameli ka muri ira yani na tamata. era sa kauti rapeka yani, ka lako sara.
target_text: and rebekah arose, and her damsels, and they rode upon the camels, and followed the man: and the servant took rebekah, and went his way.

source_text: o aisake sa lako mai vaka ki bea-laei-roi, ni sa tiko mai na ceva.
target_text: and isaac came from the way of the well lahairoi; for he dwelt in the south country.

source_text: sa lako yani o aisake ki na veibuca me vakanananu mada ni sa yakavi mai. sa rai sara yani, ka raica na veikameli era sa lako tiko mai.
target_text: and isaac went out to meditate in the field at the eventide: and he lifted up his eyes, and saw, and, behold, the camels were coming.

source_text: sa rai yani o rapeka, ka sa raici aisake sara. sa sobu mai ena nona kameli;
target_text: and rebekah lifted up her eyes, and when she saw isaac, she lighted off the camel.

source_text: ni sa taroga oti na dauveiqaravi “se ocei na tagane sa lako tiko mai oqo me sotavi ira? sa tukuna yani vua, "ni oqo na luve ni noqu turaga. " sa taura o rapeka na nona i ubi ka ubi koya ga vakavinaka.
target_text: for she had said unto the servant, what man is this that walketh in the field to meet us? and the servant had said, it is my master: therefore she took a vail, and covered herself.

source_text: na dauveiqaravi sa tukuna vei aisake na veika kece sa cakava oti.
target_text: and the servant told isaac all things that he had done.

source_text: o aisake sa kauta mai na goneyalewa ki na valelaca nei sera na tinana; sa tauri rapeka, ka sa yaco me watina ka sa lomani rapeka dina sara. oqo sa vakacegui vinaka kina o aisake mai na mate nei tinana.
target_text: and isaac brought her into his mother sarah's tent, and took rebekah, and she became his wife; and he loved her: and isaac was comforted after his mother's death.

source_text: sa vakawati tale o eparaama, na yaca i watina o ketura.
target_text: then again abraham took a wife, and her name was keturah.

source_text: sa sucu kina o simirani, jokesani, medani, mitiani, isibaki kei sua.
target_text: and she bare him zimran, and jokshan, and medan, and midian, and ishbak, and shuah.

source_text: o jokesani sa vakasucumi vua o seba kei didani. na luvei didani o asurimi, letusimi, kei liumimi.
target_text: and jokshan begat sheba, and dedan. and the sons of dedan were asshurim, and letushim, and leummim.

source_text: na luvei mitiani o efa, eferi, anoti, ebida, kei eledae. o ira kece oqo na gone mai vei ketura.
target_text: and the sons of midian; ephah, and epher, and hanoch, and abidah, and eldaah. all these were the children of keturah.

source_text: o eparaama sa solia na veika kece sa nona vei aisake.
target_text: and abraham gave all that he had unto isaac.

source_text: o eparama sa solia talega na veika vei ira na luvena ni watina talai. ni se bula tikoga o eparaama, sa vakatalai ira tani yani oqo, mai vei aisake ki na tokalau.
target_text: but unto the sons of the concubines, which abraham had, abraham gave gifts, and sent them away from isaac his son, while he yet lived, eastward, unto the east country.

source_text: na veiyabaki sa bula kina o eparaama sa dua nadrau vitusagavulu ka lima na yabaki.
target_text: and these are the days of the years of abraham's life which he lived, an hundred threescore and fifteen years.

source_text: sa ceguva nai otioti ni nona i cegu o eparaama ka sa mate yani ni sa qase sara. sa lako yani vei ira na kai nona.
target_text: then abraham gave up the ghost, and died in a good old age, an old man, and full of years; and was gathered to his people.

source_text: e rau sa buluti koya na luvena o aisake kei isimeli ena qaravatu mai makapila, e mamire, ena veiwere nei efironi na luvei soa na itaiti;
target_text: and his sons isaac and ishmael buried him in the cave of machpelah, in the field of ephron the son of zohar the hittite, which is before mamre;

source_text: na vanua sa volia o eparaama mai vei ira na luvei eci. e rau sa bulu mai kea o eparaama kei sera na watina.
target_text: the field which abraham purchased of the sons of heth: there was abraham buried, and sarah his wife.

source_text: sa yaco ni sa mate oti o eparaama, na kalou sa vosa vakalouvinakataki aisake na luvena. o aisake sa tiko mai bea-laei-roi.
target_text: and it came to pass after the death of abraham, that god blessed his son isaac; and isaac dwelt by the well lahairoi.

source_text: oqo na kawa nei isimeli na luvei eparama vei eka na yalewa dauveiqaravi ni ijipita nei sera.
target_text: now these are the generations of ishmael, abraham's son, whom hagar the egyptian, sarah's handmaid, bare unto abraham:

source_text: oqo na yacadra na luvei isimeli “na dui yacadra kei na nodra dui kawa: na ulumatua nei isimeli o nebajoci; sa qai kedari, adibili, mibisami,
target_text: and these are the names of the sons of ishmael, by their names, according to their generations: the firstborn of ishmael, nebajoth; and kedar, and adbeel, and mibsam,
and mishma, and dumah, and massa,

source_text: adari, tema, jeturi, nafisi kei kedema.
target_text: hadar, and tema, jetur, naphish, and kedemah:

source_text: sai ira oqori na luvei isimeli, oqo talega na yaca ni nodra vei koro kei nai tikotiko vagalala, e tinikarua na ravouvou me vaka na nodra dui vanua.
target_text: these are the sons of ishmael, and these are their names, by their towns, and by their castles; twelve princes according to their nations.

source_text: oqo na veiyabaki nei isimeli, e dua na drau tolusagavulu ka vitu na yabaki; sa ceguva nai otioti ni nona i cegu ka mate yani, sa soqoni yani vei ira na nona tamata.
target_text: and these are the years of the life of ishmael, an hundred and thirty and seven years: and he gave up the ghost and died; and was gathered unto his people.

source_text: (era sa tiko mai avila me yaco sara ki suri, oqori ena tokalau kei ijipita ni o lako yani vaka ki asiria. ) sa mate ena matadra na tacina.
target_text: and they dwelt from havilah unto shur, that is before egypt, as thou goest toward assyria: and he died in the presence of all his brethren.

source_text: oqo na kawa nei aisake, na luvei eparaama. o eparaama sa vakasucumi vua o aisake.
target_text: and these are the generations of isaac, abraham's son: abraham begat isaac:

source_text: o aisake sa yabaki vasagavulu ni rau sa veiwatini kei rapeka na luvei petueli na kai siria mai padani-arami, na ganei lepani na kai siria.
target_text: and isaac was forty years old when he took rebekah to wife, the daughter of bethuel the syrian of padanaram, the sister to laban the syrian.

source_text: o aisake sa vakamamasu vei jiova ena vuku i rapeka na watina, ni sa yava (sega ni vakaluveni), o jiova sa sauma na masu nei aisake, ka sa kunekune sara o rapeka.
target_text: and isaac intreated the lord for his wife, because she was barren: and the lord was intreated of him, and rebekah his wife conceived.

source_text: e rau sa yavavala vakalevu na gone e ketei tinadrau, ka sa tukuna kina “"kevaka sa vinaka oqo, na cava sa yaco tiko kina na yavavala e ketequ? " sa lako yani me vakatarogi jiova.
target_text: and the children struggled together within her; and she said, if it be so, why am i thus? and she went to enquire of the lord.

source_text: sa tukuna vua o jiova, "e rua na matanitu sa tiko oqori e ketemu, e rua na tamata e rau na tawase mai yagomu; e dua ena kaukauwa mai vua tale e dua “o koya na qase ena qaravi koya e gone. "
target_text: and the lord said unto her, two nations are in thy womb, and two manner of people shall be separated from thy bowels; and the one people shall be stronger than the other people; and the elder shall serve the younger.

source_text: ni sa yaco mai na nona siga ni vakasucu, sa tiko ena kato e dua na drua.
target_text: and when her days to be delivered were fulfilled, behold, there were twins in her womb.

source_text: o koya e liu mai e damusa, sa vaka e dua nai sulu vutivutia na yagona kece: sa vakayacani me o iso.
target_text: and the first came out red, all over like an hairy garment; and they called his name esau.

source_text: sa qai muri mai o tacina, na ligana sa vesuka tiko mai na bukubuku ni yavai iso. sa vakayacani me o jekope. sa yabaki onosagavulu o aisake ni rau sa sucu mai na luvena drua oqo.
target_text: and after that came his brother out, and his hand took hold on esau's heel; and his name was called jacob: and isaac was threescore years old when she bare them.

source_text: e rau sa tubu cake na gone. sa dau vakasasa manumanu o iso ka tamata ni veiwere. o jekope sa tamata malumu tuga ka dau tiko ga e vale.
target_text: and the boys grew: and esau was a cunning hunter, a man of the field; and jacob was a plain man, dwelling in tents.

source_text: o aisake sa dau lomani iso, baleta ni sa dau kania na nona manumanu ni vakasasa. ia, o rapeka sa lomani jekope vakalevu. sa volitaka o iso na nona i tutu vakaulumatua
target_text: and isaac loved esau, because he did eat of his venison: but rebekah loved jacob.

source_text: o jekope sa vakasaqa kakana vakarakara tiko ena nona lesu mai na veiwere o iso, ka sa wawale sara vakalevu.
target_text: and jacob sod pottage: and esau came from the field, and he was faint:

source_text: sa kerea yani o iso vei jekope me kania mada na kakana vakarakara damudamu sa vakarautaka tiko, ni sa rui wawale vakalevu. sa vakayacani sara kina me o itomi.
target_text: and esau said to jacob, feed me, i pray thee, with that same red pottage; for i am faint: therefore was his name called edom.

source_text: sa tukuna yani o jekope, "mo volitaka na dodonu ni nomu ulumatua vei au ena siga oqo. "
target_text: and jacob said, sell me this day thy birthright.

source_text: sa tukuna mai o iso, "raica au sa voleka ni mate, na cava na kena yaga vei au na ulumatua oqo? "
target_text: and esau said, behold, i am at the point to die: and what profit shall this birthright do to me?

source_text: sa tukuna mai o jekope, "mo bubului vei au e dai. " sa bubului o iso ena siga o ya vei jekope ka volitaka na nona dodonu vakaulumatua vei jekope.
target_text: and jacob said, swear to me this day; and he sware unto him: and he sold his birthright unto jacob.

source_text: o jekope sa vakarautaka sara na kakana vakarakara damudamu kei na madrai vei iso. sa kana ka gunu o iso ka tucake ka sa lako yani. o iso sa vakawaletaka na dodonu ni nona ulumatua.
target_text: then jacob gave esau bread and pottage of lentiles; and he did eat and drink, and rose up, and went his way: thus esau despised his birthright.

source_text: sa yaco e dua na dausiga levu ena vanua, me vaka na dausiga ena gauna nei eparaama. o aisake sa lako vei apimeleki na tui filisitia e qarari.
target_text: and there was a famine in the land, beside the first famine that was in the days of abraham. and isaac went unto abimelech king of the philistines unto gerar.

source_text: sa basika vei koya o jiova ka tukuna: "kua ni lako sobu ki ijipita; mo tiko ga ena vanua au na tukuna vei iko.
target_text: and the lord appeared unto him, and said, go not down into egypt; dwell in the land which i shall tell thee of:

source_text: "tiko ga ena vanua oqo, au na tiko vata kei iko ka vakalouvinakataki iko; vei iko kei ira na nomu kawa, au na solia kina na vanua oqo, au na vakayacora kina na yalayala. au a bubului kina vei eparaama na tamamu.
target_text: sojourn in this land, and i will be with thee, and will bless thee; for unto thee, and unto thy seed, i will give all these countries, and i will perform the oath which i sware unto abraham thy father;

source_text: "au na vakavuna na nomu kawa me ra vaka na kalokalo ni lomalagi; au na solia vei ira na nomu kawa na vanua taucoko oqo; mai vei iko, ena vakalouvinakataki kina na veivanua kece oqo;
target_text: and i will make thy seed to multiply as the stars of heaven, and will give unto thy seed all these countries; and in thy seed shall all the nations of the earth be blessed;

source_text: "baleta ni sa talairawarawa o eparaama ki na domoqu ka maroroya na noqu i lesilesi, na noqu i vakaro, na noqu lewa kei na noqu i vunau. "
target_text: because that abraham obeyed my voice, and kept my charge, my commandments, my statutes, and my laws.

source_text: o aisake sa tiko ga e qerari.
target_text: and isaac dwelt in gerar:

source_text: o ira na tagane ni vanua o ya era sa tarogi koya me baleta na watina. sa tukuna kina, "o koya na ganequ" “ni sa rere o koya me tukuna, "o koya na watiqu; " ni sa nanuma "ni ra na vakamatei koya ena vuku i rapeka na watina, baleta ni sa rui yalewa totoka dina ni vakasaravi. "
target_text: and the men of the place asked him of his wife; and he said, she is my sister: for he feared to say, she is my wife; lest, said he, the men of the place should kill me for rebekah; because she was fair to look upon.

source_text: sa yaco, ni sa dede tiko na nodra tiko e kea, o apimeleki na tui filisitia, ni sa rai tiko yani ena nona katuba leka “sa raica ni rau sa veiwedevi tiko o aisake kei rapeka na watina.
target_text: and it came to pass, when he had been there a long time, that abimelech king of the philistines looked out at a window, and saw, and, behold, isaac was sporting with rebekah his wife.

source_text: o apimeleki sa kacivi aisake yani ka tukuna, "e vaka vei au ni rapeka e watimu; o tukuna rawa vakacava vei au ni o koya e ganemu? " sa tukuna vua o aisake, "baleta ni'u sa kila, 'de ra na vakamatei au ena vukui rapeka. '"
target_text: and abimelech called isaac, and said, behold, of a surety she is thy wife: and how saidst thou, she is my sister? and isaac said unto him, because i said, lest i die for her.

source_text: sa tukuna mai o apimeleki, "na cava o sa cakava oqo vei keimami? vaka cava kevaka e dua sa moceri koya, o iko ga sa na kauta mai vei keimami na bula e beitaki. "
target_text: and abimelech said, what is this thou hast done unto us? one of the people might lightly have lien with thy wife, and thou shouldest have brought guiltiness upon us.

source_text: sa vakarota kina o apimeleki vei ira na nona tamata, "o koya sa tara na watina na tamata oqo, ena vakamatei vakaidina. "
target_text: and abimelech charged all his people, saying, he that toucheth this man or his wife shall surely be put to death.

source_text: sa kakaburaki ena vanua o ya o aisake, ka sa tatamusuki ena yabaki vata ga o ya “ka sa yayadrau; sa vakalouvinakataki koya o jiova.
target_text: then isaac sowed in that land, and received in the same year an hundredfold: and the lord blessed him.

source_text: sa tubu cake na nona sautu, sa gumatua tikotikoga me yacova ni sa sautu vakalevu sara;
target_text: and the man waxed great, and went forward, and grew until he became very great:

source_text: ni sa taukena na qele ni manumanu, na qele ni bulumakau, ka sa levu sara na nona dauveiqaravi. era sa vuvutaki koya na kai filisitia.
target_text: for he had possession of flocks, and possession of herds, and great store of servants: and the philistines envied him.

source_text: o ira na filisitia era sa sogota na vei mata ni wai kece era a kelia na tamata nei eparaama na tamana, era sa buluta kece ena qele.
target_text: for all the wells which his father's servants had digged in the days of abraham his father, the philistines had stopped them, and filled them with earth.

source_text: sa tukuna o apimeleki vei aisake, "mo lako tani mai vei keimami, ni o sa rui kaukauwa mai vei keimami. "
target_text: and abimelech said unto isaac, go from us; for thou art much mightier than we.

source_text: sa lako tani mai kea o aisake ka la'ki tiko ena veibuca mai qerari.
target_text: and isaac departed thence, and pitched his tent in the valley of gerar, and dwelt there.

source_text: sa kelia tale o aisake na veimata ni wai, ea kelia e liu o eparaama na tamana, ni ra sa sogota na filisitia e na nona sa mate o eparaama. o aisake sa vakayacana tale ena yaca ga ea vakayacana kina e liu o tamana.
target_text: and isaac digged again the wells of water, which they had digged in the days of abraham his father; for the philistines had stopped them after the death of abraham: and he called their names after the names by which his father had called them.

source_text: o ira talega na tamata i aisake, era sa kelia e dua na mata ni wai sa drodro tu ga, mai na buca.
target_text: and isaac's servants digged in the valley, and found there a well of springing water.

source_text: o ira na dau susu manumanu mai qerari era sa veivala kei ira na dau susu manumanu nei aisake ka tukuna, "na wai sa neimami" sa vakayacani kina na wai o ya me eseki, baleta ni ra sa veivala kei koya.
target_text: and the herdmen of gerar did strive with isaac's herdmen, saying, the water is ours: and he called the name of the well esek; because they strove with him.

source_text: era sa kelia tale e dua na mata ni wai “era sa veivala tale kina. sa vakayacana o aisake na vanua o ya me sitina.
target_text: and they digged another well, and strove for that also: and he called the name of it sitnah.

source_text: sa lako tani mai kea ka kelia tale e dua na mata ni wai “era sa sega ni veivala kina, sa vakayacana me reopoci, ni sa tukuna "o jiova sa solia na galala vei keda, eda na vuavuai kina ena vanua. "
target_text: and he removed from thence, and digged another well; and for that they strove not: and he called the name of it rehoboth; and he said, for now the lord hath made room for us, and we shall be fruitful in the land.

source_text: sa lako cake mai kea ki periesepa.
target_text: and he went up from thence to beersheba.

source_text: o jiova sa basika vua ena bogi tiko ga o ya ka tukuna, "oi au na kalou nei tamamu o eparaama; kua ni rere, au sa tiko vata kei iko. au na vakalouvinakataki iko ka vakalewelevutaki iko kei ira na nomu kawa, ena vuku i eparaama. "
target_text: and the lord appeared unto him the same night, and said, i am the god of abraham thy father: fear not, for i am with thee, and will bless thee, and multiply thy seed for my servant abraham's sake.

source_text: sa tara mai kea e dua nai cabocabo ni soro ka kaciva mai kea na yaca i jiova. sa tara talega e kea na nona valelaca; era sa kelia mai kea e dua na mata ni wai na dauveiqaravi nei aisake.
target_text: and he builded an altar there, and called upon the name of the lord, and pitched his tent there: and there isaac's servants digged a well.

source_text: o apimeleki sa lako mai vua mai qerari vata kei ausaci, e dua na nona i tokani kei fikoli nai liuliu ni nona mataivalu.
target_text: then abimelech went to him from gerar, and ahuzzath one of his friends, and phichol the chief captain of his army.

source_text: sa tukuna vei iratou o aisake, "na cava dou sa mai cakava vei au “kemudou a cati au ka vakatalai au tani mai vei kemudou? "
target_text: and isaac said unto them, wherefore come ye to me, seeing ye hate me, and have sent me away from you?

source_text: e ratou sa sauma mai, "keitou sa raica vakaidina ni sa tiko vata kei iko o jiova. keitou sa tukuna kina, me dua na nodatou veiyalayalati “o iko kei keitou. 'me datou cakava e dua na veiyalayalati,
target_text: and they said, we saw certainly that the lord was with thee: and we said, let there be now an oath betwixt us, even betwixt us and thee, and let us make a covenant with thee;

source_text: 'mo kua ni cakava vei keitou e dua na ka ca “ni keitou sa sega ni tarai iko. ni keitou sa sega ni cakava e dua na ka ca, na ka vinaka ga “ni keitou sa vakatalai iko ena vakacegu. o sa kalouvinaka kina i jiova. '"
target_text: that thou wilt do us no hurt, as we have not touched thee, and as we have done unto thee nothing but good, and have sent thee away in peace: thou art now the blessed of the lord.

source_text: sa cakava o aisake e dua na kakana, e ratou sa kana ka gunu.
target_text: and he made them a feast, and they did eat and drink.

source_text: e ratou sa yadra ena mataka, ka veiyalayalati, sa vakatalai iratou yani; e ratou sa lako tani mai vua ena vakacegu.
target_text: and they rose up betimes in the morning, and sware one to another: and isaac sent them away, and they departed from him in peace.

source_text: ena siga tiko ga o ya, era sa lako mai na tamata nei aisake ka tukuna vua me baleta na mata ni wai era a kelia, era sa mai tukuna, "sa vure na wai. "
target_text: and it came to pass the same day, that isaac's servants came, and told him concerning the well which they had digged, and said unto him, we have found water.

source_text: sa vakatoka ena yaca o siepa. sa yaca ni koro kina o ya o perisiepa.
target_text: and he called it shebah: therefore the name of the city is beersheba unto this day.

source_text: ni sa yabaki vasagavulu o iso, sa tauri jutia na luvei bieri na itaiti, kei vasemaca na luvei eloni na itaiti, me rau watina.
target_text: and esau was forty years old when he took to wife judith the daughter of beeri the hittite, and bashemath the daughter of elon the hittite:

source_text: e rau sa rarawa kina vakalevu o aisake kei rapeka.
target_text: which were a grief of mind unto isaac and to rebekah.

source_text: sa yaco na gauna ni sa qase mai o aisake ka sa buwawa sara na matana “sa sega kina ni rai rawa, sa kacivi iso mai, na nona ulumatua ka tukuna vua, "na luvequ, " sa sauma mai o iso, "sai au oqo. "
target_text: and it came to pass, that when isaac was old, and his eyes were dim, so that he could not see, he called esau his eldest son, and said unto him, my son: and he said unto him, behold, here am i.

source_text: sa tukuna tale, "raica, au sa qase sara, au sa sega talega ni kila na noqu siga ni mate.
target_text: and he said, behold now, i am old, i know not the day of my death:

source_text: "oqo mo kauta mada na nomu i yaragi, na taga ni gasau kei na veqa ni dakai, lako yani ka vakasasataka mada mai e dua na kequ manumanu.
target_text: now therefore take, i pray thee, thy weapons, thy quiver and thy bow, and go out to the field, and take me some venison;

source_text: "mo tavuna vakaveiwaki mai, me vaka au sa dau vinakata, kauta mai, me'u mai kania, me vakalouvinakataki iko kina na yaloqu ni bera ni'u mate. "
target_text: and make me savoury meat, such as i love, and bring it to me, that i may eat; that my soul may bless thee before i die.

source_text: sa vakarorogo tu o rapeka ni sa vosa tiko o aisake vei iso na luvena. sa lako yani o iso ki vanua me vavana ka me kauta lesu mai.
target_text: and rebekah heard when isaac spake to esau his son. and esau went to the field to hunt for venison, and to bring it.

source_text: o rapeka sa vosa vei jekope na luvena ka vaka: "au sa rogoci tamamu ni sa vosa oti vei iso na tacimu ka vaka,
target_text: and rebekah spake unto jacob her son, saying, behold, i heard thy father speak unto esau thy brother, saying,

source_text: 'kauta mai e dua na manumanu, mo tavuna veiwaki ka kauta mai me'u kania ka vosa vakalouvinakataki iko ena mata i jiova ni bera ni'u mate. '
target_text: bring me venison, and make me savoury meat, that i may eat, and bless thee before the lord before my death.

source_text: "na luvequ mo rogoca na noqu vosa, me vaka au sa vakarota vei iko.
target_text: now therefore, my son, obey my voice according to that which i command thee.

source_text: "lako ka kauta mai e rua na luve ni me vinaka, au na tavuna veiwakitaka me kania o tamamu me vaka e dau vinakata.
target_text: go now to the flock, and fetch me from thence two good kids of the goats; and i will make them savoury meat for thy father, such as he loveth:

source_text: "mo qai kauta vei tamamu, me kania, ka vosa vakalouvinakataki iko ni bera ni mate yani. "
target_text: and thou shalt bring it to thy father, that he may eat, and that he may bless thee before his death.

source_text: sa tukuna o jekope vei tinana “"raica, o iso e vutivutia na yagona, o au, e sega.
target_text: and jacob said to rebekah his mother, behold, esau my brother is a hairy man, and i am a smooth man:

source_text: "de qai vakayamoca o tamaqu na ligaqu, ka kilai au “ena qai tukuna ni'u tamata dauveivakaisini, oqo au na kauta ga mai kina vei au na kalouca ka sega na kalouvinaka. "
target_text: my father peradventure will feel me, and i shall seem to him as a deceiver; and i shall bring a curse upon me, and not a blessing.

source_text: sa tukuna vua o tinana, "na nomu kalouca me noqu na luvequ, cakava ga na veika au sa tukuna oti vei iko, lako, kauta mai na manumanu. "
target_text: and his mother said unto him, upon me be thy curse, my son: only obey my voice, and go fetch me them.

source_text: sa lako yani o jekope, ka kauta mai na manumanu vei tinana. sa vakarautaka o tinana me vaka sara ga sa dautaleitaka o aisake.
target_text: and he went, and fetched, and brought them to his mother: and his mother made savoury meat, such as his father loved.

source_text: sa kauta mai o tinana nai sulu vinaka nei iso sa tiko ga vua e vale, ka sa vakasulumi jekope kina.
target_text: and rebekah took goodly raiment of her eldest son esau, which were with her in the house, and put them upon jacob her younger son:

source_text: sa vakabira tu e ligana na vuti ni me kei na domona talega.
target_text: and she put the skins of the kids of the goats upon his hands, and upon the smooth of his neck:

source_text: sa solia na kakana kei na madrai ea vakarautaka mai ki na ligai jekope na luvena.
target_text: and she gave the savoury meat and the bread, which she had prepared, into the hand of her son jacob.

source_text: sa lako yani o jekope vei tamana ka tukuna, "tamaqu, " sa sauma mai, "oi au oqo, o cei o iko na luvequ? "
target_text: and he came unto his father, and said, my father: and he said, here am i; who art thou, my son?

source_text: sa tukuna o jekope vei tamana, "oi au o iso, na nomu ulumatua, au sa cakava mai oqo, me vaka o sa tukuna mai, au kerea mo duri cake, mo dabe, mo kania na ka au sa vakarautaka mai. me vakalouvinakataki au kina na yalomu. "
target_text: and jacob said unto his father, i am esau thy firstborn; i have done according as thou badest me: arise, i pray thee, sit and eat of my venison, that thy soul may bless me.

source_text: sa tukuna mai o aisake vei luvena, "o sa kunea vakacava, sa rui totolo na veika o cakava? " sa sauma yani o jekope, "na kalou o jiova sa kauta mai vei au. "
target_text: and isaac said unto his son, how is it that thou hast found it so quickly, my son? and he said, because the lord thy god brought it to me.

source_text: sa tukuna tale o aisake, "toso voleka mai me'u yamoca na ligamu, se o iko dina o iso se sega. "
target_text: and isaac said unto jacob, come near, i pray thee, that i may feel thee, my son, whether thou be my very son esau or not.

source_text: sa toso voleka yani vei tamana o jekope, ka sa yamoci koya sara o tamana ka tukuna, "na domo sa domo i jekope, ia, na ligana sa ligai iso ga. "
target_text: and jacob went near unto isaac his father; and he felt him, and said, the voice is jacob's voice, but the hands are the hands of esau.

source_text: sa sega ni kilai koya baleta ni sa vutivutia na ligana me vaka na ligai iso. sa qai vosa vakalouvinakataki koya.
target_text: and he discerned him not, because his hands were hairy, as his brother esau's hands: so he blessed him.

source_text: sa qai tukuna yani, "sai iko dina oqo, iso na luvequ? " sa sauma mai o jekope, "sai au. "
target_text: and he said, art thou my very son esau? and he said, i am.

source_text: sa tukuna o aisake, "kauta mai, me'u mai kania na ka o sa vakarautaka mai “me vakalouvinakataki iko kina na yaloqu. " sa kauta mai o jekope, sa kana sara o aisake, sa kau talega mai vua na waini ka sa gunu talega.
target_text: and he said, bring it near to me, and i will eat of my son's venison, that my soul may bless thee. and he brought it near to him, and he did eat: and he brought him wine, and he drank.

source_text: o aisake na tamana sa tukuna vua, "toso voleka mai ka reguci au, na luvequ. "
target_text: and his father isaac said unto him, come near now, and kiss me, my son.

source_text: sa toso voleka mai o jekope ka reguci tamana. sa boica na nona i sulu o aisake, ka vosa vakalouvinakataki koya ka vaka: "nai boi kei na luvequ, sa vaka nai boi ni vanua sa vakalouvinakataka o jiova.
target_text: and he came near, and kissed him: and he smelled the smell of his raiment, and blessed him, and said, see, the smell of my son is as the smell of a field which the lord hath blessed:

source_text: o koya oqo me solia kina vei iko o jiova na tegu mai lomalagi, na vuavuai vinaka kei vuravura, me levu na sila kei na waini.
target_text: therefore god give thee of the dew of heaven, and the fatness of the earth, and plenty of corn and wine:

source_text: me ra qaravi iko na tamata, ka cuva vei iko na veimatanitu, o na turaga vei ira na tacimu, o ira na luvei tinamu era na cuva vei iko, era na kalouca o ira era na vakaloucataki iko, era na kalouvinaka o ira era na vakalouvinakataki iko! "
target_text: let people serve thee, and nations bow down to thee: be lord over thy brethren, and let thy mother's sons bow down to thee: cursed be every one that curseth thee, and blessed be he that blesseth thee.

source_text: ni sa oti na nona vakalouvinakataki jekope o aisake ka sa curu yani ki tuba mai vei aisake na tamana “sa basika mai o iso ena nona lesu tiko mai na vakasasa.
target_text: and it came to pass, as soon as isaac had made an end of blessing jacob, and jacob was yet scarce gone out from the presence of isaac his father, that esau his brother came in from his hunting.

source_text: sa vakarautaka sara mai vakavinaka na nona lewe ni vakasasa ka kauta mai vei tamana ka tukuna, "me duri mada na tamaqu ka kania mada na lewe ni vakasasa na luvena, me rawa ni vakalouvinakataka kina na luvena mai na yalona. "
target_text: and he also had made savoury meat, and brought it unto his father, and said unto his father, let my father arise, and eat of his son's venison, that thy soul may bless me.

source_text: sa tarogi koya o aisake na tamana, "o cei o iko? " sa sauma mai, "o au na luvemu ulumatua, o iso. "
target_text: and isaac his father said unto him, who art thou? and he said, i am thy son, thy firstborn esau.

source_text: sa kidacala o aisake ka sautaninini, ka tukuna, "o cei? sa e vei o koya sa vakasasa oti ka liu mai, ka sa kauta oti mai vei au? au sa kana oti ni se bera ni o lako mai, au sa vakalouvinakataki koya “sa vakalouvinakataki dina o koya. "
target_text: and isaac trembled very exceedingly, and said, who? where is he that hath taken venison, and brought it me, and i have eaten of all before thou camest, and have blessed him? yea, and he shall be blessed.

source_text: ni sa rogoca oiso na vosa nei tamana, sa tagi vakararawa sara ka tukuna vei tamana "o au talega tamaqu, mo vakalouvinakataki au? "
target_text: and when esau heard the words of his father, he cried with a great and exceeding bitter cry, and said unto his father, bless me, even me also, o my father.

source_text: sa tukuna o aisake, "sa lako mai o tacimu ena veivakaisini, ka sa kauta tani na nomu vakalouvinakataki. "
target_text: and he said, thy brother came with subtilty, and hath taken away thy blessing.

source_text: sa tukuna tale o iso, "sa sega li ni vakayacani donu o jekope? ni sa vakaisini (jekope) au vaka rua oqo “sa kauta tani na noqu i tutu vakaulumatua, oqo, sa kauta talega na noqu vakalouvinakataki! " sa tukuna talega, "ka o sega ni bau biuta tu vei au edua na ka me noqui votavota? "
target_text: and he said, is not he rightly named jacob? for he hath supplanted me these two times: he took away my birthright; and, behold, now he hath taken away my blessing. and he said, hast thou not reserved a blessing for me?

source_text: sa sauma mai o aisake ka tukuna vei iso, "raica, au sa cakava me nomu turaga o koya, o ira kece na tacina, me ra nona i talai, na sila kei na waini me maroroi koya “na cava tale me'u cakava vei iko na luvequ? "
target_text: and isaac answered and said unto esau, behold, i have made him thy lord, and all his brethren have i given to him for servants; and with corn and wine have i sustained him: and what shall i do now unto thee, my son?

source_text: sa tukuna o iso vei tamana, "sa tu beka ga vei iko e dua na vosa ni veivakalouvinakataki? e sega ni rawa vei iko mo vakalouvinakataki au talega tamaqu! " sa tagi vakadomoilevu sara o iso.
target_text: and esau said unto his father, hast thou but one blessing, my father? bless me, even me also, o my father. and esau lifted up his voice, and wept.

source_text: sa sauma mai o aisake na tamana ka tukuna vua, "raica na nomu i tikotiko, ena vanua vuavuai e vuravura, kei na kena tegu mai lomalagi e na lutu tiko ga mai.
target_text: and isaac his father answered and said unto him, behold, thy dwelling shall be the fatness of the earth, and of the dew of heaven from above;

source_text: o na bula ena nomu i seleiwau, ka o na qaravi tacimu; ena yaco na gauna ni o sa sega ni kunea na vakacegu, - o na musuka tani na nona i vua mai na domomu. "
target_text: and by thy sword shalt thou live, and shalt serve thy brother; and it shall come to pass when thou shalt have the dominion, that thou shalt break his yoke from off thy neck.

source_text: o iso sa cati jekope vakalevu ena vuku ni veivakalouvinakataki sa solia vua o tamana (aisake), sa tukuna kina e lomana o iso, "sa voleka oqo na siga ni so mate vei tamaqu, ni oti o ya, au na qai vakamatei jekope. "
target_text: and esau hated jacob because of the blessing wherewith his father blessed him: and esau said in his heart, the days of mourning for my father are at hand; then will i slay my brother jacob.

source_text: sa tukuni vei rapeka na vosa oqo nei iso. sa kacivi jekope mai ka tukuna vua, "raica sa vakamalumalumutaki koya tiko o iso ena vukumu “ni sa nakita tiko me vakamatei iko.
target_text: and these words of esau her elder son were told to rebekah: and she sent and called jacob her younger son, and said unto him, behold, thy brother esau, as touching thee, doth comfort himself, purposing to kill thee.

source_text: "oqo na luvequ “rogoca na noqu vosa, tucake, dro ki vei lepani na ganequ ki arana.
target_text: now therefore, my son, obey my voice; and arise, flee thou to laban my brother to haran;

source_text: "tiko mai kea me vica na siga, qai lesu mai ni sa oti na nona cudru,
