target_text: and tarry with him a few days, until thy brother's fury turn away;

source_text: "ni sa oti na nona cudru ka sa guilecava talega, au na qai talatala yani mo lako mai. na cava me'u rarawa kina vakalevu ena dua ga na siga? "
target_text: until thy brother's anger turn away from thee, and he forget that which thou hast done to him: then i will send, and fetch thee from thence: why should i be deprived also of you both in one day?

source_text: o rapeka sa tukuna vei aisake, "au sa rarawa tiko vakalevu ena vukudra na luvei eci yalewa; kevaka sa wati jekope e dua na luvei eci “me vakataki ira na goneyalewa ni vanua oqo. ena vinaka vakacava na noqu bula vei au? "
target_text: and rebekah said to isaac, i am weary of my life because of the daughters of heth: if jacob take a wife of the daughters of heth, such as these which are of the daughters of the land, what good shall my life do me?

source_text: o aisake sa kacivi jekope ka vosa vakalouvinakataki koya ka vakaroti koya ka tukuna, "mo kua ni taura e dua me watimu, ena vanua oqo o kenani.
target_text: and isaac called jacob, and blessed him, and charged him, and said unto him, thou shalt not take a wife of the daughters of canaan.

source_text: "mo lako ki na vanua o padani-erami ki na vale nei pecueli (tukamu) na tama i tinamu; ka taura mai kea e dua na watimu, mai na vale nei lepani na ganei tinamu.
target_text: arise, go to padanaram, to the house of bethuel thy mother's father; and take thee a wife from thence of the daughters of laban thy mother's brother.

source_text: "na kalou kaukauwa, me vakalouvinakataki iko, ka mo yagavakalevu ka vuavuai, mo vakalewelevutaki talega “mo dua nai soqosoqo tamata;
target_text: and god almighty bless thee, and make thee fruitful, and multiply thee, that thou mayest be a multitude of people;

source_text: me soli talega vei iko na veivakalouvinakataki i eparaama, vei iko kei ira talega na nomu kawa era na muri iko mai “mo taukena kina na vanua o tiko vulagi kina, na vanua sa solia na kalou vei eparaama. "
target_text: and give thee the blessing of abraham, to thee, and to thy seed with thee; that thou mayest inherit the land wherein thou art a stranger, which god gave unto abraham.

source_text: sa vakatalai jekope yani o aisake, ka sa lako sara ki padani-erami vei lepani na luvei petueli na kai siria na ganei rapeka na tinadrau o jekope kei iso.
target_text: and isaac sent away jacob: and he went to padanaram unto laban, son of bethuel the syrian, the brother of rebekah, jacob's and esau's mother.

source_text: o iso sa raici aisake ni sa vakalouvinakataki jekope ka sa vakatala yani ki padanierami me taura mai kea e dua na watina, ni sa tukuna, "mo kua ni taura me watimu e dua na yalewa ni kenani, "
target_text: when esau saw that isaac had blessed jacob, and sent him away to padanaram, to take him a wife from thence; and that as he blessed him he gave him a charge, saying, thou shalt not take a wife of the daughters of canaan;

source_text: ka sa talairawarawa vei tamana kei tinana o jekope ni sa lako yani ki padani-erami.
target_text: and that jacob obeyed his father and his mother, and was gone to padanaram;

source_text: sa raica talega o iso, ni sa sega ni vinakati ira na yalewa ni kenani o tamana o aisake.
target_text: and esau seeing that the daughters of canaan pleased not isaac his father;

source_text: o iso sa lako yani vei isimeli ka tauri maelaci na luvei isimeli, na luvei eparaama, na ganei nebatoce me watina, ka sai kuri ni watina era sa tiko rawa.
target_text: then went esau unto ishmael, and took unto the wives which he had mahalath the daughter of ishmael abraham's son, the sister of nebajoth, to be his wife.

source_text: sa lako tani o jekope mai periesepa ka lako vaka ki arana.
target_text: and jacob went out from beersheba, and went toward haran.

source_text: sa yaco ki na dua na vanua ka tiko kina ena bogi taucoko, baleta ni sa dromu na mata ni siga. sa taura e dua na vatu me nona i lokoloko ka davo sobu me moce.
target_text: and he lighted upon a certain place, and tarried there all night, because the sun was set; and he took of the stones of that place, and put them for his pillows, and lay down in that place to sleep.

source_text: sa qai tadra, ka raica ni sa dua nai kabakaba sa lako yani e vuravura ka yacovi lomalagi, kei ira na agilosi ni kalou era sa veilakoyaki tiko kina “lako cake ka lako sobu mai.
target_text: and he dreamed, and behold a ladder set up on the earth, and the top of it reached to heaven: and behold the angels of god ascending and descending on it.

source_text: o jiova sa tu mai cake ka tukuna: "oi au o jiova na kalou i eparaama, na kalou i aisake. na qele o davoca tiko oqori, au na solia vei iko kei ira na nomu kawa.
target_text: and, behold, the lord stood above it, and said, i am the lord god of abraham thy father, and the god of isaac: the land whereon thou liest, to thee will i give it, and to thy seed;

source_text: "o ira talega na nomu kawa era na vaka na kuvu ni qele (kedra i wiliwili); o na tete vaka ki na ra, ki na tokalau, ki na vualiku ki na ceva talega. mai vei iko kei ira na nomu kawa, ena vakalouvinakataki kina o vuravura taucoko.
target_text: and thy seed shall be as the dust of the earth, and thou shalt spread abroad to the west, and to the east, and to the north, and to the south: and in thee and in thy seed shall all the families of the earth be blessed.

source_text: "raica, au sa tiko vata kei iko, me'u maroroi iko ena vanua kecega o sa na lako kina ka au na kauti iko lesu tale mai ki na vanua oqo, au na sega ni laivi iko me yacova ni'u sa cakava kece na veika au sa vosa kina vei iko. "
target_text: and, behold, i am with thee, and will keep thee in all places whither thou goest, and will bring thee again into this land; for i will not leave thee, until i have done that which i have spoken to thee of.

source_text: sa yadra vakasauri o jekope mai na nona moce ka tukuna, "sa dina, o jiova sa tiko eke ka au sa sega tu ni kila. "
target_text: and jacob awaked out of his sleep, and he said, surely the lord is in this place; and i knew it not.

source_text: sa rerevaka levu ka tukuna, "sa vanua vinaka dina oqo, sa sega tale ni dua na ka oqo “na vale ni kalou ga “oqo sara ga na matamata ki lomalagi! "
target_text: and he was afraid, and said, how dreadful is this place! this is none other but the house of god, and this is the gate of heaven.

source_text: sa yadra vakamataka lailai o jekope, sa taura na vatu (nona i lokoloko) sa vakaduria me duru, ka sa lumuta ena waiwai.
target_text: and jacob rose up early in the morning, and took the stone that he had put for his pillows, and set it up for a pillar, and poured oil upon the top of it.

source_text: sa vakatoka na yaca ni vanua o ya me peceli; na yaca ni vanua o ya e liu o luse.
target_text: and he called the name of that place bethel: but the name of that city was called luz at the first.

source_text: sa yalayala (bubului) o jekope ka vaka: "kevaka sa tiko vata kei au na kalou, ka maroroi au ena sala au sa lakova tiko oqo, ka solia vei au na kakana me'u kania kei nai sulu me'u suluma,
target_text: and jacob vowed a vow, saying, if god will be with me, and will keep me in this way that i go, and will give me bread to eat, and raiment to put on,

source_text: "me'u lesu tale mai kina ki na vale nei tamaqu ena vakacegu “o jiova, sa na noqu kalou.
target_text: so that i come again to my father's house in peace; then shall the lord be my god:

source_text: "na vatu oqo au sa vakaduria me duru, sa na vale ni kalou. na veika kece o ni na solia vei au, na kena i katini (sigana) au na solia vakaidina vei kemuni. "
target_text: and this stone, which i have set for a pillar, shall be god's house: and of all that thou shalt give me i will surely give the tenth unto thee.

source_text: o jekope sa lako ena nona i lakolako ka sa yaco ki na nodra vanua na tamata mai na tokalau.
target_text: then jacob went on his journey, and came into the land of the people of the east.

source_text: sa rai yani ka raica e dua na mata ni wai ena buca; era sa davo voleka tu kina e tolu na qele ni sipi. era sa dau gunu na sipi mai na mata ni wai oqori. e dua na vatu levu sa ubi tu kina na mata ni wai.
target_text: and he looked, and behold a well in the field, and, lo, there were three flocks of sheep lying by it; for out of that well they watered the flocks: and a great stone was upon the well's mouth.

source_text: era sa dau lako yani ki kea na qele ni manumanu, sa dau vakaqiqici tani na vatu mai na gusu ni mata ni wai, era sa dau gunu na sipi ka sogo tale na mata ni wai ena vatu.
target_text: and thither were all the flocks gathered: and they rolled the stone from the well's mouth, and watered the sheep, and put the stone again upon the well's mouth in his place.

source_text: sa taro yani vei ira o jekope, "kemudou na taciqu, oi kemudou sara mada mai vei? " e ratou sa sauma, "mai arana. "
target_text: and jacob said unto them, my brethren, whence be ye? and they said, of haran are we.

source_text: sa qai taro tale vei iratou, "dou sa kilai lepani beka, na luvei neori? " e ratou sa sauma mai, "keitou sa kilai koya. "
target_text: and he said unto them, know ye laban the son of nahor? and they said, we know him.

source_text: "sa vinaka tiko beka o koya se sega? " e ratou sa sauma mai, "io, sa bula vinaka o koya, raica o raijeli na luvena yalewa sa lako tiko mai oqori kei ira na sipi. "
target_text: and he said unto them, is he well? and they said, he is well: and, behold, rachel his daughter cometh with the sheep.

source_text: sa tukuna sara o jekope, "raica e se sigalevu tutu na vanua, e se sega ni kena gauna me ra kacivi vata mai na sipi. me ra gunu na sipi ka dou vakania talega. "
target_text: and he said, lo, it is yet high day, neither is it time that the cattle should be gathered together: water ye the sheep, and go and feed them.

source_text: e ratou sa tukuna mai, "keitou na sega ni cakava oqori, vakavo ke sa soqoni vata kece mai na manumanu, ka vakaqiqici tani na vatu mai na gusu ni mata ni wai, era na qai gunu. "
target_text: and they said, we cannot, until all the flocks be gathered together, and till they roll the stone from the well's mouth; then we water the sheep.

source_text: ni se vosa tiko ga vei ira, sa lako mai o raijeli kei na sipi nei tamana “ni sa dau qarava na vakatawani ni sipi.
target_text: and while he yet spake with them, rachel came with her father's sheep: for she kept them.

source_text: o jekope ni sa raici raijeli, na luvei lepani na ganei tinana, kei na sipi nei lepani, sa toso yani o jekope ka vakaqiqica tani na vatu mai na mata ni wai, ka vakagunuvi ira na sipi nei lepani.
target_text: and it came to pass, when jacob saw rachel the daughter of laban his mother's brother, and the sheep of laban his mother's brother, that jacob went near, and rolled the stone from the well's mouth, and watered the flock of laban his mother's brother.

source_text: o jekope sa reguci raijeli, ka sa tagi.
target_text: and jacob kissed rachel, and lifted up his voice, and wept.

source_text: o jekope sa tukuna vei raijeli ni o koya na wekai lepani, ka ni sa luvei rapeka. sa cici yani o raijeli ka tukuna vei tamana.
target_text: and jacob told rachel that he was her father's brother, and that he was rebekah's son: and she ran and told her father.

source_text: ni sa rogoca o lepani nai tukutuku kei jekope na luvei ganena, sa cici sara yani me sotavi koya. sa mokoti koya ka reguci koya ka kauti koya sara yani ki nona vale. sa tukuna o jekope na veika kece vei lepani.
target_text: and it came to pass, when laban heard the tidings of jacob his sister's son, that he ran to meet him, and embraced him, and kissed him, and brought him to his house. and he told laban all these things.

source_text: sa tukuna vua o lepani, "e dina, e daru sa sui vata ka lewe vata. " sa tiko e kea o jekope me vula dua.
target_text: and laban said to him, surely thou art my bone and my flesh. and he abode with him the space of a month.

source_text: sa tukuna o lepani vei jekope, "baleta ni o sa wekaqu, e dodonu beka mo cakacaka wale vei au? tukuna mada vei au, na cava me kemu i sau? "
target_text: and laban said unto jacob, because thou art my brother, shouldest thou therefore serve me for nought? tell me, what shall thy wages be?

source_text: o lepani sa rua tiko na luvena yalewa: sa qase o lia ka gone o raijeli.
target_text: and laban had two daughters: the name of the elder was leah, and the name of the younger was rachel.

source_text: sa mata kamica o lia, ia, o raijeli sa rui totoka qai talei na kena i rairai.
target_text: leah was tender eyed; but rachel was beautiful and well favoured.

source_text: o jekope e taleitaki raijeli vakalevu ka tukuna, "au na qaravi iko me vitu na yabaki ena vuku i raijeli na luvemu yalewa gone. "
target_text: and jacob loved rachel; and said, i will serve thee seven years for rachel thy younger daughter.

source_text: sa sauma o lepani, "e vinaka me'u solia na luvequ vei iko “ka sega ni vua tale e dua na tagane. mo tiko mada vata kei au. "
target_text: and laban said, it is better that i give her to thee, than that i should give her to another man: abide with me.

source_text: sa cakacakataka na vitu na yabaki o jekope ena vuku i raijeli “sa vaka ga e vica na siga na vitu na yabaki oqori, baleta ni sa rui vinakati raijeli vakalevu.
target_text: and jacob served seven years for rachel; and they seemed unto him but a few days, for the love he had to her.

source_text: o jekope sa tukuna vei lepani, "solia vei au na watiqu, ni sa oti na noqu veisiga ni veiqaravi, ni'u sa vinakata me curumi koya. "
target_text: and jacob said unto laban, give me my wife, for my days are fulfilled, that i may go in unto her.

source_text: sa kacivi ira kece mai na tamata o lepani, ka cakava e dua na kakana levu.
target_text: and laban gathered together all the men of the place, and made a feast.

source_text: ni sa yakavi bogi mai, sa tauri lia ka kauti koya mai vei jekope. sa curumi koya sara o jekope.
target_text: and it came to pass in the evening, that he took leah his daughter, and brought her to him; and he went in unto her.

source_text: o lepani sa soli siliva na nona dauveiqaravi me dauveiqaravi nei lia.
target_text: and laban gave unto his daughter leah zilpah his maid for an handmaid.

source_text: ni sa mataka mai, sa kila o jekope ni sa i lia ka sega ni o raijeli. sa tarogi lepani sara, "na cava o sa cakava vei au? e sega beka ni au a cakacaka ena vuku i raijeli? na cava o sa vakaisini au kina? "
target_text: and it came to pass, that in the morning, behold, it was leah: and he said to laban, what is this thou hast done unto me? did not i serve with thee for rachel? wherefore then hast thou beguiled me?

source_text: sa sauma o lepani, "e sega ni dodonu me caka oqo, ena neimami vanua “me dau soli e liu na gone mai vua na qase.
target_text: and laban said, it must not be so done in our country, to give the younger before the firstborn.

source_text: "mo cakacakataka talega na nona gauna, me qai soli kina vei iko. "
target_text: fulfil her week, and we will give thee this also for the service which thou shalt serve with me yet seven other years.

source_text: sa qai cakacakataka o jekope na vitu tale na yabaki, sa qai soli vei koya o raijeli me watina.
target_text: and jacob did so, and fulfilled her week: and he gave him rachel his daughter to wife also.

source_text: o lepani sa soli bila na nona dauveiqaravi, me dauveiqaravi nei raijeli.
target_text: and laban gave to rachel his daughter bilhah his handmaid to be her maid.

source_text: sa curumi raijeli o jekope ni sa taleitaki koya vakalevu, ni sa qaravi lepani ena vitu tale na yabaki.
target_text: and he went in also unto rachel, and he loved also rachel more than leah, and served with him yet seven other years.

source_text: ni sa raica o jiova ni sega ni lomani vakalevu o lia “na kalou sa qai dolava na kato ni gone nei lia, qai sogota na kato nei raijeli.
target_text: and when the lord saw that leah was hated, he opened her womb: but rachel was barren.

source_text: sa kunekune o lia ka vakasucuma e dua na tagane, ka vakayacani koya me o rupeni; ni sa tukuna, "o jiova sa raica dina na noqu rarawa. oqo ena lomani au kina o na watiqu jekope. "
target_text: and leah conceived, and bare a son, and she called his name reuben: for she said, surely the lord hath looked upon my affliction; now therefore my husband will love me.

source_text: sa kunekune tale ka vakasucuma e dua na tagane ka tukuna, "o jiova sa rogoca ni'u sa sega ni lomani. oqo sa solia kina vei au e dua tale na tagane. " sa yacana o simione.
target_text: and she conceived again, and bare a son; and said, because the lord hath heard that i was hated, he hath therefore given me this son also: and she called his name simeon.

source_text: sa kunekune ka vakasucuma tale e dua na tagane, sa tukuna kina, "oqo sa na qai kabiti au kina o watiqu (jekope), baleta ni'u sa vakasucuma vua e tolu na gone tagane. " sa yacana o livai.
target_text: and she conceived again, and bare a son; and said, now this time will my husband be joined unto me, because i have born him three sons: therefore was his name called levi.

source_text: sa kunekune tale ka vakasucuma e dua tale na tagane, sa tukuna kina, "oqo au na vakavinavinaka vua na kalou. " sa vakayacana kina na gone me o juta. sa qai tu vakadua na nona vakasucu gone.
target_text: and she conceived again, and bare a son: and she said, now will i praise the lord: therefore she called his name judah; and left bearing.

source_text: ni sa raica o raijeli ni sa sega tiko ni vakaluveni vei jekope, sa vuvutaki tuakana vakalevu, sa tukuna vei jekope, "solia vei au e dua na gone, de'u na qai mate! "
target_text: and when rachel saw that she bare jacob no children, rachel envied her sister; and said unto jacob, give me children, or else i die.

source_text: sa cudru vakalevu o jekope ena vuku i raijeli, sa tukuna kina, "o au beka na kalou ni o koya ga e lewa na vakaluveni, ni o koya ga e sogota tiko na nomu bola ni gone? "
target_text: and jacob's anger was kindled against rachel: and he said, am i in god's stead, who hath withheld from thee the fruit of the womb?

source_text: sa tukuna mai o raijeli, "oqo o bila na noqu dauveiqaravi, vakacurumi iko vua me vakasucuma kina e dua na gone e duruqu, me dua kina na luvequ mai vua. "
target_text: and she said, behold my maid bilhah, go in unto her; and she shall bear upon my knees, that i may also have children by her.

source_text: sa soli bila vua, ka sa curumi koya sara o jekope.
target_text: and she gave him bilhah her handmaid to wife: and jacob went in unto her.

source_text: sa kunekune o bila, ka vakasucuma vei jekope e dua na tagane.
target_text: and bilhah conceived, and bare jacob a son.

source_text: sa tukuna o raijeli, "sa vakatulewa vei au na kalou; sa rogoca talega o koya na domoqu ka solia vei au e dua na gone. " sa vakayacani koya kina me o tani.
target_text: and rachel said, god hath judged me, and hath also heard my voice, and hath given me a son: therefore called she his name dan.

source_text: sa kunekune tale na dauveiqaravi nei raijeli, o bila, sa vakasucuma vei jekope nai karua ni luvena.
target_text: and bilhah rachel's maid conceived again, and bare jacob a second son.

source_text: sa tukuna o raijeli, "au sa veiqati vakalevu kei na tuakaqu ia, au sa toso tikoga. " sa vakayacana na gone me o navitalai.
target_text: and rachel said, with great wrestlings have i wrestled with my sister, and i have prevailed: and she called his name naphtali.

source_text: o lia, ni sa sega tiko ni dua tale na luvena, sa tauri siliva na nona dauveiqaravi ka solia vei jekope me curumi koya.
target_text: when leah saw that she had left bearing, she took zilpah her maid, and gave her jacob to wife.

source_text: o siliva sa vakasucuma vei jekope e dua na tagane.
target_text: and zilpah leah's maid bare jacob a son.

source_text: sa tukuna o lia, "sa lako tiko mai na mataivalu. " sa vakayacana me o kata.
target_text: and leah said, a troop cometh: and she called his name gad.

source_text: o siliva sa vakasucuma nai karua ni luvei jekope.
target_text: and zilpah leah's maid bare jacob a second son.

source_text: sa tukuna o lia, "au sa marau, ni ra na tukuna vei au na goneyalewa na dauveivakalouvinakataki. " sa vakayacani koya kina me o aseri.
target_text: and leah said, happy am i, for the daughters will call me blessed: and she called his name asher.

source_text: o rupeni sa lako yani ena gauna ni tatamusuki, ka sa kunea mai e so na wainimate ni moce, ka sa kauta sara mai vei tinana. sa kerekere yani o raijeli vei lia ka vaka: "au kerea e so na wai ni moce nei rupeni. "
target_text: and reuben went in the days of wheat harvest, and found mandrakes in the field, and brought them unto his mother leah. then rachel said to leah, give me, i pray thee, of thy son's mandrakes.

source_text: sa sauma mai o lia, "e se lailai vei iko o jekope na watiqu? oqo, o sa vinakata tale na wai ni moce nei luvequ talega? " sa sauma yani o raijeli, "drau moce vata mada ena bogi oqo, mei sosomi ni wai ni moce oqori. "
target_text: and she said unto her, is it a small matter that thou hast taken my husband? and wouldest thou take away my son's mandrakes also? and rachel said, therefore he shall lie with thee to night for thy son's mandrakes.

source_text: ni sa lesu mai o jekope mai na veiwere ena yakavi, sa lako yani o lisa ka tukuna vua, "mo mai curu vei au, ni sa o saumi oti ena wai ni moce nei luvequ. " e rau sa mai veimoceri ena bogi o ya.
target_text: and jacob came out of the field in the evening, and leah went out to meet him, and said, thou must come in unto me; for surely i have hired thee with my son's mandrakes. and he lay with her that night.

source_text: na kalou sa rogoci lia, sa kunekune ka vakasucuma vei jekope nai ka lima ni luvena tagane.
target_text: and god hearkened unto leah, and she conceived, and bare jacob the fifth son.

source_text: sa tukuna kina o lia, "na kalou sa solia vei au na kequ i voli, ni'u sa solia na noqu dauveiqaravi vei watiqu. " sa vakayacani koya kina me o isakari.
target_text: and leah said, god hath given me my hire, because i have given my maiden to my husband: and she called his name issachar.

source_text: sa kunekune tale o lia, ka sa vakasucuma nai ka ono ni luvena vei jekope.
target_text: and leah conceived again, and bare jacob the sixth son.

source_text: sa tukuna o lia, "na kalou sa vakatikora vei au na veika vivinaka, oqo sa na tikoga kina vata kei au o na watiqu, baleta ni'u sa vakasucuma vua e ono na luvena tagane. " sa vakayacani koya kina me o sevuloni.
target_text: and leah said, god hath endued me with a good dowry; now will my husband dwell with me, because i have born him six sons: and she called his name zebulun.

source_text: sa qai vakasucuma tale e dua na luvena yalewa, ka vakayacani koya me o taina.
target_text: and afterwards she bare a daughter, and called her name dinah.

source_text: na kalou sa qai nanumi raijeli, sa rogoci koya ka dolava na nona kato ni gone.
target_text: and god remembered rachel, and god hearkened to her, and opened her womb.

source_text: sa kunekune ka vakasucuma e dua na tagane, ka tukuna, "na kalou sa kauta tani na noqu rogorogo ca. "
target_text: and she conceived, and bare a son; and said, god hath taken away my reproach:

source_text: sa vakayacani koya me o joseva ka tukuna kina, "o jiova ena solia tale vei au e dua na luvequ tagane. "
target_text: and she called his name joseph; and said, the lord shall add to me another son.

source_text: ni sa vakasucumi joseva oti o raijeli, sa tukuna o jekope vei lepani, "laivi au me'u lako, me'u lako ki na noqu tikina, ki na noqu vanua.
target_text: and it came to pass, when rachel had born joseph, that jacob said unto laban, send me away, that i may go unto mine own place, and to my country.

source_text: "soli ira vei au na watiqu, kei ira na luvequ, o ira, au sa qaravi iko kina, ka laivi keimami me keimami lako, o sa kila talega na veiqaravi au sa cakava vei iko. "
target_text: give me my wives and my children, for whom i have served thee, and let me go: for thou knowest my service which i have done thee.

source_text: sa tukuna vua o lepani, "mo tiko mada, kevaka au sa kune loloma e matamu, ni'u sa kila ka vulica ni o jiova sa vakalouvinakataki au ena vukumu. "
target_text: and laban said unto him, i pray thee, if i have found favour in thine eyes, tarry: for i have learned by experience that the lord hath blessed me for thy sake.

source_text: sa qai tukuna tale yani, "tukuna vei au na kemu i sau, au na solia vei iko. "
target_text: and he said, appoint me thy wages, and i will give it.

source_text: sa tukuna vua o jekope, "o sa kila vinaka na noqu qaravi iko kei na qaravi ni nomu manumanu.
target_text: and he said unto him, thou knowest how i have served thee, and how thy cattle was with me.

source_text: "na veika e a tu vei iko e liu ni se bera na noqu lako mai, e lailai oqo sa levu sara; na kalou sa vakalouvinakataki iko mai na gauna au a lako mai kina. oqo au na vakania talega na noqu vale ena gauna cava? "
target_text: for it was little which thou hadst before i came, and it is now increased unto a multitude; and the lord hath blessed thee since my coming: and now when shall i provide for mine own house also?

source_text: sa tukuna mai o lepani, "na cava me'u solia vei iko? " sa sauma mai o jekope, "kua ni solia vei au e dua na ka, au na tiko tale me'u veiqaravi, kevaka o solia vei au na ka:
target_text: and he said, what shall i give thee? and jacob said, thou shalt not give me any thing: if thou wilt do this thing for me, i will again feed and keep thy flock.

source_text: "me'u lako mada yani ki na qele ni manumanu ena siga oqo, na manumanu kece sa tavutonotono me wasei mai na kena e dravu. na sipi, na lami, na me, oqori me kequ i sau.
target_text: i will pass through all thy flock to day, removing from thence all the speckled and spotted cattle, and all the brown cattle among the sheep, and the spotted and speckled among the goats: and of such shall be my hire.

source_text: "ena saumi vei au na noqu yalododonu na veisiga ni mataka, ni sa lako mai vei iko na kequ i sau. na manumanu kece sa sega ni tavutonotono ena kedra maliwa na me, ka dravu vei ira na lami, era na kilai me sa ka butakoci, kevaka era sa kune vei au. "
target_text: so shall my righteousness answer for me in time to come, when it shall come for my hire before thy face: every one that is not speckled and spotted among the goats, and brown among the sheep, that shall be counted stolen with me.

source_text: sa tukuna o lepani, "io, oqori sa na vaka na nomu vosa! "
target_text: and laban said, behold, i would it might be according to thy word.

source_text: ena siga o ya sa kauta tani na me tagane kece sa tavutonotono, kei na me yalewa kece sa tavutonotono, o ira kece sa via vulavula tiko, kei na ka dravu kece vei ira na lami, sa solia yani ki na ligadra na luvena.
target_text: and he removed that day the he goats that were ringstraked and spotted, and all the she goats that were speckled and spotted, and every one that had some white in it, and all the brown among the sheep, and gave them into the hand of his sons.

source_text: sa lako yani vakayawa mai vei jekope. (me vaka na yawa, ni lakovi ena tolu na siga). o jekope sa vakania tiko na vo ni manumanu i lepani.
target_text: and he set three days' journey betwixt himself and jacob: and jacob fed the rest of laban's flocks.

source_text: o jekope ka taura tiko na taba ni kau drokadroka mai na amodi kei na jesinati. sa vocia na kulini kau me laurai mai na vulavula ni kau e loma.
target_text: and jacob took him rods of green poplar, and of the hazel and chesnut tree; and pilled white strakes in them, and made the white appear which was in the rods.

source_text: na kau kece sa voci veilutuki, sa cuva tiko mai na mata ni wai ena vanua era dau lako yani kina na manumanu me ra gunu. me ra kunekune kina ni ra sa mai gunu.
target_text: and he set the rods which he had pilled before the flocks in the gutters in the watering troughs when the flocks came to drink, that they should conceive when they came to drink.

source_text: era sa kunekune ena mata ni kau sa voci tu. na manumanu kece era sa vakasucuma mai na ka tavutonotono.
target_text: and the flocks conceived before the rods, and brought forth cattle ringstraked, speckled, and spotted.

source_text: o jekope sa wasei ira na lami, na manumanu kece me ra sa raica tikoga na kau sa voci tu, o ira talega na ka dravu ena qele ni manumanu nei lepani. era sa tiko tani ga na nona manumanu mai vei ira na manumanu nei lepani.
target_text: and jacob did separate the lambs, and set the faces of the flocks toward the ringstraked, and all the brown in the flock of laban; and he put his own flocks by themselves, and put them not unto laban's cattle.

source_text: sa yaco tiko ga na gauna, ni ra sa kunekune tiko mai na manumanu, o jekope sa biuta tiko ga e matada na kau sa voci oti tu. mera kunekune tiko ena nodra vakaraica tikoga na kau sa voci oti tu.
target_text: and it came to pass, whensoever the stronger cattle did conceive, that jacob laid the rods before the eyes of the cattle in the gutters, that they might conceive among the rods.

source_text: na manumanu sa malumalumu sa biu tani “na ka kaukauwa sa nei jekope kei na ka malumalumu sa nei lepani.
target_text: but when the cattle were feeble, he put them not in: so the feebler were laban's, and the stronger jacob's.

source_text: o jekope sa tamata kaukauwa sara ka tamata yaco, sa levu na nona manumanu, sa levu na nona dauveiqaravi yalewa kei na tagane, sa levu sara na nona kameli kei na nona asa.
target_text: and the man increased exceedingly, and had much cattle, and maidservants, and menservants, and camels, and asses.

source_text: sa rogoca o jekope na nodra vosa na luvei lepani ka vaka: "o jekope sa kauta kece na vei ka sa nei tamada, sa rawata na nona i yau, mai na veika ga sa nei tamada. "
target_text: and he heard the words of laban's sons, saying, jacob hath taken away all that was our father's; and of that which was our father's hath he gotten all this glory.

source_text: o jekope sa raica tiko na veitokoni nei lepani vua sa vaka e sega ni vinaka mai me vaka e liu.
target_text: and jacob beheld the countenance of laban, and, behold, it was not toward him as before.

source_text: o jiova sa tukuna vei jekope, "mo lesu tale ki nomu vanua, vei ira na wekamu, au na tiko vata kei iko. "
target_text: and the lord said unto jacob, return unto the land of thy fathers, and to thy kindred; and i will be with thee.

source_text: o jekope sa kacivi raijeli yani kei lia ki na buca ena vanua era sa tiko kina na manumanu,
target_text: and jacob sent and called rachel and leah to the field unto his flock,

source_text: sa tukuna vei rau, "au sa raica na nona veitokoni o tamamudrau “ni sa sega ni vinaka me vaka e liu, ia, na kalou i tamaqu sa tiko vata kei au.
target_text: and said unto them, i see your father's countenance, that it is not toward me as before; but the god of my father hath been with me.

source_text: "drau sa kila talega, au sa qarava na tamamudrau ena noqu kaukauwa kece.
target_text: and ye know that with all my power i have served your father.

source_text: "ia, o tamamudrau sa vakaisini au ena nona veisautaka na kequ i sau vaka tini, ia, na kalou sa sega ni vakatarai koya me vakacacani au.
target_text: and your father hath deceived me, and changed my wages ten times; but god suffered him not to hurt me.

source_text: "kevaka sa tukuna vaka oqo, 'na tavutonotono sa kemu i sau' “era na tavutonotono kece. kevaka sa tukuna, 'na roka veimama ena kemu i sau' “era na roka veimama kece.
target_text: if he said thus, the speckled shall be thy wages; then all the cattle bare speckled: and if he said thus, the ringstraked shall be thy hire; then bare all the cattle ringstraked.

source_text: "na kalou sa kauta tani na manumanu kece i tamamudrau ka solia mai vei au.
target_text: thus god hath taken away the cattle of your father, and given them to me.

source_text: "sa yaco ena gauna era sa kunekune kina na manumanu, au sa raica ena tadra na luve ni me era sa ladelade tiko “era sa veivolavolai kece tu ka tavutonotono.
target_text: and it came to pass at the time that the cattle conceived, that i lifted up mine eyes, and saw in a dream, and, behold, the rams which leaped upon the cattle were ringstraked, speckled, and grisled.

source_text: "na agilosi ni kalou sa vosa vei au ena tadra ka tukuna, 'jekope', sa saumi mai, 'sai au oqo. '
target_text: and the angel of god spake unto me in a dream, saying, jacob: and i said, here am i.

source_text: "na agilosi sa tukuna mai, 'mo raica, na lami kecega sa rika tiko era sa volavolai ka tavutonotono, au sa raica na veika kecega sa cakava o lepani, sa caka ga ena vukumudrau.
target_text: and he said, lift up now thine eyes, and see, all the rams which leap upon the cattle are ringstraked, speckled, and grisled: for i have seen all that laban doeth unto thee.

source_text: 'oi au na kalou kei peceli “na vanua o a lumuta kina na duru ka cakava kina na bubului vei au. mo tucake, ka lako tani mai na vanua oqo, ka lesu ki na vanua e nodra na wekamu dina. '"
target_text: i am the god of bethel, where thou anointedst the pillar, and where thou vowedst a vow unto me: now arise, get thee out from this land, and return unto the land of thy kindred.

source_text: o raijeli kei lia e rau sa sauma vua ka vaka: "e se vo tale tiko e so nai votavota e neirau mai na vale nei tamai keirau?
target_text: and rachel and leah answered and said unto him, is there yet any portion or inheritance for us in our father's house?

source_text: "keirau sa sega beka ni vulagi mai vua, ni sa volitaki keirau ka sa kania kece na neirau i lavo?
target_text: are we not counted of him strangers? for he hath sold us, and hath quite devoured also our money.

source_text: "ni sai yau sa taura kece na kalou mai vei tamai keirau sa neirau kei ira kece na luvei keirau; oqo, na veika ga sa tukuna vei iko na kalou, mo cakava. "
target_text: for all the riches which god hath taken from our father, that is ours, and our children's: now then, whatsoever god hath said unto thee, do.

source_text: o jekope sa vakavodoki ira na luvena kei na watina ena kameli.
target_text: then jacob rose up, and set his sons and his wives upon camels;

source_text: sa kauta talega na nona manumanu kece kei na veika kece e taukena, na veika kece e sa rawata mai padani-erami, ka lako vei aisake na tamana ena vanua o kenani.
target_text: and he carried away all his cattle, and all his goods which he had gotten, the cattle of his getting, which he had gotten in padanaram, for to go to isaac his father in the land of canaan.

source_text: o lepani e se lako tu me kotiva na nona sipi “o raijeli sa butakoca mai na matakau ni vuvale e nei tamana.
target_text: and laban went to shear his sheep: and rachel had stolen the images that were her father's.

source_text: sa dro yani o jekope, ka sa sega ni kila o lepani na kai siria ni sa sega ni via tukuna vua.
target_text: and jacob stole away unawares to laban the syrian, in that he told him not that he fled.

source_text: sa dro yani kei na ka kece sa tu vua, sa takosova yani na wai ka lako vaka ki na veiulunivanua e kiliati.
target_text: so he fled with all that he had; and he rose up, and passed over the river, and set his face toward the mount gilead.

source_text: ena i katolu ni siga sa tukuni vei lepani ni sa dro o jekope.
target_text: and it was told laban on the third day that jacob was fled.

source_text: sa kauti ira na nona ka cici muri jekope me vitu na siga, sa qai yaco vei ira ena veiulunivanua mai kiliati.
target_text: and he took his brethren with him, and pursued after him seven days' journey; and they overtook him in the mount gilead.

source_text: na kalou sa lako mai vei lepani ena bogi ena tadra ka tukuna vua, "qarauni iko, mo lewa vinaka na nomu vosa vei jekope. "
target_text: and god came to laban the syrian in a dream by night, and said unto him, take heed that thou speak not to jacob either good or bad.

source_text: sa yaco yani o lepani vei jekope ni se qai vakaduria tiko na nona veivale laca ena veiulunivanua e kiliati.
target_text: then laban overtook jacob. now jacob had pitched his tent in the mount: and laban with his brethren pitched in the mount of gilead.

source_text: sa tukuna o lepani vei jekope, "na cava o sa cakava, ni o sa lako vakavuni tani mai vei au, o sa kauti rau tani na luvequ me vaka na bobula e na i seleiwau?
target_text: and laban said to jacob, what hast thou done, that thou hast stolen away unawares to me, and carried away my daughters, as captives taken with the sword?

source_text: "na cava o sa dro kina vakavuni ka sega ni tukuna vei au, me'u veitalatala vinaka vei iko ena marau kei na lagasere kei na tibereli na api?
target_text: wherefore didst thou flee away secretly, and steal away from me; and didst not tell me, that i might have sent thee away with mirth, and with songs, with tabret, and with harp?

source_text: "o sa sega ni vakatara me'u reguci ira na luvequ tagane kei na luvequ yalewa. o sa cakacaka vakalialia.
target_text: and hast not suffered me to kiss my sons and my daughters? thou hast now done foolishly in so doing.

source_text: "sa tu vei au na kaukauwa me'u veitotogitaki, ia, na kalou i tamamu sa vosa vei au ena bogi ka tukuna, 'qarauni iko vinaka, ni o sa vosa vei jekope. '
target_text: it is in the power of my hand to do you hurt: but the god of your father spake unto me yesternight, saying, take thou heed that thou speak not to jacob either good or bad.

source_text: "o sa lako dina mai oqo, baleta ni o sa via lako ki na vale nei tamamu, ia, na cava ga o butakoca mai kina na noqu kalou-matakau? "
target_text: and now, though thou wouldest needs be gone, because thou sore longedst after thy father's house, yet wherefore hast thou stolen my gods?

source_text: sa sauma o jekope, "au sa rere baleta, 'de o na qai tauri rau tale vakaukauwa na luvemu yalewa. '
target_text: and jacob answered and said to laban, because i was afraid: for i said, peradventure thou wouldest take by force thy daughters from me.

source_text: "vei koya o sa raica vua na nomu kaloumatakau, me kua ni bula o koya. ena matadra na tamata, mo vakatakilakilataka na ka e nomu ka taura yani. " o jekope sa sega ni kila ni sa kauta mai o raijeli na ka o ya.
target_text: with whomsoever thou findest thy gods, let him not live: before our brethren discern thou what is thine with me, and take it to thee. for jacob knew not that rachel had stolen them.

source_text: sa lako yani o lepani ki na vale laca nei jekope, nei lia, nodrau na dauveiqaravi, sa sega ga ni kunea na kalou-matakau. sa lako yani ki na vale laca nei raijeli.
target_text: and laban went into jacob's tent, and into leah's tent, and into the two maidservants' tents; but he found them not. then went he out of leah's tent, and entered into rachel's tent.

source_text: o raijeli sa biuta na kalou-matakau oqo ena i dabedabe ni ose ka qai dabeca yani. sa vakasaqaqara o lepani ena loma ni vale “ka sa sega ga ni kunea.
target_text: now rachel had taken the images, and put them in the camel's furniture, and sat upon them. and laban searched all the tent, but found them not.

source_text: sa tukuna yani vei tamana, "me kua ni ca vua na noqu turaga ni'u sa sega ni tucake rawa, ni sa se tiko na rosi me vaka sa dauyacovi ira ga na yalewa “sa yaco vei au oqo. " sa vakasaqaqara, ia, sa sega ga ni kunea na kaloumatakau.
target_text: and she said to her father, let it not displease my lord that i cannot rise up before thee; for the custom of women is upon me. and he searched, but found not the images.

source_text: sa cudru vakalevu o jekope ka sa vosa vakaukauwa vei lepani ka vaka: "na cava au cala kina vei iko, na cava na noqu i valavala ca, mo cicivi au kina vaka oqo?
target_text: and jacob was wroth, and chode with laban: and jacob answered and said to laban, what is my trespass? what is my sin, that thou hast so hotly pursued after me?

source_text: "o sa vakaraica kece na noqu veika au taukena, na cava e nomu o sa kunea? biuta e mataqu oqo me ra vakatulewa kina o ira kece oqo e matadaru!
target_text: whereas thou hast searched all my stuff, what hast thou found of all thy household stuff? set it here before my brethren and thy brethren, that they may judge betwixt us both.

source_text: "e ruasagavulu na yabaki oqo au sa tiko vata kei iko, na nomu sipi kei na nomu me e se sega vakadua ni bau vakalutuka na luvena, au se sega talega ni kania e dua na luve ni me mai na kedra bai.
target_text: this twenty years have i been with thee; thy ewes and thy she goats have not cast their young, and the rams of thy flock have i not eaten.

source_text: "o ira mada ga era sa basuraki mai vei ira na manumanu kila au sa sega ni kauta mai vei iko, au sa vakaisosomitaka ga na ka sa yali. o sa vinakata ga mai na ligaqu se era butakoci ena siga se ena bogi.
target_text: that which was torn of beasts i brought not unto thee; i bare the loss of it; of my hand didst thou require it, whether stolen by day, or stolen by night.

source_text: "au sa tiko ga kei ira, ena siga sa kani au na katakata, ena bogi na batabata-liliwa, na noqu moce ni vakacegui sa drovaka na mataqu.
target_text: thus i was; in the day the drought consumed me, and the frost by night; and my sleep departed from mine eyes.

source_text: "au sa tiko ena nomu vale me ruasagavulu na yabaki, au qaravi iko me tinikava na yabaki ena vukudrau na luvemu yalewa, ka ono tale na yabaki ena vukudra na manumanu ka o sa veisautaka na kequ i sau vaka tini na gauna.
target_text: thus have i been twenty years in thy house; i served thee fourteen years for thy two daughters, and six years for thy cattle: and thou hast changed my wages ten times.

source_text: "baleta ni sa tiko vata kei au na kalou i tamaqu, na kalou i eparaama, na rerevaki i aisake “e dina, o na vakatalai au tani ena liga lala. na kalou sa raica na noqu vakararawataki kei na cakacaka ni ligaqu, ka sa vunauci iko ena bogi. "
target_text: except the god of my father, the god of abraham, and the fear of isaac, had been with me, surely thou hadst sent me away now empty. god hath seen mine affliction and the labour of my hands, and rebuked thee yesternight.

source_text: sa vosa o lepani vei jekope, "oi rau na yalewa oqo e rau sa noqu, o ira na gone oqo era sa noqu, na manumanu kece oqo sa noqu, na ka kece o raica sa noqu. ia, na cava me'u cakava vei rau na luvequ yalewa oqo kei ira na luvedrau?
target_text: and laban answered and said unto jacob, these daughters are my daughters, and these children are my children, and these cattle are my cattle, and all that thou seest is mine: and what can i do this day unto these my daughters, or unto their children which they have born?

source_text: "lako mai me daru veiyalayalati mada, o iko kei au, me i vakadinadina ena kedaru maliwa. "
target_text: now therefore come thou, let us make a covenant, i and thou; and let it be for a witness between me and thee.

source_text: sa vakaduria o jekope e dua na duru vatu.
target_text: and jacob took a stone, and set it up for a pillar.

source_text: sa tukuna o jekope vei ira na tamata, "mo ni tomi vatu mai, " era sa binia mai ka kana ena dela ni binibini vatu.
target_text: and jacob said unto his brethren, gather stones; and they took stones, and made an heap: and they did eat there upon the heap.

source_text: o lepani sa vakayacana me jeka-saaduca, ia, o jekope sa vakayacana me kaliti.
target_text: and laban called it jegarsahadutha: but jacob called it galeed.

source_text: sa tukuna o lepani, "nai binibini vatu oqo sai vakadinadina vei kedaru ena siga oqo. " sa vakayacani kina me o kaliti,
target_text: and laban said, this heap is a witness between me and thee this day. therefore was the name of it called galeed;

source_text: o misipa talega, baleta ni sa tukuna, "me raica tiko mai o jiova ena kedaru maliwa, ni daru sa dui tikotiko.
target_text: and mizpah; for he said, the lord watch between me and thee, when we are absent one from another.

source_text: "kevaka o sa vakararawataki rau na luvequ, se o sa taura tale e so na watimu, sa sega na tamata me” raica na kalou ga sai vakadinadina vei kedaru! "
target_text: if thou shalt afflict my daughters, or if thou shalt take other wives beside my daughters, no man is with us; see, god is witness betwixt me and thee.

source_text: sa tukuna o lepani vei jekope. "oqo nai binibini vatu kei na duru, sa tu oqo ena kedaru maliwa.
target_text: and laban said to jacob, behold this heap, and behold this pillar, which i have cast betwixt me and thee:

source_text: "oqo nai vakadinadina, nai binibini vatu kei na duru, au na sega ni lako sivia nai binibini oqo ki vei iko, se, mo lako sivia mai nai binibini oqo ki vei au, me ia na veivakacacani.
target_text: this heap be witness, and this pillar be witness, that i will not pass over this heap to thee, and that thou shalt not pass over this heap and this pillar unto me, for harm.

source_text: "na kalou nei eparaama, na kalou nei neori, na kalou nei tamadrau me mai lewa ena kedaru maliwa. " o jekope sa bubului vei koya na rerevaki i aisake na tamana.
target_text: the god of abraham, and the god of nahor, the god of their father, judge betwixt us. and jacob sware by the fear of his father isaac.

source_text: sa vakacabora o jekope nai soro ena ulunivanua, ka sa kacivi ira mai na tamata me ra mai kana. era sa kana madrai ka tiko ena ulunivanua me yacova na mataka.
target_text: then jacob offered sacrifice upon the mount, and called his brethren to eat bread: and they did eat bread, and tarried all night in the mount.

source_text: ena mataka lailai, sa tucake o lepani ka reguci ira na gone kei rau na luvena yalewa ka vosa vakalouvinakataki ira. sa lako o lepani ka lesu tale ki nona vanua.
target_text: and early in the morning laban rose up, and kissed his sons and his daughters, and blessed them: and laban departed, and returned unto his place.

source_text: sa lako yani ena sala o jekope ka sa sota kei ira na agilosi ni kalou.
target_text: and jacob went on his way, and the angels of god met him.

source_text: ni sa raici ira o jekope, sa tukuna, "oqo nai tikotiko ni kalou, " ka sa vakatoka na yaca ni vanua o ya, me maenaimi.
target_text: and when jacob saw them, he said, this is god's host: and he called the name of that place mahanaim.

source_text: o jekope sa vakatala eso na mata vei iso na tacina ena vanua nei sia e itomi.
target_text: and jacob sent messengers before him to esau his brother unto the land of seir, the country of edom.

source_text: sa vakarota vei ira ka vaka, "mo ni vosa vei iso na noqu turaga ka vaka, 'sa tukuna na nomuni tamata o jekope, "au a tiko mai vei lepani ka yacova oqo.
target_text: and he commanded them, saying, thus shall ye speak unto my lord esau; thy servant jacob saith thus, i have sojourned with laban, and stayed there until now:

source_text: "sa tu vei au na bulumakau, na asa, na sipi kei na me, na dauveiqaravi tagane kei na yalewa, au sa talatala yani me tukuni vua na noqu turaga, me'u kune loloma kina e matamuni. "'"
target_text: and i have oxen, and asses, flocks, and menservants, and womenservants: and i have sent to tell my lord, that i may find grace in thy sight.

source_text: era sa lesu tale mai vei jekope na i talaki ka tukuna, "keitou sa lesu mai vei iso, ka sa lako tiko mai o koya me mai sotavi iko. e va na drau na tamata sa tiko vata kei koya. "
target_text: and the messengers returned to jacob, saying, we came to thy brother esau, and also he cometh to meet thee, and four hundred men with him.

source_text: sa rere ka taqaya vakalevu o jekope, ka sa wasei ira na tamata sa tiko vata kei koya, na sipi kei na bulumakau kei na kameli, me rua nai wasewase.
target_text: then jacob was greatly afraid and distressed: and he divided the people that was with him, and the flocks, and herds, and the camels, into two bands;

source_text: sa tukuna sara, "kevaka sa lakova mai o iso ka valuta e dua nai wasewase, me dro yani nai wasewase ka dua. "
target_text: and said, if esau come to the one company, and smite it, then the other company which is left shall escape.

source_text: sa tukuna tale o jekope, "na kalou nei tamaqu o eparaama, na kalou nei aisake na tamaqu, na kalou o koya sa tukuna vei au, 'lesu tale ki na nomu vanua, vei ira na wekamu, ka au na cakacaka vata kei iko':
target_text: and jacob said, o god of my father abraham, and god of my father isaac, the lord which saidst unto me, return unto thy country, and to thy kindred, and i will deal well with thee:

source_text: "ssa sega ni ganiti au na loloma kece kei na dina kece o ni sa vakaraitaka vei au na nomuni tamata. au a takosova mai na joritani kei na noqu i titoko “ia, oqo au sa yaco me rua nai vavakoso levu.
target_text: i am not worthy of the least of all the mercies, and of all the truth, which thou hast shewed unto thy servant; for with my staff i passed over this jordan; and now i am become two bands.

source_text: "mo ni vakabulai au mai na ligai koya na taciqu, mai na ligai iso; ni'u sa rerevaki koya, de qai vala kei au kei ira na gone kei ira na tinadra.
target_text: deliver me, i pray thee, from the hand of my brother, from the hand of esau: for i fear him, lest he will come and smite me, and the mother with the children.

source_text: "ni kemuni sa tukuna, 'au na raica mo na vinaka, ka cakava na nomu kawa me vaka na nuku ni wasawasa, ni sa sega ni wiliki rawa na kena levu. '"
target_text: and thou saidst, i will surely do thee good, and make thy seed as the sand of the sea, which cannot be numbered for multitude.

source_text: sa moce mai kea ena bogi, ka taura na veika sa lako mai ligana “me ka ni loloma vei iso na tacina:
target_text: and he lodged there that same night; and took of that which came to his hand a present for esau his brother;

source_text: e rua na drau na me yalewa, ruasagavulu na me tagane, ruanadrau na sipi yalewa kei na ruasagavulu na sipi tagane,
target_text: two hundred she goats, and twenty he goats, two hundred ewes, and twenty rams,

source_text: e tolusagavulu na kameli yalewa kei na luvedra, vasagavulu na bulumakau yalewa ka tini na bulumakau tagane (yadru), ruasagavulu na asa yalewa kei na tini na kena ka tagane.
target_text: thirty milch camels with their colts, forty kine, and ten bulls, twenty she asses, and ten foals.

source_text: sa solia yani ki na ligadra na nona tamata ka tukuna vei ira, "dou liu yani, ka me dua na veiyawaki ena keda maliwa. "
target_text: and he delivered them into the hand of his servants, every drove by themselves; and said unto his servants, pass over before me, and put a space betwixt drove and drove.

source_text: sa vakarota vei ira sa liu, "kevaka sa sotavi kemuni o iso ka tarogi kemuni, 'o ni sa nei cei? o ni na lako tiko ki vei? e nei cei na veika sa tu oqo? '
target_text: and he commanded the foremost, saying, when esau my brother meeteth thee, and asketh thee, saying, whose art thou? and whither goest thou? and whose are these before thee?

source_text: "mo ni qai tukuna, 'oqo era sa nona na nomuni tamata o jekope. oqo sa soli tiko mai me nona ka ni loloma vua na noqu turaga o iso; o koya talega sa muri tiko mai. '"
target_text: then thou shalt say, they be thy servant jacob's; it is a present sent unto my lord esau: and, behold, also he is behind us.

source_text: sa vakarota talega nai karua ni lawalawa kei nai katolu ka vaka: "me vaka talega oqori na veika mo ni tukuna vei iso ni kemuni sa kunei koya;
target_text: and so commanded he the second, and the third, and all that followed the droves, saying, on this manner shall ye speak unto esau, when ye find him.

source_text: "mo ni tukuna talega, 'raica na nomuni tamata o jekope sa muri tiko mai. '" ni sa tukuna mai o koya, "nai solisoli oqo ena vinaka vua ka ni oti oqori au na raici koya e mataqu; de na qai ciqomi au kina. "
target_text: and say ye moreover, behold, thy servant jacob is behind us. for he said, i will appease him with the present that goeth before me, and afterward i will see his face; peradventure he will accept of me.

source_text: sa liu sara vua nai solisoli oqori, ia, o koya e se bogi dua tale ena vanua era cegu tiko kina.
target_text: so went the present over before him: and himself lodged that night in the company.

source_text: sa tucake o jekope ena bogi ka kauti rau na watina, rau na dauveiqaravi kei ira na luvena e tinikadua, ka takosovi japoki.
target_text: and he rose up that night, and took his two wives, and his two womenservants, and his eleven sons, and passed over the ford jabbok.

source_text: sa kauti ira ka vakatalai ira yani ki tai kadua, ka vakauta talega yani na veika sa tu vua.
target_text: and he took them, and sent them over the brook, and sent over that he had.

source_text: sa tiko duadua ga o jekope, sa dua na tamata e rau sa veimulomulo kaya me yacova na kida ni mataka.
target_text: and jacob was left alone; and there wrestled a man with him until the breaking of the day.

source_text: na tamata oqo, ni sa raica ni sa sega ni rawa ni gumatua vei jekope, sa qai boboka na veiuturi ni sema ni sui ni dibina. oqo sa lutu kina nai sema ni dibina ni rau sa veimulomulo tiko.
target_text: and when he saw that he prevailed not against him, he touched the hollow of his thigh; and the hollow of jacob's thigh was out of joint, as he wrestled with him.

source_text: sa tukuna mai na tamata, "laivi au me'u lako, ni sa kida mai na mataka. " sa sauma o jekope, "mo vakalouvinakataki au sara, au sa na qai laivi iko! "
target_text: and he said, let me go, for the day breaketh. and he said, i will not let thee go, except thou bless me.

source_text: sa qai tarogi jekope, "o cei na yacamu? " sa sauma yani, "o jekope. "
target_text: and he said unto him, what is thy name? and he said, jacob.

source_text: "sa na sega tale ni yacamu o jekope, sa na yacamu oqo o isireli (sotia ni kalou), ni o sa sasaga tiko ga vua na kalou kei na tamata talega, ka sa gumatua kina. "
target_text: and he said, thy name shall be called no more jacob, but israel: for as a prince hast thou power with god and with men, and hast prevailed.

source_text: o jekope talega sa tarogi koya ka vaka: "o cei na yacamu? " sa sauma mai, "na cava o taroga kina na yacaqu? " sa qai vakalouvinakataki koya mai kea.
target_text: and jacob asked him, and said, tell me, i pray thee, thy name. and he said, wherefore is it that thou dost ask after my name? and he blessed him there.

source_text: sa vakatoka na yaca ni vanua o ya o penieli, "au sa raica na kalou ena matana votu ka au se bula tiko ga. "
target_text: and jacob called the name of the place peniel: for i have seen god face to face, and my life is preserved.

source_text: ni se takosovi penieli tiko “sa cadra vua na matanisiga ka sa gera na dibina ni lako voli.
target_text: and as he passed over penuel the sun rose upon him, and he halted upon his thigh.

source_text: me yacova mai nikua, o ira na isireli era sa sega ni kania na lewe ni dibi. baleta na kalou sa tara na dibi i jekope, ka sa (mavule) lutu kina na sui ni dibina.
target_text: therefore the children of israel eat not of the sinew which shrank, which is upon the hollow of the thigh, unto this day: because he touched the hollow of jacob's thigh in the sinew that shrank.

source_text: sa rai yani o jekope, ka raica ni sa lako tiko mai o iso vata kei na va na drau na nona tamata. sa wasewasei ira vakatotolo na gone vei ira na dui tinadra.
target_text: and jacob lifted up his eyes, and looked, and, behold, esau came, and with him four hundred men. and he divided the children unto leah, and unto rachel, and unto the two handmaids.

source_text: sa liu oirau na dauveiqaravi kei ira na luvena, tarava yani o lia kei na luvena, ka muri sara o raijeli kei joseva.
target_text: and he put the handmaids and their children foremost, and leah and her children after, and rachel and joseph hindermost.

source_text: sa takoso yani o jekope ka cuva ki na qele vakavitu, me yacova ni sa voleka mai vei iso na tacina.
target_text: and he passed over before them, and bowed himself to the ground seven times, until he came near to his brother.

source_text: ia, o iso sa cici mai ka roqoti koya ka lele yani ki domona ka reguci jekope ka tagi, ni rau sa veitagicaki ena marau.
target_text: and esau ran to meet him, and embraced him, and fell on his neck, and kissed him: and they wept.

source_text: sa rai yani o iso, ka sa raici ira na yalewa kei na dui luvedra ka taroga, "o cei o ira oqo? " sa sauma yani, "o ira na gone oqo era sai solisoli ni loloma ni kalou vua na nomuni tamata. "
target_text: and he lifted up his eyes, and saw the women and the children; and said, who are those with thee? and he said, the children which god hath graciously given thy servant.

source_text: e rau na lako talega mai na dauveiqaravi kei na luvedra ka cuva sobu.
target_text: then the handmaidens came near, they and their children, and they bowed themselves.

source_text: sa lako talega mai o lia kei ira na luvena ka cuva sobu. ni oti oqo sa lako talega mai o joseva, kei raijeli ka cuva talega.
target_text: and leah also with her children came near, and bowed themselves: and after came joseph near and rachel, and they bowed themselves.

source_text: sa taroga mai o iso, "na cava nai balebale ni lawalawa kei oqo keimami sa sota oti? " sa tukuna yani o jekope, "oqori me ra kune loloma kina ena mata ni noqu turaga. "
target_text: and he said, what meanest thou by all this drove which i met? and he said, these are to find grace in the sight of my lord.

source_text: sa tukuna tale o iso, "sa levu tu vei au na veika, taciqu; maroroya kece oqo me nomu ga. "
target_text: and esau said, i have enough, my brother; keep that thou hast unto thyself.

source_text: sa sauma yani o jekope, "e sega, kevaka au sa kune loloma e matamu, mo ciqoma nai solisoli mai na ligaqu “ni'u sa raica na matamu ni sa vaka ga ni'u raica na mata ni kalou, ni o sa vinaka vei au.
target_text: and jacob said, nay, i pray thee, if now i have found grace in thy sight, then receive my present at my hand: for therefore i have seen thy face, as though i had seen the face of god, and thou wast pleased with me.

source_text: "au kerea mo taura na veivakalouvinakataki sa kau mai vei kemuni, baleta na kalou sa levu dina na nona yalololoma vei au, ka sa rui levu tale vei au oqo. " sa uqeti koya tikoga o jekope “sa mani ciqoma o iso.
target_text: take, i pray thee, my blessing that is brought to thee; because god hath dealt graciously with me, and because i have enough. and he urged him, and he took it.

source_text: sa mani tukuna o iso, "mai me daru lako sara, au na liu tiko vei iko. "
target_text: and he said, let us take our journey, and let us go, and i will go before thee.

source_text: sa sauma yani o jekope, "na noqu turaga sa kila ni ra sa malumalumu na gone, era sa malumalumu talega na manumanu, kevaka me ra na toso tale me dua na siga, era na mate kece.
target_text: and he said unto him, my lord knoweth that the children are tender, and the flocks and herds with young are with me: and if men should overdrive them one day, all the flock will die.

source_text: "au kerea, me liu ga yani na noqu turaga, ka me'u na kauti ira ga yani vakamalua na manumanu kei ira na gone ena neimami toso ga, me yacova ni keimami sa yaco yani vua na noqu turaga e sia. "
target_text: let my lord, i pray thee, pass over before his servant: and i will lead on softly, according as the cattle that goeth before me and the children be able to endure, until i come unto my lord unto seir.

source_text: sa tukuna mai o iso, "me'u biuta tiko mai eso na noqu tamata vata kei iko? " sa sauma mai o jekope, "ena dua beka na kedra yaga? me'u kune loloma mai na mata ni noqu turaga. "
target_text: and esau said, let me now leave with thee some of the folk that are with me. and he said, what needeth it? let me find grace in the sight of my lord.

source_text: sa lesu yani o iso ena siga o ya, ena sala ki sia.
target_text: so esau returned that day on his way unto seir.

source_text: sa lako yani o jekope ki sakoca, sa tara e dua na nona vale, kei na vale me nodra na manumanu. sa vakayacani kina na vanua o ya me sakoca.
target_text: and jacob journeyed to succoth, and built him an house, and made booths for his cattle: therefore the name of the place is called succoth.

source_text: sa yaco vinaka mai sikemi o jekope, ena vanua o kenani, ena nona lako mai padanierami; sa vakaduria na nona valelaca ena mata ni koro.
target_text: and jacob came to shalem, a city of shechem, which is in the land of canaan, when he came from padanaram; and pitched his tent before the city.

source_text: sa volia na tiki ni vanua sa mai vakaduria kina na nona vale laca, mai vei ira na luvei emori na tamai sikemi ena rua na drau na dola.
target_text: and he bought a parcel of a field, where he had spread his tent, at the hand of the children of hamor, shechem's father, for an hundred pieces of money.

source_text: sa tara mai kea e dua nai cabocabo ni soro, ka vakatoka me ilai-eloe isireli.
target_text: and he erected there an altar, and called it eleloheisrael.

source_text: o taina na luvei lia, o koya sa vakasucuma vei jekope “sa lako yani me vakaraici ira na goneyalewa ni vanua.
target_text: and dinah the daughter of leah, which she bare unto jacob, went out to see the daughters of the land.

source_text: ni sa raici koya o sikemi, na ravouvou ni vanua o ivaiti, na luvei emori, sa kauti koya, ka moceri koya, ka vakacacani koya.
target_text: and when shechem the son of hamor the hivite, prince of the country, saw her, he took her, and lay with her, and defiled her.

source_text: na yalona sa kabiti taina na luvei jekope, sa domoni taina ka sa vosa vinaka vua.
target_text: and his soul clave unto dinah the daughter of jacob, and he loved the damsel, and spake kindly unto the damsel.

source_text: sa vosa vei emori na tamana o sikemi ka vaka, "mo kauta mai na goneyalewa oqo me watiqu. "
target_text: and shechem spake unto his father hamor, saying, get me this damsel to wife.

source_text: sa rogoca o jekope ni sa vakacacani taina na luvena yalewa o sikemi. o ira na luvena tagane era se tu mai na buca vata kei ira na manumanu. sa tiko ga vakamalua o jekope me yacova ni ra sa lesu mai.
target_text: and jacob heard that he had defiled dinah his daughter: now his sons were with his cattle in the field: and jacob held his peace until they were come.

source_text: sa lako yani o emori na tamai sikemi vei jekope me rau veivosaki.
target_text: and hamor the father of shechem went out unto jacob to commune with him.

source_text: era sa lesu mai na luvei jekope tagane mai vanua ka rogoca na ka sa yaco, era sa rarawa sara vakalevu “baleta ni sa cakava na tamata oqo e dua nai valavala toro sobu sara e isireli. ni sa mocera na luvei jekope, e dua na ka e sega ni dodonu me yaco.
target_text: and the sons of jacob came out of the field when they heard it: and the men were grieved, and they were very wroth, because he had wrought folly in israel in lying with jacob's daughter; which thing ought not to be done.

source_text: sa vosa vei ira o emori ka vaka: "na yalo i sikemi na luvequ, sa rui kabita dina na luvemudou yalewa. au kerea mo dou soli koya me watina.
target_text: and hamor communed with them, saying, the soul of my son shechem longeth for your daughter: i pray you give her him to wife.

source_text: "me da veimusumusuki, ni taura na neimami goneyalewa, ka me keimami taura na nomuni goneyalewa.
target_text: and make ye marriages with us, and give your daughters unto us, and take our daughters unto you.

source_text: "mo ni tiko vata kei keimami, sa tu oqori na vanua. mo ni tiko kina ka veivoli kina, ka mo ni taura ga na veika o ni vinakata mai kina. "
target_text: and ye shall dwell with us: and the land shall be before you; dwell and trade ye therein, and get you possessions therein.

source_text: o sikemi sa tukuna vei jekope kei iratou na ganena, "me'u kune loloma mada mai vei kemudou “na veika ga dou sa vinakata, au na solia vei kemudou.
target_text: and shechem said unto her father and unto her brethren, let me find grace in your eyes, and what ye shall say unto me i will give.

source_text: "dou tukuna vei au na cava ga me kena i vakamalua, au na solia vei kemudou. me soli ga na goneyalewa oqo me watiqu. "
target_text: ask me never so much dowry and gift, and i will give according as ye shall say unto me: but give me the damsel to wife.

source_text: o iratou na luvei jekope e ratou sa sauma vei sikemi kei emori na tamana, ka vosa vakaukauwa sara baleta ni sa vakacacani na ganedratou o taina.
target_text: and the sons of jacob answered shechem and hamor his father deceitfully, and said, because he had defiled dinah their sister:

source_text: e ratou sa tukuna vei rau, "sa sega ni rawa oqo, me soli na neimami yalewa vei ira na sega ni cili, ni oqori sa dua nai valavala ca levu vei keimami.
target_text: and they said unto them, we cannot do this thing, to give our sister to one that is uncircumcised; for that were a reproach unto us:

source_text: "ena ka ga oqo, keimami na yalovinaka kina: o ya mo ni vakataki keimami “na nomuni tagane kece me ra cilivi,
target_text: but in this will we consent unto you: if ye will be as we be, that every male of you be circumcised;

source_text: "oqori ga keimami na soli ira kina na neimami goneyalewa vei kemuni, ka keimami na tauri ira kina na nomuni goneyalewa, keimami na tiko kina vata kei kemuni, eda na dua ga kina na tamata.
target_text: then will we give our daughters unto you, and we will take your daughters to us, and we will dwell with you, and we will become one people.

source_text: "kevaka o ni sa sega ni rogoca na vosa mo ni cilivi kina, keimami na kauta na luvei keimami goneyalewa ka lako. "
target_text: but if ye will not hearken unto us, to be circumcised; then will we take our daughter, and we will be gone.

source_text: na vosa oqo sa vinaka vei emori kei sikemi na luvena.
target_text: and their words pleased hamor, and shechem hamor's son.

source_text: o sikemi sa sega ni berabera tale ni cakava na ka sa tukuni vua, baleta ni sa rui domona dina na luvei jekope goneyalewa. o sikemi sa tamata dokai sara ena vale nei tamana.
target_text: and the young man deferred not to do the thing, because he had delight in jacob's daughter: and he was more honourable than all the house of his father.

source_text: o emori kei sikemi na luvena tagane, e rau sa lako mai ki na matamata ni koro ka vosa vei ira na tagane kecega ka tukuna:
target_text: and hamor and shechem his son came unto the gate of their city, and communed with the men of their city, saying,

source_text: "o ira na tamata oqo era sa duavata kei keda me ra tiko ena noda vanua ka veivoli kina. ni sa veiraurau na vanua vei ira me da tauri ira na luvedra yalewa me watida ka soli ira na luveda yalewa me watidra.
target_text: these men are peaceable with us; therefore let them dwell in the land, and trade therein; for the land, behold, it is large enough for them; let us take their daughters to us for wives, and let us give them our daughters.

source_text: "e dua ga na ka, era vinakata me ra tiko kina vata kei keda, ka meda dua ga na tamata, o ya me da cilivi me vaka era sa cilivi.
target_text: only herein will the men consent unto us for to dwell with us, to be one people, if every male among us be circumcised, as they are circumcised.

source_text: "e na sega beka ni noda na nodra manumanu kei na veika era taukena, na ka e nodra ena noda? me da vaka io ga vei ira, ka era na tiko vata kei keda. "
target_text: shall not their cattle and their substance and every beast of theirs be ours? only let us consent unto them, and they will dwell with us.

source_text: o ira kece sa lako yani ki na matamata, sa vaka io vei emori kei sikemi na luvena. era sa cilivi kece na tagane mai na koro.
target_text: and unto hamor and unto shechem his son hearkened all that went out of the gate of his city; and every male was circumcised, all that went out of the gate of his city.

source_text: sa yaco ni sa oti e tolu na siga “ni se tarai ira tiko na mosi-vuvuca ni veicili, o simione kei livai na luvei jekope, o irau na ganei taina “era sa taura na nodrau i seleiwau ka lako vakadoudou ki na koro ka vakamatei ira kecega na tagane.
target_text: and it came to pass on the third day, when they were sore, that two of the sons of jacob, simeon and levi, dinah's brethren, took each man his sword, and came upon the city boldly, and slew all the males.

source_text: e rau sa vakamatei emori kei sikemi talega e nai seleiwau ka vakacacana na koro ka kauti taina tani mai na vale nei sikemi ka lako tani.
target_text: and they slew hamor and shechem his son with the edge of the sword, and took dinah out of shechem's house, and went out.

source_text: era sa curuma yani na koro, o ira na luvei jekope ka raica na veivakamatei, baleta na veivakacacani sa caka vei taina.
target_text: the sons of jacob came upon the slain, and spoiled the city, because they had defiled their sister.

source_text: era sa kauta na sipi, na bulumakau, na nodra asa “na veika sa tiko ena koro kei na veika sa tu mai vanua,
target_text: they took their sheep, and their oxen, and their asses, and that which was in the city, and that which was in the field,

source_text: kei na nodra i yau kecega, o ira na gone kei tinadra era sa kau vakavesu. era sa vakacacana ka kauta kece na ka sa tiko e vale.
target_text: and all their wealth, and all their little ones, and their wives took they captive, and spoiled even all that was in the house.

source_text: sa tukuna o jekope vei simione kei livai, "drau sa vakaleqai au, ena nomudrau vakaboicataki au ena kedra maliwa na lewenivanua oqo, ena kedra maliwa na kai kenani, kei na perisaiti, ni'u sa lewe vica ga, era na vakasoqoni vata mai ka vakamatei au. au na vakarusai kei na noqu vuvale. "
target_text: and jacob said to simeon and levi, ye have troubled me to make me to stink among the inhabitants of the land, among the canaanites and the perizzites: and i being few in number, they shall gather themselves together against me, and slay me; and i shall be destroyed, i and my house.

source_text: e rau sa sauma mai na cauravou, "me vakatautauvatataka na tamata oqo na ganei keirau me vaka na yalewa dauvolitaki koya? "
target_text: and they said, should he deal with our sister as with an harlot?

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna vei jekope, "mo tucake ka lako ki peceli ka la'ki tiko kina; mo cakava mai kea e dua nai cabocabo ni soro vei jiova “o koya e a basika mai vei iko, ena nomu a dro tiko mai vei iso na tacimu. "
target_text: and god said unto jacob, arise, go up to bethel, and dwell there: and make there an altar unto god, that appeared unto thee when thou fleddest from the face of esau thy brother.

source_text: o jekope sa tukuna ki na nona vuvale kei ira kece sa tiko vua, "me biu na kalou tani sa tiko vei kemuni, ni vakasavasavataki kemuni, ka veisautaka na nomuni i sulu.
target_text: then jacob said unto his household, and to all that were with him, put away the strange gods that are among you, and be clean, and change your garments:

source_text: "ka me da sa tucake ka lako ki peceli; au na cakava mai kea e dua nai cabocabo ni soro vei jiova, o koya sa dau vakacegui au ena gauna ni veilecayaki, ka sa tiko vata kei au ena sala au lakova. "
target_text: and let us arise, and go up to bethel; and i will make there an altar unto god, who answered me in the day of my distress, and was with me in the way which i went.

source_text: era sa solia vei jekope na veikalou tani, kei na kena sau ni daliga “o jekope sa vunitaka ena ruku ni veikau e sikemi.
target_text: and they gave unto jacob all the strange gods which were in their hand, and all their earrings which were in their ears; and jacob hid them under the oak which was by shechem.

source_text: era sa lako yani, ka sa kani ira na rere na veimatanitu vakavolivoliti ira, ka era sa sega kina ni via veivala kei ira na luvei jekope.
target_text: and they journeyed: and the terror of god was upon the cities that were round about them, and they did not pursue after the sons of jacob.

source_text: sa lako mai o jekope ki lusi (oqori o peceli) ena vanua o kenani, o koya kei ira na tamata sa tiko vata kei koya.
target_text: so jacob came to luz, which is in the land of canaan, that is, bethel, he and all the people that were with him.

source_text: sa tara mai kea e dua na i cabocabo ni soro ka vakatoka me eli-peceli, baleta mai kea sa basika kina vua na kalou ena nona dro mai vei iso na tacina.
target_text: and he built there an altar, and called the place elbethel: because there god appeared unto him, when he fled from the face of his brother.

source_text: sa mate o tepora na dauveiqaravi nei rapeka, ka sa buluti mai peceli ena ruku ni vunikau, ena tikina e ra. sa vakayacani na vanua o ya o alonibakuci.
target_text: but deborah rebekah's nurse died, and she was buried beneath bethel under an oak: and the name of it was called allonbachuth.

source_text: sa basika tale na kalou vei jekope ena nona lako mai padani-erami ka vakalouvinakataki koya.
target_text: and god appeared unto jacob again, when he came out of padanaram, and blessed him.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna vua, "na yacamu o jekope “o sa na sega tale ni jekope, o isireli sa na yacamu mai ni kua. " na kalou sa kaciva na yacana me isireli.
target_text: and god said unto him, thy name is jacob: thy name shall not be called any more jacob, but israel shall be thy name: and he called his name israel.

source_text: na kalou sa tukuna vua, "oi au na kalou qaqa, mo vuavuai ka lewe levu mai, na matanitu kei na veimatanitu era na lako mai vei iko, na veitui era na lako mai yagomu.
target_text: and god said unto him, i am god almighty: be fruitful and multiply; a nation and a company of nations shall be of thee, and kings shall come out of thy loins;

source_text: "na vanua au sa solia vei eparaama kei aisake, au sa solia vei iko kei ira na nomu kawa, au sa solia kina na vanua. "
target_text: and the land which i gave abraham and isaac, to thee i will give it, and to thy seed after thee will i give the land.

source_text: na kalou sa lako cake mai vua, ena vanua sa vosa kina vua.
target_text: and god went up from him in the place where he talked with him.

source_text: sa vakaduria o jekope e dua na duru ena vanua sa vosa kina vua na kalou, na duru vatu; sa sova kina e dua nai soro liviraki sa sova/lumuta talega kina na waiwai.
target_text: and jacob set up a pillar in the place where he talked with him, even a pillar of stone: and he poured a drink offering thereon, and he poured oil thereon.

source_text: sa vakayacana o jekope na vanua sa vosa kina vua na kalou, me o peceli.
target_text: and jacob called the name of the place where god spake with him, bethel.

source_text: era sa lako tani mai peceli, ka se vo vakalailai me yaco ki efiraca, sa taratara o raijeli ka sa kaukauwa sara.
target_text: and they journeyed from bethel; and there was but a little way to come to ephrath: and rachel travailed, and she had hard labour.

source_text: ni sa kaukauwa sara na nona taratara ni vakasucu, sa tukuna vua na nona nasi, "kua ni rere, ena lako mai na gone tagane oqo. "
target_text: and it came to pass, when she was in hard labour, that the midwife said unto her, fear not; thou shalt have this son also.

source_text: sa yaco, ni sa lako tani tiko vua na yalona (sa mate), sa vakayacani koya me peni-oni, ia, o tamana sa vakayacana me penijamini.
target_text: and it came to pass, as her soul was in departing, (for she died) that she called his name benoni: but his father called him benjamin.

source_text: sa mate o raijieli, ka sa bulu ni ra sa lako tiko ki efiraca (oqori o peceliema).
target_text: and rachel died, and was buried in the way to ephrath, which is bethlehem.

source_text: sa vakaduria e dua na duru o jekope ena kena i bulubulu me yacova na siga oqo.
target_text: and jacob set a pillar upon her grave: that is the pillar of rachel's grave unto this day.

source_text: sa lako tiko o isireli, ka biria na nona vale-laca ni sivia na vanua ni yadra e eola.
target_text: and israel journeyed, and spread his tent beyond the tower of edar.

source_text: sa yaco, ni sa tiko ena vanua o isireli, o rupeni sa moceri bila na (dauveiqaravi) nei raijeli, sa rogoca o isireli na ka oqo. na luvei jekope tagane e tinikarua:
target_text: and it came to pass, when israel dwelt in that land, that reuben went and lay with bilhah his father's concubine: and israel heard it. now the sons of jacob were twelve:

source_text: na luvei lia tagane o rupeni na ulumatua, o simione, o livai, o juta, o isakari kei sevuloni;
target_text: the sons of leah; reuben, jacob's firstborn, and simeon, and levi, and judah, and issachar, and zebulun:

source_text: na luvei raijeli tagane o: joseva kei penijamini;
target_text: the sons of rachel; joseph, and benjamin:

source_text: na luvei bila tagane, (na dauveiqaravi) nei raijeli; o tani kei navitalai;
target_text: and the sons of bilhah, rachel's handmaid; dan, and naphtali:

source_text: na luvei sipa tagane, (na dauveiqaravi) nei lia; o kata kei aseri. oqo, o ira na luvei jekope tagane era sa vakasucumi vua e padani-erami.
target_text: and the sons of zilpah, leah's handmaid; gad, and asher: these are the sons of jacob, which were born to him in padanaram.

source_text: sa lako mai o jekope vei tamana o aisake e mamire kirijaci araba (oqori o epironi), na vanua e rau mai tiko kina o eparaama kei aisake.
target_text: and jacob came unto isaac his father unto mamre, unto the city of arbah, which is hebron, where abraham and isaac sojourned.

source_text: na yabaki nei aisake e dua na drau ka mani walusagavulu na yabaki.
target_text: and the days of isaac were an hundred and fourscore years.

source_text: sa ceguva nai otioti ni nona i cegu o aisake, ka sa mate, sa lako yani vei ira na wekana ni sa qase sara ka sa levu na nona veisiga vinaka. e rau sa buluti koya na nona cauravou, o iso kei jekope.
target_text: and isaac gave up the ghost, and died, and was gathered unto his people, being old and full of days: and his sons esau and jacob buried him.

source_text: oqo nai vola ni kawa nei iso, sa vakayacani talega me o itomi.
target_text: now these are the generations of esau, who is edom.

source_text: o iso sa taura na watina mai vei ira na goneyalewa ni kenani: o ada na luvei eloni na itaiti; o aolibama na luvei ana, na luvei sibioni na iraiti;
target_text: esau took his wives of the daughters of canaan; adah the daughter of elon the hittite, and aholibamah the daughter of anah the daughter of zibeon the hivite;

source_text: kei vasemaca, na luvei isimeli, na ganei nebajoci.
target_text: and bashemath ishmael's daughter, sister of nebajoth.

source_text: o ada sa vakasucumi elifasi vei iso kei vasemaca sa vakasucumi rueli.
target_text: and adah bare to esau eliphaz; and bashemath bare reuel;

source_text: o aolibama sa vakasucumi jeusi, jaelami, kei kora. sai ira oqori na luvei iso, sa vakasucumi vua ena vanua o kenani.
target_text: and aholibamah bare jeush, and jaalam, and korah: these are the sons of esau, which were born unto him in the land of canaan.

source_text: o iso sa kauti ira na watina, ira na luvena kei ira kece ena nona vuvale, na nona bulumakau kei na nona manumanu kece kei na nona veika kece sa rawata mai na vanua o kenani. ka sa lako ki na vanua vakayawa sara mai na matai tacina o jekope.
