target_text: and esau took his wives, and his sons, and his daughters, and all the persons of his house, and his cattle, and all his beasts, and all his substance, which he had got in the land of canaan; and went into the country from the face of his brother jacob.

source_text: sa ka levu sara na nodrau dui-yau, sa na dredre kina me rau na tiko vata, kei na vanua e rau tiko vulagi kina, sa dredre me tokoni rau, baleta na levu ni nodrau manumanu.
target_text: for their riches were more than that they might dwell together; and the land wherein they were strangers could not bear them because of their cattle.

source_text: o iso, sa tiko ena ulunivanua o sia. o iso, sai itomi.
target_text: thus dwelt esau in mount seir: esau is edom.

source_text: oqo na kawa nei iso na tamadra na itomi ena ulunivanua o sia.
target_text: and these are the generations of esau the father of the edomites in mount seir:

source_text: oqo na yacadra na luvei iso; o elifasi na luvei ada na wati iso kei rueli na luvei vasemaca na wati iso.
target_text: these are the names of esau's sons; eliphaz the son of adah the wife of esau, reuel the son of bashemath the wife of esau.

source_text: o ira na luvei elifasi o temana, o omari, o sefo, o qatama kei kenasi.
target_text: and the sons of eliphaz were teman, omar, zepho, and gatam, and kenaz.

source_text: o timina na wati elifasi lailai sa vakasucumi amaleki vei elifasi. sai ira oqo na luvei ada na wati iso.
target_text: and timna was concubine to eliphaz esau's son; and she bare to eliphaz amalek: these were the sons of adah esau's wife.

source_text: sai ira oqo na luvei rueli; o naaci, o sera, o sama kei misa. oqo o ira na luvei vasemaca na wati iso.
target_text: and these are the sons of reuel; nahath, and zerah, shammah, and mizzah: these were the sons of bashemath esau's wife.

source_text: sai ira oqo na luvei aolibama, na wati iso na luvei ana yalewa, na luvei sibione yalewa. sa vakasucuma vei iso, o jeusi, o jaelami kei kora.
target_text: and these were the sons of aholibamah, the daughter of anah the daughter of zibeon, esau's wife: and she bare to esau jeush, and jaalam, and korah.

source_text: sai ira oqo na vei turaga vei ira na luvei iso. o ira na luvei elifasi na ulumatua nei iso, o temami na turaga, o oma na turaga, o sefo na turaga, o kenasi na turaga,
target_text: these were dukes of the sons of esau: the sons of eliphaz the firstborn son of esau; duke teman, duke omar, duke zepho, duke kenaz,

source_text: o kora na turaga, o qatama na turaga, o ameleki na turaga. sai ira oqo na vei turaga nei elifasi ena vanua o itomi. oqo o ira na luvei ada.
target_text: duke korah, duke gatam, and duke amalek: these are the dukes that came of eliphaz in the land of edom; these were the sons of adah.

source_text: sai ira oqo na luvei rueli na luvei iso. o naaci na turaga, o sera na turaga, o sama na turaga kei misa na turaga. sai ira oqo na veituraga nei rueli ena vanua o itomi. oqo o ira na luvei vasemaca na wati iso.
target_text: and these are the sons of reuel esau's son; duke nahath, duke zerah, duke shammah, duke mizzah: these are the dukes that came of reuel in the land of edom; these are the sons of bashemath esau's wife.

source_text: sai ira oqo na luvei aolibama, na wati iso. o jeusi na turaga, o jaelami na turaga kei kora na turaga. sai ira oqo na vei turaga era sa lako mai vei aolibama na wati iso, na luvei ana.
target_text: and these are the sons of aholibamah esau's wife; duke jeush, duke jaalam, duke korah: these were the dukes that came of aholibamah the daughter of anah, esau's wife.

source_text: sai ira oqo na luvei iso, (itomi); oqori o ira na kena vei turaga.
target_text: these are the sons of esau, who is edom, and these are their dukes.

source_text: o ira oqo na luvei sia na oraite, o ira sa tawana tiko na vanua: o lotani, o sobali, o sibione, kei ana,
target_text: these are the sons of seir the horite, who inhabited the land; lotan, and shobal, and zibeon, and anah,

source_text: o disioni, o esari, kei disani. sai ira oqori na turaga nodra na oraite, o ira na luvei sia ena vanua o itomi.
target_text: and dishon, and ezer, and dishan: these are the dukes of the horites, the children of seir in the land of edom.

source_text: o ira na luvei lotani, o ori kei emami, na ganei lotani o timina.
target_text: and the children of lotan were hori and hemam; and lotan's sister was timna.

source_text: sai ira oqo na luvei sobali: o elirani, o manaeci, o ibali, o sefo, kei onami.
target_text: and the children of shobal were these; alvan, and manahath, and ebal, shepho, and onam.

source_text: sai ira oqo na luvei sibione, o rau o aja kei anae. o anae oqo sa kunea na wai ena vanua liwa, ni a lako voli kina ka vakania tiko na asa nei tamana o sibione.
target_text: and these are the children of zibeon; both ajah, and anah: this was that anah that found the mules in the wilderness, as he fed the asses of zibeon his father.

source_text: sai ira oqo na luvei anae: o disioni kei aolibama na luvei anae yalewa.
target_text: and the children of anah were these; dishon, and aholibamah the daughter of anah.

source_text: sai ira oqo na luvei disioni; o amedani, o esibana, o icarani, kei jerani.
target_text: and these are the children of dishon; hemdan, and eshban, and ithran, and cheran.

source_text: sai ira oqo na luvei esari, biliani, o saerani, kei akani.
target_text: the children of ezer are these; bilhan, and zaavan, and akan.

source_text: sai ira oqo na luvei disani, o usi kei erani.
target_text: the children of dishan are these; uz, and aran.

source_text: sai ira oqo na veituraga e oraite: o lotani na turaga, o sobali na turaga, o sibione na turaga, o anae na turaga,
target_text: these are the dukes that came of the horites; duke lotan, duke shobal, duke zibeon, duke anah,

source_text: o disioni na turaga, o esari na turaga, o disani na turaga, o ira oqo na veituraga vei ira na oraite, me vaka na nodra dui turaga ena vanua o sia.
target_text: duke dishon, duke ezer, duke dishan: these are the dukes that came of hori, among their dukes in the land of seir.

source_text: sai ira oqo na veitui sa lewa e itomi, ni se bera na tui vei ira na isireli:
target_text: and these are the kings that reigned in the land of edom, before there reigned any king over the children of israel.

source_text: o bela na luvei peori, sa lewa e itomi, na yaca ni nona koro o diniaba.
target_text: and bela the son of beor reigned in edom: and the name of his city was dinhabah.

source_text: ni sa mate o bela, o jobaba na luvei sera e bosara sa veiliutaki ena vukuna.
target_text: and bela died, and jobab the son of zerah of bozrah reigned in his stead.

source_text: ni sa mate o jobaba, o usaemi ena vanua noda na temanaiti sa lewa ena vukui jobaba.
target_text: and jobab died, and husham of the land of temani reigned in his stead.

source_text: ni sa mate o usaemi, o etati na luvei betati, o koya sa kabai mitiani ena buca mai moape, sa lewa ena vukuna. na yaca ni koro o avici.
target_text: and husham died, and hadad the son of bedad, who smote midian in the field of moab, reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was avith.

source_text: ni sa mate o etati, o samila mai masareka sa lewa ena vukui etati.
target_text: and hadad died, and samlah of masrekah reigned in his stead.

source_text: ni sa mate o samila, o saula mai reopoci ena bati ni uciwai, sa lewa ena vukuna.
target_text: and samlah died, and saul of rehoboth by the river reigned in his stead.

source_text: ni sa mate o saula, o peali-anana na luvei akebori sa lewa ena vukuna.
target_text: and saul died, and baalhanan the son of achbor reigned in his stead.

source_text: ni sa mate o peali-anana na luvei akebori o adari sa lewa ena vukuna; na yaca ni nona koro o pau. na yaca i watina o maetabeli na luvei matereti, na luvei maseabi yalewa.
target_text: and baalhanan the son of achbor died, and hadar reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was pau; and his wife's name was mehetabel, the daughter of matred, the daughter of mezahab.

source_text: sai ira oqo na veituraga nei iso, me vaka na nodra veivuvale ena nodra i tikotiko, na yacadra yadudua oqo: o timana na turaga, o alava na turaga, o jeteci na turaga,
target_text: and these are the names of the dukes that came of esau, according to their families, after their places, by their names; duke timnah, duke alvah, duke jetheth,

source_text: o aolibama na turaga, o ela na turaga, o pinoni na turaga,
target_text: duke aholibamah, duke elah, duke pinon,

source_text: o kenasi na turaga, o temana na turaga o mibisa na turaga,
target_text: duke kenaz, duke teman, duke mibzar,

source_text: o meqedeeli na turaga kei irami na turaga. sai ira oqo na veituraga e itomi me vaka na nodra dui tikotiko ena vanua era sa taukena. o iso sa tamadra na kai itomi.
target_text: duke magdiel, duke iram: these be the dukes of edom, according to their habitations in the land of their possession: he is esau the father of the edomites.

source_text: o jekope sa tiko ena vanua sa vulagi kina o tamana, ena vanua o kenani.
target_text: and jacob dwelt in the land wherein his father was a stranger, in the land of canaan.

source_text: oqo na kawa i jekope. o joseva ni se qai yabaki tinikavitu, sa vaka na manumanu tiko vata kei ira na tacina. o koya sa tiko kei ira na luvei bila kei ira na luvei siliva na wati tamana. o joseva sa kauta na kedratou i tukutuku ca vei tamana.
target_text: these are the generations of jacob. joseph, being seventeen years old, was feeding the flock with his brethren; and the lad was with the sons of bilhah, and with the sons of zilpah, his father's wives: and joseph brought unto his father their evil report.

source_text: o isireli, sa lomani joseva vakalevu cake mai vei ira kece na luvena, baleta ni o koya e luvena ni sa qase sara. sa dau cula talega na nona kote balavu ka dui rokaroka.
target_text: now israel loved joseph more than all his children, because he was the son of his old age: and he made him a coat of many colours.

source_text: ni ratou sa dau raica na tacina ni sa daulomani koya vakalevu o isireli mai vei iratou, e ratou sa dau cati koya ka dauvosa vakaca vua.
target_text: and when his brethren saw that their father loved him more than all his brethren, they hated him, and could not speak peaceably unto him.

source_text: o joseva sa tadra e dua na tadra, ka tukuna sara vei ira na tacina; e ratou sa qai cati koya ga vakalevu.
target_text: and joseph dreamed a dream, and he told it his brethren: and they hated him yet the more.

source_text: sa tukuna vei iratou na tacina, "au kerea mo dou rogoca na noqu tadra:
target_text: and he said unto them, hear, i pray you, this dream which i have dreamed:

source_text: "edatou sa vau sila tiko ena were, sa duri ka tucake tu na noqui vau sila; na nomudou i vau sila talega sa tucake ka cuva kina noqu i vau sila. "
target_text: for, behold, we were binding sheaves in the field, and, lo, my sheaf arose, and also stood upright; and, behold, your sheaves stood round about, and made obeisance to my sheaf.

source_text: e ratou sa tukuna vua na tacina, "o iko, mo na mai liutaki keitou? se o mai via vakatulewa vei keitou? " e ratou sa qai cati koya ga vakalevu baleta na nona tadra kei na nona vosa.
target_text: and his brethren said to him, shalt thou indeed reign over us? or shalt thou indeed have dominion over us? and they hated him yet the more for his dreams, and for his words.

source_text: e se baci tadra tale e dua na tadra, ka tukuna vei ira na tacina ka vaka: "au sa baci tadra tale, ka sa vaka oqo, na siga, na vula kei na veikalokalo era sa cuva kece vei au. "
target_text: and he dreamed yet another dream, and told it his brethren, and said, behold, i have dreamed a dream more; and, behold, the sun and the moon and the eleven stars made obeisance to me.

source_text: sa tukuna vei tamana kei ira na tacina, sa vunauci koya o tamana ka tukuna vua, "e tadra vakacava oqo? me lako beka mai o tinamu, o tamamu kei ira na tacimu ka mai cuva ki na qele e matamu? "
target_text: and he told it to his father, and to his brethren: and his father rebuked him, and said unto him, what is this dream that thou hast dreamed? shall i and thy mother and thy brethren indeed come to bow down ourselves to thee to the earth?

source_text: era sa qai vuvutaki koya ga na tacina, ia, o tamana sa taura vuni tikoga ki yalona.
target_text: and his brethren envied him; but his father observed the saying.

source_text: era sa lako ki sikemi na tacina me ra vakania na sipi nei tamadra.
target_text: and his brethren went to feed their father's flock in shechem.

source_text: sa tukuna o isireli vei joseva, "era sa sega beka ni tiko mai sikemi na tacimu? lako mai me'u talai iko vei ira. sa sauma mai o joseva, "sai au oqo. "
target_text: and israel said unto joseph, do not thy brethren feed the flock in shechem? come, and i will send thee unto them. and he said to him, here am i.

source_text: sa tukuna sara vua, "lako ka raica se sa vakatiko e vei o ira na tacimu kei ira na manumanu, ka kauta lesu mai vei au na i tukutuku. " sa vakatalai koya tani yani mai na buca o epironi ka sa lako sara yani ki sikemi.
target_text: and he said to him, go, i pray thee, see whether it be well with thy brethren, and well with the flocks; and bring me word again. so he sent him out of the vale of hebron, and he came to shechem.

source_text: e dua na tamata sa kunei koya, ni sa veilakoyaki voli ena vanua. sa tarogi koya na tamata, "na cava o sa vakasaqara tiko? "
target_text: and a certain man found him, and, behold, he was wandering in the field: and the man asked him, saying, what seekest thou?

source_text: sa sauma yani, "au vakaraici iratou tiko na tuakaqu, era sa vakana manumanu tiko e vei. "
target_text: and he said, i seek my brethren: tell me, i pray thee, where they feed their flocks.

source_text: sa tukuna mai na tamata, "era sa lako tani eke, ia, au sa rogoci ira ga ni ra sa tukuna, 'tou lako ki tocani. '" a sa lako yani o joseva ka kunei iratou na tuakana e tocani.
target_text: and the man said, they are departed hence; for i heard them say, let us go to dothan. and joseph went after his brethren, and found them in dothan.

source_text: ni ra sa raici koya tiko mai vakayawa, era sa bosea me vakamatei koya.
target_text: and when they saw him afar off, even before he came near unto them, they conspired against him to slay him.

source_text: era sa veitukuniyaka, "raica sa lako tiko mai oqo na dautadra!
target_text: and they said one to another, behold, this dreamer cometh.

source_text: "mai, me da sa na vakamatei koya ka viritaki koya ki na dua na qara, me noda i ulubale, 'me dua na manumanu kila sa vakamatei koya, ' eda na qai raica se sa vakacava na nona tadra! "
target_text: come now therefore, and let us slay him, and cast him into some pit, and we will say, some evil beast hath devoured him: and we shall see what will become of his dreams.

source_text: ia, ni sa rogoca o rupeni, sa vakabulai koya mai na ligadra ka tukuna, "me da kua ni vakamatei koya. "
target_text: and reuben heard it, and he delivered him out of their hands; and said, let us not kill him.

source_text: sa tukuna vei ira o rupeni, "me kua ni vakadavei na dra, me viritaki ga ki na qara sa tiko mai na vanua liwa, me kua ga ni da tarai koya ena ligada" “ni sa nakita me vakabulai joseva mai vei ira na tacina ka kauti koya lesu vei tamadra.
target_text: and reuben said unto them, shed no blood, but cast him into this pit that is in the wilderness, and lay no hand upon him; that he might rid him out of their hands, to deliver him to his father again.

source_text: ni sa qai yaco mai vei ira o joseva, era sa basuraka na nona kote, na kote dui rokaroka sa dara tiko.
target_text: and it came to pass, when joseph was come unto his brethren, that they stript joseph out of his coat, his coat of many colours that was on him;

source_text: era sa tauri koya ka viritaki koya ki na qara. sa lala tu na qara, ni sa maca tu na kena wai.
target_text: and they took him, and cast him into a pit: and the pit was empty, there was no water in it.

source_text: era sa dabe sobu ka kana. ni ra sa rai yani, era sa lako tiko mai e dua nai lawalawa era luvei isimeli, era lako tiko mai kiliati kei na nodra kameli, kei na nodra i usausa ni voliciri ena nodra lako sobu tiko ki ijipita.
target_text: and they sat down to eat bread: and they lifted up their eyes and looked, and, behold, a company of ishmeelites came from gilead with their camels bearing spicery and balm and myrrh, going to carry it down to egypt.

source_text: sa tukuna o juta vei ira na tacina, "na cava na kena yaga, kevaka e da na vakamatei koya ka vunitaka na nona dra?
target_text: and judah said unto his brethren, what profit is it if we slay our brother, and conceal his blood?

source_text: "me da volitaki koya vei ira na isimeli, me kua ni tarai koya kina na ligada, ni o koya e tacida ka eda lewe vata. " era sa rogoca na tacina na veika oqo.
target_text: come, and let us sell him to the ishmeelites, and let not our hand be upon him; for he is our brother and our flesh. and his brethren were content.

source_text: era sa lako tale mai na kai mitiani dauveivoli, era sa tauri joseva mai ka volitaki koya yani vei ira na isimeli me ruasagavulu na sikele siliva. era sa kauti joseva ki ijipita.
target_text: then there passed by midianites merchantmen; and they drew and lifted up joseph out of the pit, and sold joseph to the ishmeelites for twenty pieces of silver: and they brought joseph into egypt.

source_text: sa lesu yani o rupeni ki na qara, ka sa yali kina o joseva, sa basuraka na nona i sulu.
target_text: and reuben returned unto the pit; and, behold, joseph was not in the pit; and he rent his clothes.

source_text: sa lesu yani vei iratou na tacina ka tukuna, "sa yali na gone, me'u lako beka i vei? "
target_text: and he returned unto his brethren, and said, the child is not; and i, whither shall i go?

source_text: era sa taura na kote i joseva, ka vakamatea e dua na me, sa qai toni na kote ena kena dra.
target_text: and they took joseph's coat, and killed a kid of the goats, and dipped the coat in the blood;

source_text: era sa vakauta mai na kote vei tamadra ka tukuna, "keimami sa kunea oqo, mo raica oqo, e nei luvemu se sega? "
target_text: and they sent the coat of many colours, and they brought it to their father; and said, this have we found: know now whether it be thy son's coat or no.

source_text: sa kila o jekope ka tukuna, "oqo na kote nei luvequ, e dua na manumanu kila sa kani koya, sa sega ni cala, o joseva sa basuki vakalalai. "
target_text: and he knew it, and said, it is my son's coat; an evil beast hath devoured him; joseph is without doubt rent in pieces.

source_text: sa basuraka na nona i sulu o jekope ka vakaisulu taga na tolona ka lolokutaki joseva me vica vata na siga.
target_text: and jacob rent his clothes, and put sackcloth upon his loins, and mourned for his son many days.

source_text: o ira kece na luvena era sa mai vakacegui koya, sa tukuna o jekope, "au na lako sobu ki nai bulubulu vei luvequ ena vakaloloku. " sa tagi o jekope ena vukuna.
target_text: and all his sons and all his daughters rose up to comfort him; but he refused to be comforted; and he said, for i will go down into the grave unto my son mourning. thus his father wept for him.

source_text: o ira na mitiani era sa volitaki joseva sara ki ijipita vei potifa na vakai lesilesi i fero ka sa nodra i liuliu na mata yadra.
target_text: and the midianites sold him into egypt unto potiphar, an officer of pharaoh's, and captain of the guard.

source_text: sa yaco ena dua na gauna sa lako tani mai kina o juta mai vei ira na tacina, sa sikova yani e dua mai etulama na yacana o ira.
target_text: and it came to pass at that time, that judah went down from his brethren, and turned in to a certain adullamite, whose name was hirah.

source_text: sa raica talega mai kea e dua na goneyalewa ni kenani, na luvei sua, sa vakawatitaki koya ka curumi koya sara.
target_text: and judah saw there a daughter of a certain canaanite, whose name was shuah; and he took her, and went in unto her.

source_text: sa kunekune ka vakasucuma vua e dua na luvena talega sa yacana o eri.
target_text: and she conceived, and bare a son; and he called his name er.

source_text: sa kunekune tale, ka vakasucuma e dua na tagane, sa vakayacani koya o tinana me o onani.
target_text: and she conceived again, and bare a son; and she called his name onan.

source_text: sa dua tale na luvena tagane, sa yacana o sela. sa tiko mai jesiba ena gauna sa sucu kina o sela.
target_text: and she yet again conceived, and bare a son; and called his name shelah: and he was at chezib, when she bare him.

source_text: o juta sa kauta mai e dua na wati eri, na nona ulumatua, na yacana o tamare.
target_text: and judah took a wife for er his firstborn, whose name was tamar.

source_text: ia, o eri na ulumatua i juta, sa caka ca ena mata i jiova, o jiova ga sa vakamatei koya.
target_text: and er, judah's firstborn, was wicked in the sight of the lord; and the lord slew him.

source_text: o juta sa tukuna vei onani, "lako vei wati tacimu, mo drau veiwatini, ka vakatubura e dua na kawa vei tacimu. "
target_text: and judah said unto onan, go in unto thy brother's wife, and marry her, and raise up seed to thy brother.

source_text: sa kila o onami ni o na luvena ena sega ni nona, sa vakadrodroya kina qele, ena gauna sa curumi wati tacina tiko kina “de qai solia na kawa vei tacina.
target_text: and onan knew that the seed should not be his; and it came to pass, when he went in unto his brother's wife, that he spilled it on the ground, lest that he should give seed to his brother.

source_text: na veika oqo sa sega ni marautaka o jiova, oqo, sa vakamatei onani talega kina.
target_text: and the thing which he did displeased the lord: wherefore he slew him also.

source_text: sa tukuna o juta vei vugona o tamare, "mo tiko yada mada ena vale i tamamu, " me yacova ni sa cauravou mai o sela. " de qai mate tale me vakataki tacina. " sa lako o tamare ka tiko wawa ena vale nei tamana.
target_text: then said judah to tamar his daughter in law, remain a widow at thy father's house, till shelah my son be grown: for he said, lest peradventure he die also, as his brethren did. and tamar went and dwelt in her father's house.

source_text: sa yaco na gauna sa mate kina na wati juta, sa vakacegui ka lako cake vei ira na nona dauvakatawa sipi e timana, o koya kei na nona i tokani o ira na kai etulama.
target_text: and in process of time the daughter of shuah judah's wife died; and judah was comforted, and went up unto his sheepshearers to timnath, he and his friend hirah the adullamite.

source_text: sa tukuni vei tamare, "raica o nomu momo sa lako cake i timana me raica na nona sipi. "
target_text: and it was told tamar, saying, behold thy father in law goeth up to timnath to shear his sheep.

source_text: sa luvata tani na nona i sulu vaka yada, sa ubi koya ka la'ki dabe tiko ena tikina lala ena sala vaka ki timana; ni sa raici sela sa cauravou levu mai “ia sa sega ga ni lako yani me rau veiwatini.
target_text: and she put her widow's garments off from her, and covered her with a vail, and wrapped herself, and sat in an open place, which is by the way to timnath; for she saw that shelah was grown, and she was not given unto him to wife.

source_text: ni sa raici koya o juta, sa nanuma ni oqo e dua e volitaki koya tiko, baleta ni ubia tiko na matana taucoko.
target_text: when judah saw her, he thought her to be an harlot; because she had covered her face.

source_text: sa vuki yani vua ena sala ka tukuna, "au kerea me'u curumi iko mada, " sa sega ni kila, o ya o na vugona. sa taroga o vugona, "na cava o na solia vei au, me rawa ni o curumi au kina? "
target_text: and he turned unto her by the way, and said, go to, i pray thee, let me come in unto thee; (for he knew not that she was his daughter in law. ) and she said, what wilt thou give me, that thou mayest come in unto me?

source_text: sa sauma mai, "au na solia mai e dua na me gone. " sa tukuna tale yani, "mo solia mai e dua na kena i vakadinadina? "
target_text: and he said, i will send thee a kid from the flock. and she said, wilt thou give me a pledge, till thou send it?

source_text: "na cava me'u solia vei iko? " sa sauma mai na nomu i taube/mama kei na nomu i titoko. " sa mani solia yani vua, ka curumi koya sara ka sa kunekune talega mai vua.
target_text: and he said, what pledge shall i give thee? and she said, thy signet, and thy bracelets, and thy staff that is in thine hand. and he gave it her, and came in unto her, and she conceived by him.

source_text: sa tucake ka lako yani, sa veisautaka na nona i sulu ka dara tale na nona i sulu vakayada.
target_text: and she arose, and went away, and laid by her vail from her, and put on the garments of her widowhood.

source_text: sa vakauta yani o juta na me gone, mai na ligana na nona i tokani na kai etulama vua na yalewa. ia, sa sega ga ni kune.
target_text: and judah sent the kid by the hand of his friend the adullamite, to receive his pledge from the woman's hand: but he found her not.

source_text: sa tarogi ira na tagane ena vanua o ya, "e vei o koya na dau volivolitaki sa tu ena sala? " era sa sauma, "sa sega eke na dauvolivolitaki sa tu ena sala. "
target_text: then he asked the men of that place, saying, where is the harlot, that was openly by the way side? and they said, there was no harlot in this place.

source_text: sa lesu tale yani vei juta ka tukuna, "au sa sega ni raici koya, o ira talega na tagane mai keau era sa tukuna ni sa sega na dauvolivolitaki vakaoqo ena vanua. "
target_text: and he returned to judah, and said, i cannot find her; and also the men of the place said, that there was no harlot in this place.

source_text: sa tukuna o juta, "me sa taura ga yani o koya de daru na qai madua “ni'u sa solia yani na me, ia sa yali o koya. "
target_text: and judah said, let her take it to her, lest we be shamed: behold, i sent this kid, and thou hast not found her.

source_text: ni sa oti tale e tolu na vula, sa tukuni sara vei juta ka vaka: "o tamare na vugomu ea volitaki koya ena sala ka sa bukete tiko. " sa tukuna yani o juta, "kauti koya mai me mai vakamai! "
target_text: and it came to pass about three months after, that it was told judah, saying, tamar thy daughter in law hath played the harlot; and also, behold, she is with child by whoredom. and judah said, bring her forth, and let her be burnt.

source_text: ni sa kau mai, sa tukuna vei nona momo, "o koya na tagane sa nona oqo, sa vakabuketetaki au, " mo raica mada se nei cei oqo, nai taube, mama kei na i titoko. "
target_text: when she was brought forth, she sent to her father in law, saying, by the man, whose these are, am i with child: and she said, discern, i pray thee, whose are these, the signet, and bracelets, and staff.

source_text: sa tukuna o juta, ni sa kila ka sa tukuna, "sa yalododonu cake o koya mai vei au, ni'u sa sega ni soli koya vei sela baleta ni sa tamata levu mai. " sa sega ni curumi koya tale.
target_text: and judah acknowledged them, and said, she hath been more righteous than i; because that i gave her not to shelah my son. and he knew her again no more.

source_text: ena gauna me sa vakasucu kina, sa tiko e ketena e rua na gone.
target_text: and it came to pass in the time of her travail, that, behold, twins were in her womb.

source_text: ni sa vakasucu tiko, sa basika mai e dua na liga, o koya na dau ni veivakasucumi sa vesuka sara e dua na wa lokaloka e ligana ka tukuna, "oqo e liu mai. "
target_text: and it came to pass, when she travailed, that the one put out his hand: and the midwife took and bound upon his hand a scarlet thread, saying, this came out first.

source_text: na ka e yaco ni sa vakasuka lesu tale na ligana, sa basika mai o tacina vakasauri ni sega ni namaki, ka tukuna sara, "o lako mai vakacava? o takoso mai. " sa yacana kina me o veresi.
target_text: and it came to pass, as he drew back his hand, that, behold, his brother came out: and she said, how hast thou broken forth? this breach be upon thee: therefore his name was called pharez.

source_text: ni oti oqo sa qai basika mai o tacina ni sa tiko e ligana na wa lokaloka. sa yacana o sira.
target_text: and afterward came out his brother, that had the scarlet thread upon his hand: and his name was called zarah.

source_text: sa kau sobu o joseva ki ijipita. o potifa nai vakalesilesi nei fero ka nodra i liuliu na mata yadra, sa voli koya mai vei ira na isimeli.
target_text: and joseph was brought down to egypt; and potiphar, an officer of pharaoh, captain of the guard, an egyptian, bought him of the hands of the ishmeelites, which had brought him down thither.

source_text: sa tiko vata kei joseva o jiova. sa tamata yaco o koya; ka sa tiko ena vale ni nona turaga na kai ijipita.
target_text: and the lord was with joseph, and he was a prosperous man; and he was in the house of his master the egyptian.

source_text: sa raica tiko na nona turaga ni sa tiko vata kei koya o jiova. o jiova sa vakavuna na vuavuai vinaka na veika sa tara tiko na ligana.
target_text: and his master saw that the lord was with him, and that the lord made all that he did to prosper in his hand.

source_text: sa taleitaki tiko vakalevu o joseva mai vua na nona turaga. sa yaco me lewa taucoko na vale ni nona turaga.
target_text: and joseph found grace in his sight, and he served him: and he made him overseer over his house, and all that he had he put into his hand.

source_text: sa yaco talega me vakalouvinakataka o jiova na nona vale na kai ijipita oqo, ena vuku i joseva, na kalouvinaka oqo sa tara yani na loma ni vale kei na vei ka e tuba.
target_text: and it came to pass from the time that he had made him overseer in his house, and over all that he had, that the lord blessed the egyptian's house for joseph's sake; and the blessing of the lord was upon all that he had in the house, and in the field.

source_text: sa soli na veika kecega ki na ligai joseva, sa sega ni via kila tale e dua na ka, vakavo ga na madrai ni sa taura e ligana me kana. sa tamata rairai vinaka talega o joseva.
target_text: and he left all that he had in joseph's hand; and he knew not ought he had, save the bread which he did eat. and joseph was a goodly person, and well favoured.

source_text: ni sa yaco tiko na veika oqo, na wati potifa sa domoni joseva vakalevu, sa mani tukuna kina vei joseva, "daru veidomoni mada. "
target_text: and it came to pass after these things, that his master's wife cast her eyes upon joseph; and she said, lie with me.

source_text: sa bese o joseva ka tukuna, "raica na noqu turaga sa sega ni kila na ka kece sa tu oqo e vale, baleta ni sa solia kece tu oqo ki na ligaqu.
target_text: but he refused, and said unto his master's wife, behold, my master wotteth not what is with me in the house, and he hath committed all that he hath to my hand;

source_text: "sa sega ni dua e uasivi vei au ena vale oqo, sa sega talega ni vakavoca vei au e dua na ka me'u lewa, au sa lewa kecega, vakavo duadua o iko, ni o sa watina. me'u cakava vakacava nai valavala ca levu oqo, nai valavala ca vua na kalou? "
target_text: there is none greater in this house than i; neither hath he kept back any thing from me but thee, because thou art his wife: how then can i do this great wickedness, and sin against god?

source_text: sa sagai joseva tikoga ena veisiga “sa sega ga ni via rogoci koya o joseva.
target_text: and it came to pass, as she spake to joseph day by day, that he hearkened not unto her, to lie by her, or to be with her.

source_text: sa qai yaco ni sa lako tale yani o joseva me cakava na nona cakacaka e vale “sa sega na tagane me kune e vale,
target_text: and it came to pass about this time, that joseph went into the house to do his business; and there was none of the men of the house there within.

source_text: sa vesuki joseva vata kei na nona i oro bale ka tukuna, "daru mai veicurumi mada. " sa biuta tu na nona i oro bale e ligana ka dro yani ki tuba.
target_text: and she caught him by his garment, saying, lie with me: and he left his garment in her hand, and fled, and got him out.

source_text: sa qai yaco, ni sa raica ni sa biuta tu mai o joseva na nona i oro ena ligana ka dro yani ki tuba,
target_text: and it came to pass, when she saw that he had left his garment in her hand, and was fled forth,

source_text: sa kacivi ira mai na turaga ena vale ka tukuna vei ira, "raica sa kau mai vei keda e dua na iperiu oqo me vakalialiai keda. sa lako mai ka vakasagai au, ka vinakata me moceri au, au sa qai kaila vakadomoi levu.
target_text: that she called unto the men of her house, and spake unto them, saying, see, he hath brought in an hebrew unto us to mock us; he came in unto me to lie with me, and i cried with a loud voice:

source_text: "ni sa rogoca o koya ni'u sa qoqolou, sa qai biuta tu mai na nona i oro ka dro yani ki tuba. "
target_text: and it came to pass, when he heard that i lifted up my voice and cried, that he left his garment with me, and fled, and got him out.

source_text: sa taura tiko ga na nona i oro me yacova ni sa lako mai na nona turaga ki vale.
target_text: and she laid up his garment by her, until his lord came home.

source_text: sa qai vosa vua me vaka oqo: "na iperiu dauveiqaravi o a kauta mai vei keda, sa lako mai vei au me vakalialiai au;
target_text: and she spake unto him according to these words, saying, the hebrew servant, which thou hast brought unto us, came in unto me to mock me:

source_text: "ena gauna au sa kaikaila kina, sa biuta tu mai na nona i oro ka dro yani ki tuba. "
target_text: and it came to pass, as i lifted up my voice and cried, that he left his garment with me, and fled out.

source_text: ni sa rogoca o nona turaga na veika sa tukuna vua o watina ni sa tukuna, "na nomu tamata sa cakava vaka oqo vei au, " sa tubu sara na nona cudru.
target_text: and it came to pass, when his master heard the words of his wife, which she spake unto him, saying, after this manner did thy servant to me; that his wrath was kindled.

source_text: na turaga i joseva sa tauri koya ka biuta ki vale ni veivesu. na vanua era sa tiko kina na kaivesu ni tui. sa tiko talega kina o joseva.
target_text: and joseph's master took him, and put him into the prison, a place where the king's prisoners were bound: and he was there in the prison.

source_text: ia, o jiova sa tiko vata ga kei joseva, ka sa vakaraitaka tiko vua na nona loloma. sa solia tiko ga vei joseva na nona vinaka ena mata i koya na i vakatawa ni vale ni veivesu.
target_text: but the lord was with joseph, and shewed him mercy, and gave him favour in the sight of the keeper of the prison.

source_text: nai vakatawa ni valeniveivesu sa solia kece ki na ligai joseva na lewa ni nodra bula kece na kaivesu; na ka kece era cakava sa nona lewa ga.
target_text: and the keeper of the prison committed to joseph's hand all the prisoners that were in the prison; and whatsoever they did there, he was the doer of it.

source_text: sa sega tale ni via kila mai nai vakatawa ni valeniveivesu e dua na ka, baleta ni sa tiko vata kei koya o jiova. na veika kece e caka, sa vakagugumatuataka o jiova.
target_text: the keeper of the prison looked not to any thing that was under his hand; because the lord was with him, and that which he did, the lord made it to prosper.

source_text: sa qai yaco ena dua na gauna, o koya na dauvakarau mena waini kei koya na dau vavi kakana nei fero, e rau sa caka cala vua na nodrau turaga na tui ijipita.
target_text: and it came to pass after these things, that the butler of the king of egypt and his baker had offended their lord the king of egypt.

source_text: o fero sa cudruvi rau vakalevu na nona dauveiqaravi oqo, na i liuliu ni caka waini kei nai liuliu ni dauvavavi.
target_text: and pharaoh was wroth against two of his officers, against the chief of the butlers, and against the chief of the bakers.

source_text: sa biuti rau ena ligai koya nai liuliu ni mata yadra ni valeniveivesu. ena vanua sa vesu tiko kina o joseva.
target_text: and he put them in ward in the house of the captain of the guard, into the prison, the place where joseph was bound.

source_text: nai liuliu ni mata yadra sa beitaki joseva vata kei rau, ka sa qaravi rau. e ratou s vesu tiko vakawawa.
target_text: and the captain of the guard charged joseph with them, and he served them: and they continued a season in ward.

source_text: o koya na dauvakarau waini kei koya na dauvavavi nei fero, e rau sa tadra ruarua, na nodrau tadra yadudua ena dua ga na bogi, ka duidui na kena i balebale.
target_text: and they dreamed a dream both of them, each man his dream in one night, each man according to the interpretation of his dream, the butler and the baker of the king of egypt, which were bound in the prison.

source_text: sa lako mai vei rau o joseva ena mataka, ka raici rau, sa raica ni rau sa rarawa sara vakalevu.
target_text: and joseph came in unto them in the morning, and looked upon them, and, behold, they were sad.

source_text: sa tarogi rau sara ka vaka: "na cava drau sa rui rarawa kina vakalevu ena siga oqo? "
target_text: and he asked pharaoh's officers that were with him in the ward of his lord's house, saying, wherefore look ye so sadly to day?

source_text: e rau sa tukuna vua, "keirau sa dui tadra na tadra e duidui, ka sa sega na kena i vakavakadewa. " sa tukuna o joseva, "sa sega beka ni nona ga na kalou na vakavakadewa? drau tukuna mai vei au. "
target_text: and they said unto him, we have dreamed a dream, and there is no interpreter of it. and joseph said unto them, do not interpretations belong to god? tell me them, i pray you.

source_text: nai liuliu ni dauvakarau waini sa tukuna vei joseva na nona tadra ka vaka: "ena noqu tadra, sa tu e mataqu e dua na vaini,
target_text: and the chief butler told his dream to joseph, and said to him, in my dream, behold, a vine was before me;

source_text: "na vaini oqo sa tolu na tabana, sa kubu mai, sa vakadrauna sara, sa se ka kauta mai na vuana sa dreu tu.
target_text: and in the vine were three branches: and it was as though it budded, and her blossoms shot forth; and the clusters thereof brought forth ripe grapes:

source_text: "sa tu e ligaqu na bula nei fero, au sa taura na vaini dreu ka lobaka ena bilo nei fero, ka au sa kauta sara na bilo ka solia ena ligai fero. "
target_text: and pharaoh's cup was in my hand: and i took the grapes, and pressed them into pharaoh's cup, and i gave the cup into pharaoh's hand.

source_text: sa tukuna vua o joseva, "oqo na kena i vakavakadewa, na tolu na tabana sa tolu na siga.
target_text: and joseph said unto him, this is the interpretation of it: the three branches are three days:

source_text: "ena tolu na siga oqo, o fero ena laveti iko cake tale, ka vakatikori iko lesu tale ki na nomu i tutu, ka o na dau soli mena gunu tale na fero me vaka ga o sa dau cakava e liu.
target_text: yet within three days shall pharaoh lift up thine head, and restore thee unto thy place: and thou shalt deliver pharaoh's cup into his hand, after the former manner when thou wast his butler.

source_text: "mo qai nanumi au mai ni o sa tiko vinaka, ka mo vakaraitaka vei au na nomu yalovinaka; mo dau tukuni au vei fero, ka mo kauti au tani mai na vale oqo.
target_text: but think on me when it shall be well with thee, and shew kindness, i pray thee, unto me, and make mention of me unto pharaoh, and bring me out of this house:

source_text: "ni sa ka dina, na noqu kau tani mai vakaukauwa mai na nodra vanua na iperiu; au sa sega talega ni cakava e dua na ka e ganita na noqu mai tu oqo. "
target_text: for indeed i was stolen away out of the land of the hebrews: and here also have i done nothing that they should put me into the dungeon.

source_text: ni sa raica na i liuliu ni dau vavavi ni sa vinaka nai vakamacala nei joseva, sa tukuna sara yani, "o au talega, ena noqu tadra, sa tolu na i su vulavula e uluqu.
target_text: when the chief baker saw that the interpretation was good, he said unto joseph, i also was in my dream, and, behold, i had three white baskets on my head:

source_text: "nai su sa tiko duadua e cake, sa tiko kina na veikakana vavi me kei fero, era sa mai kania na manumanu vuka, mai na uluqu. "
target_text: and in the uppermost basket there was of all manner of bakemeats for pharaoh; and the birds did eat them out of the basket upon my head.

source_text: sa sauma vua o joseva ka vaka: "oqo na kena i balebale, e tolu na i su, sa tolu na siga.
target_text: and joseph answered and said, this is the interpretation thereof: the three baskets are three days:

source_text: "ena tolu na siga oqo, o fero ena vakaliliga na domomu ena dua na vunikau, mai kea, era na kania kina na lewemu na manumanu vuka. "
target_text: yet within three days shall pharaoh lift up thy head from off thee, and shall hang thee on a tree; and the birds shall eat thy flesh from off thee.

source_text: sa qai yaco ena i ka tolu ni siga, na siga talega ni vakananumi ni sucu nei fero, sa cakava kina e dua na kakana levu vei ira na nona dauveiqaravi; sa vakaturi rau cake na nona i liuliu ni daucaka waini kei koya nai liuliu ni dau vavavi e matadra na dauveiqaravi.
target_text: and it came to pass the third day, which was pharaoh's birthday, that he made a feast unto all his servants: and he lifted up the head of the chief butler and of the chief baker among his servants.

source_text: sa vakatikora lesu na nona dau caka waini, ka sa dau biuta na waini ena ligai fero.
target_text: and he restored the chief butler unto his butlership again; and he gave the cup into pharaoh's hand:

source_text: sa vakakukunataki koya na dau vavavi, me vaka nai vakamacala nei joseva vei rau.
target_text: but he hanged the chief baker: as joseph had interpreted to them.

source_text: nai liuliu ni dau vakarau waini sa sega ni nanumi joseva, ka sa guilecavi koya.
target_text: yet did not the chief butler remember joseph, but forgat him.

source_text: ni sa oti vinaka e rua na yabaki, sa tadra o fero; ni sa tucake tu ena dua na bati ni uciwai.
target_text: and it came to pass at the end of two full years, that pharaoh dreamed: and, behold, he stood by the river.

source_text: vakasauri e ratou sa basika mai wai e vitu na bulumakau rairai vinaka ka levulevu, ka era sa mai kakana voli.
target_text: and, behold, there came up out of the river seven well favoured kine and fatfleshed; and they fed in a meadow.

source_text: era sa muri tale mai e vitu tale na bulumakau lila ka rairai ca, ka ra sa mai tu talega ena bati ni uciwai.
target_text: and, behold, seven other kine came up after them out of the river, ill favoured and leanfleshed; and stood by the other kine upon the brink of the river.

source_text: o ira na ka lila rairai ca oqo, era sa kani ira na ka levulevu ka rairai vinaka oqo: sa yadra sara o fero.
target_text: and the ill favoured and leanfleshed kine did eat up the seven well favoured and fat kine. so pharaoh awoke.

source_text: sa moce tale, ka tadra ena i karua ni gauna, ni sa basika e vitu na sila mai na dua ga na vuna, sa bulabula ka rairai vinaka.
target_text: and he slept and dreamed the second time: and, behold, seven ears of corn came up upon one stalk, rank and good.

source_text: sa basika tale mai e vitu na sila raqosa ka matemate, ena kena liwa mai na tokalau.
target_text: and, behold, seven thin ears and blasted with the east wind sprung up after them.

source_text: na vitu na sila raqosa sa tiloma na vitu na sila bulabula ka vinaka oqo. sa yadra o fero, ka qai kila, ni sa tadra walega.
target_text: and the seven thin ears devoured the seven rank and full ears. and pharaoh awoke, and, behold, it was a dream.

source_text: ena mataka o ya, sa leqa vakalevu tiko na yaloi fero, sa talatala yani me ra lako mai vua na dau caka i sausau kece e ijipita kei ira kece na tamata vuku. sa tukuna vei ira o fero na nona tadra, ia, sa sega e dua me vakamacalataka rawa na kena i balebale vei fero.
target_text: and it came to pass in the morning that his spirit was troubled; and he sent and called for all the magicians of egypt, and all the wise men thereof: and pharaoh told them his dream; but there was none that could interpret them unto pharaoh.

source_text: sa qai vosa vei fero nai liuliu ni dauvakarau waini ka tukuna, "ena siga oqo, au sa qai kila kina na noqu cala.
target_text: then spake the chief butler unto pharaoh, saying, i do remember my faults this day:

source_text: "ena gauna sa cudru kina o fero vei rau na nona tamata, o au kei koya na dauvavavi, ka keirau sa tu vakavesu,
target_text: pharaoh was wroth with his servants, and put me in ward in the captain of the guard's house, both me and the chief baker:

source_text: "keirau sa dui tadra yadudua ena dua ga na bogi. sa tu ga na i vakavakadewa ni neirau dui tadra.
target_text: and we dreamed a dream in one night, i and he; we dreamed each man according to the interpretation of his dream.

source_text: "sa dua na cauravou ni iperiu sa tiko vata kei keda, e nona dauveiqaravi na i liuliu ni mata yadra. keirau sa tukuna vua na neirau tadra, ka sa vakabalebaletaka vei keirau na neirau tadra.
target_text: and there was there with us a young man, an hebrew, servant to the captain of the guard; and we told him, and he interpreted to us our dreams; to each man according to his dream he did interpret.

source_text: "sa yaco me vaka sa vakabalebaletaka vei keirau. au sa vakatikori lesu tale, o koya ka dua sa vakakukunataki. "
target_text: and it came to pass, as he interpreted to us, so it was; me he restored unto mine office, and him he hanged.

source_text: sa talatala o fero me kau mai o joseva, era sa kauti koya mai vakatotolo. era sa vakasavasavataki koya, toro na kumina ka veisau na nona i sulu ka kau mai vei fero.
target_text: then pharaoh sent and called joseph, and they brought him hastily out of the dungeon: and he shaved himself, and changed his raiment, and came in unto pharaoh.

source_text: sa tukuna vua o fero, "au a tadra e dua na tadra, sa sega ni dua me tukuna vei au na kena i balebale. au sa rogoca ni o iko, e rawa ni o vakaibalebaletaka na tadra. "
target_text: and pharaoh said unto joseph, i have dreamed a dream, and there is none that can interpret it: and i have heard say of thee, that thou canst understand a dream to interpret it.

source_text: sa vosa o joseva vei fero ka vaka: "sa sega ni o au, na kalou ga, ena rawa ni sauma vei fero ena vakacegu. "
target_text: and joseph answered pharaoh, saying, it is not in me: god shall give pharaoh an answer of peace.

source_text: sa qai tukuna o fero na nona tadra vei joseva, "raica, ena noqu tadra, au sa tucake tu ena bati ni uciwai.
target_text: and pharaoh said unto joseph, in my dream, behold, i stood upon the bank of the river:

source_text: "vakasauri, e ratou sa lako mai wai e vitu na bulumakau bulabula ka rairai vinaka, ka e ratou sa mai kakana voli.
target_text: and, behold, there came up out of the river seven kine, fatfleshed and well favoured; and they fed in a meadow:

source_text: "e ratou sa lako tale mai e vitu tale na bulumakau bulabula ka rairai vinaka, ka e ratou sa mai kakana voli.
target_text: and, behold, seven other kine came up after them, poor and very ill favoured and leanfleshed, such as i never saw in all the land of egypt for badness:

source_text: "era sa kani iratou na lewe vitu bulabula rairai vinaka ka basika e liu.
target_text: and the lean and the ill favoured kine did eat up the first seven fat kine:

source_text: "ni ratou sa kana oti, e sega sara ga ni kilai ni ratou kania e dua na ka, baleta ni ratou rairai tuga vaka e liu. oqo sa vakayadrati au.
target_text: and when they had eaten them up, it could not be known that they had eaten them; but they were still ill favoured, as at the beginning. so i awoke.

source_text: "au sa raica talega ena noqu tadra, e vitu na sila vinaka ka bulabula sa basika mai na dua na vuna.
target_text: and i saw in my dream, and, behold, seven ears came up in one stalk, full and good:

source_text: "raica sa vitu talega na sila, lila ka raqosa, sa kauta mai na cagi tokalau sa basika cake talega mai.
target_text: and, behold, seven ears, withered, thin, and blasted with the east wind, sprung up after them:

source_text: "na sila lila, raqosa malai oqo, sa tilomi ira na ka bulabula rairai vinaka. au sa vakamacalataka oqo vei ira na kila ka, sa sega ni dua e vakaibalebaletaka rawa vei au. "
target_text: and the thin ears devoured the seven good ears: and i told this unto the magicians; but there was none that could declare it to me.

source_text: sa tukuna o joseva vei fero, "sa dua ga na tadra nei fero, na kalou sa vakaraitaka vei fero na veika sa vakarau me cakava:
target_text: and joseph said unto pharaoh, the dream of pharaoh is one: god hath shewed pharaoh what he is about to do.

source_text: "na vitu na bulumakau, sa vitu na yabaki, na vitu na sila vinaka, sa vitu na yabaki vinaka “sa dua ga na tadra.
target_text: the seven good kine are seven years; and the seven good ears are seven years: the dream is one.

source_text: "na vitu na bulumakau lila matemate sa muri mai, oqori sa vitu na yabaki kei na cagi tokalau, sa vitu na yabaki ni dausiga.
target_text: and the seven thin and ill favoured kine that came up after them are seven years; and the seven empty ears blasted with the east wind shall be seven years of famine.

source_text: "oqo na veika au sa tukuna vei fero. na kalou sa vakaraitaka vei fero na veika ena vakarau cakava.
target_text: this is the thing which i have spoken unto pharaoh: what god is about to do he sheweth unto pharaoh.

source_text: "raica, ena liu mai na vitu na yabaki ni sautu ena vanua taucoko e ijipita;
target_text: behold, there come seven years of great plenty throughout all the land of egypt:

source_text: "ni oti o ya, ena lako mai na vitu na yabaki ni via kana. ena guilecavi na vitu na yabaki vinaka ena vanua o ijipita, na dausiga ena vakarusa na vanua.
target_text: and there shall arise after them seven years of famine; and all the plenty shall be forgotten in the land of egypt; and the famine shall consume the land;

source_text: "na sautu ena guilecavi ena vanua, baleta ni sa lako mai na dausiga, ena ca vakalevu sara.
target_text: and the plenty shall not be known in the land by reason of that famine following; for it shall be very grievous.

source_text: "sa tokaruataki vei fero nai balebale ni tadra, baleta na kalou sa vakadeitaka, na kalou ga ena vakayacora dina.
target_text: and for that the dream was doubled unto pharaoh twice; it is because the thing is established by god, and god will shortly bring it to pass.

source_text: "oqo, me qai digitaka o fero e dua na tamata vuku ka rai yawa, me qarava na ka oqo ena vanua o ijipita.
target_text: now therefore let pharaoh look out a man discreet and wise, and set him over the land of egypt.

source_text: "me cakava o fero oqo, me digitaki ira nai vakalesilesi ena vanua taucoko, me ra kumuna mai e dua nai kalima na vua ni qele e ijipita ena yabaki ni sautu oqo.
target_text: let pharaoh do this, and let him appoint officers over the land, and take up the fifth part of the land of egypt in the seven plenteous years.

source_text: "me ra sa kumuna mai na kakana ena vei yabaki vinaka oqo, ka biuta tiko ena i lololo ena lewa vakalawa i fero, ka me ra maroroi tiko ena vei koro lelevu.
target_text: and let them gather all the food of those good years that come, and lay up corn under the hand of pharaoh, and let them keep food in the cities.

source_text: "na lololo ni kakana oqo me ra tu vakarau tu ni sa basika mai na dausiga o koya ena tarai ijipita mai, me kua ni leqa kina oijipita ni sa yaco mai na dausiga. "
target_text: and that food shall be for store to the land against the seven years of famine, which shall be in the land of egypt; that the land perish not through the famine.

source_text: nai vakasala mai vei joseva, sa vinaka vei fero kei ira kece nai vakalesilesi.
target_text: and the thing was good in the eyes of pharaoh, and in the eyes of all his servants.

source_text: sa tukuna o fero vei ira na dauveiqaravi, "e rawa beka ni da kunea e dua na tamata vaka oqo, na tamata sa tu vua na yalo ni kalou? "
target_text: and pharaoh said unto his servants, can we find such a one as this is, a man in whom the spirit of god is?

source_text: sa tukuna o fero vei joseva, "me vaka sa vakaraitaka oqo vei iko na kalou, sa sega tale e dua me rai yawa ka vuku me vakataki iko.
target_text: and pharaoh said unto joseph, forasmuch as god hath shewed thee all this, there is none so discreet and wise as thou art:

source_text: "o na lewa na noqu vale kei ira na noqu tamata era na lewai ena nomu vosa, ena i tikotiko vakaturaga ga, au na liu tiko kina vei iko. "
target_text: thou shalt be over my house, and according unto thy word shall all my people be ruled: only in the throne will i be greater than thou.

source_text: sa tukuna o fero vei joseva, "raica au sa solia vei iko na lewa ena vanua taucoko o ijipita. "
target_text: and pharaoh said unto joseph, see, i have set thee over all the land of egypt.

source_text: sa taura na nona mama ni lewa cecere o ijipita ka vakacuruma e ligai joseva, ka vakasulumi koya ena i oro bale lineni matailalai kei nai taube koula e domona.
target_text: and pharaoh took off his ring from his hand, and put it upon joseph's hand, and arrayed him in vestures of fine linen, and put a gold chain about his neck;

source_text: sa vakavodoki joseva ena i karua ni qiqi vakatui, ka era sa kaciva yani "mo ni tekiduru! " sa vakatikori koya me lewa taucoko e ijipita.
target_text: and he made him to ride in the second chariot which he had; and they cried before him, bow the knee: and he made him ruler over all the land of egypt.

source_text: sa tukuna talega o fero vei joseva, "o au o fero, ena nomu lewa ga, ena qai tara kina vua e dua me laveta na ligana se yavana ena vanua taucoko o ijipita. "
target_text: and pharaoh said unto joseph, i am pharaoh, and without thee shall no man lift up his hand or foot in all the land of egypt.

source_text: o fero sa vakayacani joseva me sefanacipaenaca. sa solia vua e dua na watina, na yacana o asenaca na luvei poti-fera na bete mai oni. sa lako yani o joseva ki na vanua taucoko o ijipita.
target_text: and pharaoh called joseph's name zaphnathpaaneah; and he gave him to wife asenath the daughter of potipherah priest of on. and joseph went out over all the land of egypt.

source_text: sa yabaki tolusagavulu o joseva ni sa tu ena matai fero na tui ijipita. sa lako tani mai na mata i fero ka lako yani ki ijipita taucoko.
target_text: and joseph was thirty years old when he stood before pharaoh king of egypt. and joseph went out from the presence of pharaoh, and went throughout all the land of egypt.

source_text: ena vitu na yabaki ni sautu, sa vuavuai dina na vanua e ijipita.
target_text: and in the seven plenteous years the earth brought forth by handfuls.

source_text: sa kumuna kece mai na kakana, ena vitu na yabaki ni sautu e ijipita, ka binia ena veikoro lelevu na kakana mai na veivanua volivolita.
target_text: and he gathered up all the food of the seven years, which were in the land of egypt, and laid up the food in the cities: the food of the field, which was round about every city, laid he up in the same.

source_text: sa kumuna mai na sila o joseva, sa vaka na nuku ni matasawa, me yacova ga ni ra sa sega ni wiliki rawa.
target_text: and joseph gathered corn as the sand of the sea, very much, until he left numbering; for it was without number.

source_text: sa vakasucumi vei joseva e rua na luvena tagane ni bera na dausiga mai vei asenaca na luvei poti-fera na bete mai oni.
target_text: and unto joseph were born two sons before the years of famine came, which asenath the daughter of potipherah priest of on bare unto him.

source_text: o joseva sa vakayacani koya na ulumatua me o manasa, "ni kalou sa vakavuna me'u guilecava na noqu oca kei na noqu vuvale. "
target_text: and joseph called the name of the firstborn manasseh: for god, said he, hath made me forget all my toil, and all my father's house.

source_text: sa vakayacani koya nai karua me o ifereimi, "ni kalou sa vakavuna me'u vuavuai ena vanua ni noqu rarawa. "
target_text: and the name of the second called he ephraim: for god hath caused me to be fruitful in the land of my affliction.

source_text: sa mai cava na vitu na yabaki ni sautu ena vanua o ijipita,
target_text: and the seven years of plenteousness, that was in the land of egypt, were ended.

source_text: sa tekivu me basika mai na veiyabaki ni dausiga, me vaka sa tukuna o joseva. na dausiga oqo sa tara na vanua taucoko, mai ijipita ga sa tiko kina na madrai.
target_text: and the seven years of dearth began to come, according as joseph had said: and the dearth was in all lands; but in all the land of egypt there was bread.

source_text: na vanua taucoko sa tarai ira na dausiga, ka era sa tagi vei fero me so na kedra madrai. sa tukuna vei ira o fero, "ni lako vei joseva, na veika ga sa tukuna vei kemuni mo ni qai cakava. "
target_text: and when all the land of egypt was famished, the people cried to pharaoh for bread: and pharaoh said unto all the egyptians, go unto joseph; what he saith to you, do.

source_text: sa tarai vuravura taucoko na dausiga oqo. o joseva sa dolava na lololo kece ka volivolitaki vei ira na ijipita. sa qai ca ga mai na dausiga e ijipita.
target_text: and the famine was over all the face of the earth: and joseph opened all the storehouses, and sold unto the egyptians; and the famine waxed sore in the land of egypt.

source_text: na veivanua kece, era sa lako mai vei joseva e ijipita, me ra voli sila, baleta na dausiga sa sivia ena vanua kecega.
target_text: and all countries came into egypt to joseph for to buy corn; because that the famine was so sore in all lands.

source_text: ni sa kila o jekope ni sa tu na sila mai ijipita, sa tukuna vei iratou na luvena, "na cava dou sa veiraici tiko kina? "
target_text: now when jacob saw that there was corn in egypt, jacob said unto his sons, why do ye look one upon another?

source_text: au sa rogoca ni sa tiko na sila mai ijipita, "dou lako sobu ka volivoli mai ena vukuda me da bula kina. "
target_text: and he said, behold, i have heard that there is corn in egypt: get you down thither, and buy for us from thence; that we may live, and not die.

source_text: o iratou na lewe tini na taci joseva, e ratou sa lako sobu i ijipita me voli sila.
target_text: and joseph's ten brethren went down to buy corn in egypt.

source_text: o jekope sa sega ni vakatalai penijamini na taci joseva vata kei ira na tacina, ni sa tukuna, "de qai yacovi koya e dua na leqa. "
target_text: but benjamin, joseph's brother, jacob sent not with his brethren; for he said, lest peradventure mischief befall him.

source_text: o iratou na luvei isireli e ratou sa la'ki voli sila vata kei ira na tamata, ni sa levu na dausiga e kenani.
target_text: and the sons of israel came to buy corn among those that came: for the famine was in the land of canaan.

source_text: o joseva sa kovana levu ena vanua, ni sai koya ga sa volivolitaki tiko ena vanua. e ratou sa lako mai na tacina ka cuva e matana.
target_text: and joseph was the governor over the land, and he it was that sold to all the people of the land: and joseph's brethren came, and bowed down themselves before him with their faces to the earth.

source_text: sa raici iratou o joseva ka sa kilai iratou, sa vuki ga me vaka na vulagi vei iratou ka vosa tiko vakaukauwa vei iratou. sa mani tarogi iratou, "dou lako tiko mai vei? " e ratou sa sauma mai, "mai kenani me voli kakana. "
target_text: and joseph saw his brethren, and he knew them, but made himself strange unto them, and spake roughly unto them; and he said unto them, whence come ye? and they said, from the land of canaan to buy food.

source_text: sa kilai iratou na tacina o joseva, ia, o iratou e sega e ratou sega ni kilai koya.
target_text: and joseph knew his brethren, but they knew not him.

source_text: sa nanuma sara o joseva na tadra e a tadra me baleti iratou, ka tukuna vei iratou, "dou sa yamata vuni mai! dou sa lako mai me raica na lala tu ni vanua! "
target_text: and joseph remembered the dreams which he dreamed of them, and said unto them, ye are spies; to see the nakedness of the land ye are come.

source_text: e ratou sa tukuna vei joseva, "e sega neitou turaga, keitou sa lako me voli kakana ga.
target_text: and they said unto him, nay, my lord, but to buy food are thy servants come.

source_text: "keitou sa luvena kecega e dua na tamata, keitou sa tamata dina keitou sa sega ni yamata. "
target_text: we are all one man's sons; we are true men, thy servants are no spies.

source_text: sa tukuna tiko ga o koya, "e sega dou sa lako mai me vakaraica lo na vanua. "
target_text: and he said unto them, nay, but to see the nakedness of the land ye are come.

source_text: e ratou sa tukuna, "keitou na nomuni tamata sa lewe tinikarua na veitacini, na luve ni dua na tamata ena vanua o kenani; o koya e gone duadua sa tiko ga kei tamai keitou, ia, e dua tale sa sega. "
target_text: and they said, thy servants are twelve brethren, the sons of one man in the land of canaan; and, behold, the youngest is this day with our father, and one is not.

source_text: sa tukuna tiko ga o joseva, "o au sa vosa tiko vei kemudou ka tukuna, 'dou sa yamata vuni! '
target_text: and joseph said unto them, that is it that i spake unto you, saying, ye are spies:

source_text: "oqo dou sa na vakatovolei, me vaka sa bula o fero, dou na sega ni biuta na vanua vakavo, kevaka sa kau mai o koya e gone duadua.
target_text: hereby ye shall be proved: by the life of pharaoh ye shall not go forth hence, except your youngest brother come hither.

source_text: "dou vakatala e dua vei kemudou, me la'ki kauti tacina mai, na kena vo, dou na tiko e vale ni veivesu, me na kilai kina na dina sa tu vei kemudou; kevaka e sega, me vaka sa bula o fero “dou sa yamata vuni dina! "
target_text: send one of you, and let him fetch your brother, and ye shall be kept in prison, that your words may be proved, whether there be any truth in you: or else by the life of pharaoh surely ye are spies.

source_text: sa biuti iratou kece ki vale ni veivesu me tolu na siga.
target_text: and he put them all together into ward three days.

source_text: sa tukuna vei iratou o joseva e nai katolu ni siga, "dou cakava oqo, mo dou bula, ni'u sa rerevaka na kalou:
target_text: and joseph said unto them the third day, this do, and live; for i fear god:

source_text: "kevaka dou sa tamata dina, me dua vei kemudou me vesu tiko, dou lako ka kauta na kakana ni sa levu na dausiga ena nomudou vanua.
target_text: if ye be true men, let one of your brethren be bound in the house of your prison: go ye, carry corn for the famine of your houses:

source_text: "me kau mai na tacimudou gone duadua vei au: me vakadinadinataki kina na nomudou vosa, dou na sega ni mate kina. " e ratou sa cakava vakakina.
target_text: but bring your youngest brother unto me; so shall your words be verified, and ye shall not die. and they did so.

source_text: e ratou sa veitukunayaka, "e datou sa cala dina ena vuku i tacidatou, ni datou sa raica na via bula ena yalona, ni sa vakamasuti kedatou, e datou sa sega ga ni via rogoci koya; o koya oqo sa lakovi kedatou mai kina na veilecayaki levu oqo. "
target_text: and they said one to another, we are verily guilty concerning our brother, in that we saw the anguish of his soul, when he besought us, and we would not hear; therefore is this distress come upon us.

source_text: sa sauma yani vei iratou o rupeni ka vaka: "e sega beka ni'u a tukuna vei kemudou, 'mo dou kua ni valavala ca ena vuku ni gone; ' ia, dou sa sega ni via vakarorogo? ia, oqo na nona dra sa tarogi mai vei kedatou. "
target_text: and reuben answered them, saying, spake i not unto you, saying, do not sin against the child; and ye would not hear? therefore, behold, also his blood is required.

source_text: e ratou sega ni kila ni sa kila o joseva na veika oqo “ni sa vosa tikoga vei iratou mai vua na dau vakavakadewa.
target_text: and they knew not that joseph understood them; for he spake unto them by an interpreter.

source_text: sa vuki tani mai vei iratou ka tagi. sa qai dau lesu tale mai vei iratou ka vosa tale vei iratou. sa tauri simione mai ka vesuki koya e matadratou.
target_text: and he turned himself about from them, and wept; and returned to them again, and communed with them, and took from them simeon, and bound him before their eyes.

source_text: sa solia nai vakaro o joseva me vakatawani kece na nodra dui taga ena sila, me vakalesui tale na nodra i lavo ki na nodra dui taga, me soli talega na kedra i vaqa, e nai lakolako lesu. sa vakayacori me vakakina.
target_text: then joseph commanded to fill their sacks with corn, and to restore every man's money into his sack, and to give them provision for the way: and thus did he unto them.

source_text: era sa vakavodoka na nodra dui asa ena sila ka lako yani mai kea.
target_text: and they laded their asses with the corn, and departed thence.

source_text: ia, sa dua vei ira, sa dolava na nona taga me vakania na nona asa ena sila ena nodra mai cegu tiko, sa raica nai lavo ena gusu ni nona taga.
target_text: and as one of them opened his sack to give his ass provender in the inn, he espied his money; for, behold, it was in his sack's mouth.

source_text: sa tukuna sara yani vei ira na tacina, "na noqu i lavo sa vakasukai tale mai vei au, sa tu oqo ena noqu taga! " era sa rere vakalevu ka veitukuniyaka, "na cava sa cakava vei keda oqo na kalou? "
target_text: and he said unto his brethren, my money is restored; and, lo, it is even in my sack: and their heart failed them, and they were afraid, saying one to another, what is this that god hath done unto us?

source_text: era sa lako vei tamadra o jekope, ena vanua o kenani ka tukuna vua na veika sa yaco ka vaka:
target_text: and they came unto jacob their father unto the land of canaan, and told him all that befell unto them; saying,

source_text: "na nodra turaga ena vanua, sa vosa vakaukauwa vei keitou, ka tukuna ni keitou sa lako yani me raica lo na vanua.
target_text: the man, who is the lord of the land, spake roughly to us, and took us for spies of the country.

source_text: "keitou sa tukuna vua, 'ni keitou sa vosa dina ka sega ni yamata vuni.
target_text: and we said unto him, we are true men; we are no spies:

source_text: 'keitou sa lewe tinikarua ka dua ga na tamai keitou, e dua sa oti yani kei koya e gone duadua sa tiko vata kei tamai keitou ena siga oqo, ena vanua o kenani. '
target_text: we be twelve brethren, sons of our father; one is not, and the youngest is this day with our father in the land of canaan.

source_text: "na turaga ni vanua sa tukuna vei keitou, 'ena ka oqo au na kila kina ni dou sa dina, me biu tiko mai e ke e dua vei kemudou, dou kauta yani na kakana ni dausiga me kedra na nomudou vuvale, ka lako.
target_text: and the man, the lord of the country, said unto us, hereby shall i know that ye are true men; leave one of your brethren here with me, and take food for the famine of your households, and be gone:

source_text: 'dou kauta lesu mai na tacimudou gone duadua vei au, me'u kila dina kina ni dou sa sega ni yamata vuni, ka sa tukuna na ka dina. au na qai soli tacimudou yani ka veivoli talega ena vanua. '"
target_text: and bring your youngest brother unto me: then shall i know that ye are no spies, but that ye are true men: so will i deliver you your brother, and ye shall traffick in the land.

source_text: sa yaco, ni ratou sa sova yani na nodratou dui taga “era sa dui kurabui ni sa tu na nodra dui taga i lavo ena nodra taga ni sila yadudua. ni ra sa raica nai lavo kei tamadra talega, era sa sa rere vakalevu.
target_text: and it came to pass as they emptied their sacks, that, behold, every man's bundle of money was in his sack: and when both they and their father saw the bundles of money, they were afraid.

source_text: sa tukuna vei ira o jekope, "dou sa vakayalolailaitaki au ena vuku ni luvequ. sa yali o joseva, sa yali o simione, oqo dou sa via kauti penijamini tani. na veika kece oqo sa veicoqacoqa kei au. "
target_text: and jacob their father said unto them, me have ye bereaved of my children: joseph is not, and simeon is not, and ye will take benjamin away: all these things are against me.

source_text: sa vosa o rupeni vei tamana ka tukuna, "vakamatei rau na luvequ tagane kevaka au sega ni kauti koya lesu tale mai vei iko; biuti koya e ligaqu “au na kauti koya lesu tale mai vei iko. "
target_text: and reuben spake unto his father, saying, slay my two sons, if i bring him not to thee: deliver him into my hand, and i will bring him to thee again.

source_text: sa tukuna mai o jekope, "na luvequ ena sega ni lako sobu kei kemudou, sa mate oti o tacina, sa vo duadua ga o koya. kevaka ena yacovi koya e dua na ka ena sala dou na lakova, dou na kauta sobu na ulu sika oqo ena rarawa ki nai bulubulu. "
target_text: and he said, my son shall not go down with you; for his brother is dead, and he is left alone: if mischief befall him by the way in the which ye go, then shall ye bring down my gray hairs with sorrow to the grave.

source_text: sa ca vakalevu sara na dausiga ena vanua.
target_text: and the famine was sore in the land.

source_text: sa yaco, ni ra sa kania oti na sila sa kau mai ijipita, sa tukuna vei ira o tamadra, "dou lesu tale ka volia tale mai na kakana. "
target_text: and it came to pass, when they had eaten up the corn which they had brought out of egypt, their father said unto them, go again, buy us a little food.

source_text: sa vosa vua o juta, "raica sa vosa vei keitou na tamata, 'dou kua tale ni raica na mataqu, vakavo ke sa lako mai na tacimudou gone duadua. '
target_text: and judah spake unto him, saying, the man did solemnly protest unto us, saying, ye shall not see my face, except your brother be with you.

source_text: "kevaka o sa vakatala vata kei keitou na taci keitou, keitou na qai lako sobu ka voli kakana.
target_text: if thou wilt send our brother with us, we will go down and buy thee food:

source_text: "kevaka e sega, keitou na sega ni lako sobu: ni sa tukuna vei keitou na tamata, dou na sega ni raica na mataqu, vakavo, ke sa lako mai na tacimudou. '"
target_text: but if thou wilt not send him, we will not go down: for the man said unto us, ye shall not see my face, except your brother be with you.

source_text: sa tukuna o isireli, "ena cava dou sa cakacaka vakaca kina vei au, ni dou sa tukuna vua na tamata ni se tiko tale e dua na tacimudou? "
target_text: and israel said, wherefore dealt ye so ill with me, as to tell the man whether ye had yet a brother?

source_text: e ratou sa tukuna, "na tamata sa vakatarogi keitou vakalalai kei ira talega na wekai keitou ka vaka: 'e se bula tiko o tamamudou? e dua tale tiko na tacimudou? ' keitou sa sauma vua me vaka na nona taro. keitou sa sega ni kila ni na tukuna mai, 'me kau sobu mai o tacimudou'? "
target_text: and they said, the man asked us straitly of our state, and of our kindred, saying, is your father yet alive? have ye another brother? and we told him according to the tenor of these words: could we certainly know that he would say, bring your brother down?

source_text: sa tukuna o juta vei isireli na tamana, "mo vakatalai koya vata kei au, me keitou lako me da bula kina ka sega ni mate, o iko kei ira na lalai.
target_text: and judah said unto israel his father, send the lad with me, and we will arise and go; that we may live, and not die, both we, and thou, and also our little ones.

source_text: "o au, nai vakadei ni nona lako, mo na tarogi koya mai na ligaqu. kevaka au na sega ni kauti koya lesu mai vei iko ka biuti koya e matamu. me'u qai beitaki kina me sega ni mudu.
target_text: i will be surety for him; of my hand shalt thou require him: if i bring him not unto thee, and set him before thee, then let me bear the blame for ever:

source_text: "kevaka keitou a sega ni vakaberabera tiko, e dodonu me keitou sa lesu tale mai vakarua oqo. "
target_text: for except we had lingered, surely now we had returned this second time.

source_text: sa qai tukuna vei iratou o isireli na tamadratou, "kevaka sa dina oqori, dou cakava oqo “dou kauta na vuata vinaka duadua ni vanua ena nomudou taga ka vakacabora vua na tamata, so talega na waiwai boivinaka, vakalailai na oni, na i waki ni kakana, na pinati lalai kei na pinati lelevu.
target_text: and their father israel said unto them, if it must be so now, do this; take of the best fruits in the land in your vessels, and carry down the man a present, a little balm, and a little honey, spices, and myrrh, nuts, and almonds:

source_text: "me vakaruataki nai lavo mo dou kauta me kau lesu nai lavo e kune ena nomudou taga, de a sega ni nakiti.
target_text: and take double money in your hand; and the money that was brought again in the mouth of your sacks, carry it again in your hand; peradventure it was an oversight:

source_text: "dou kauti tacimudou talega, ka lako yani vua na tamata.
target_text: take also your brother, and arise, go again unto the man:

source_text: "na kalou me vakaraitaka na yalololoma vua na tamata me rawa ni sereki tacimudou kei penijamini, kevaka me'u sa sega ni lomani, sa na vakakina ga! "
target_text: and god almighty give you mercy before the man, that he may send away your other brother, and benjamin. if i be bereaved of my children, i am bereaved.

source_text: e ratou sa tucake na tamata ka lako yani ki ijipita ka tu ena mata i joseva kei nai yau vakayadua e a vakarautaki.
target_text: and the men took that present, and they took double money in their hand, and benjamin; and rose up, and went down to egypt, and stood before joseph.

source_text: o joseva, ni sa raici penijamini vata kei iratou na tacina, sa tukuna vua na nona tamata, "kauti iratou oqo ki noqu vale. vakamatea e dua na manumanu ka vakarautaka rawa, o ira oqo era na kana vata kei au ena siga levu. "
target_text: and when joseph saw benjamin with them, he said to the ruler of his house, bring these men home, and slay, and make ready; for these men shall dine with me at noon.

source_text: era sa cakava na tamata me vaka sa vakarota o joseva. e ratou sa kau sara kina vale nei joseva.
target_text: and the man did as joseph bade; and the man brought the men into joseph's house.

source_text: era sa rere na tamata ni ra sa kau sara ki na vale nei joseva, e ratou sa tukuna, "oqo sa baleta nai lavo sa tiko ena nodatou taga sila ena i matai ni lako mai, oqo sa vakasaqara e dua na ka, me rawa ni beitaki kedatou kina ka me qai tauri kedatou me nona bobula. "
target_text: and the men were afraid, because they were brought into joseph's house; and they said, because of the money that was returned in our sacks at the first time are we brought in; that he may seek occasion against us, and fall upon us, and take us for bondmen, and our asses.

source_text: ni ratou sa toso voleka yani vua na dauveiqaravi ni vale nei joseva, era sa veivosaki sara ena mata ni katuba,
target_text: and they came near to the steward of joseph's house, and they communed with him at the door of the house,

source_text: ka tukuna, "io, saka, keimami a lako mai ena i matai ni gauna me voli kakana;
target_text: and said, o sir, we came indeed down at the first time to buy food:

source_text: "sa yaco ni keimami sa lesu tale, keimami sa kunea na i lavo ena gusu ni neimami taga. nai lavo o ya, keimami sa kauta lesu tale tiko mai oqo e ligai keimami.
target_text: and it came to pass, when we came to the inn, that we opened our sacks, and, behold, every man's money was in the mouth of his sack, our money in full weight: and we have brought it again in our hand.

source_text: "keimami sa kauta tale tikoga mai eso na i lavo me voli kakana kina “keimami sa sega ga ni kila se o cei e biuta nai lavo ena neimami taga. "
target_text: and other money have we brought down in our hands to buy food: we cannot tell who put our money in our sacks.

source_text: ia, sa tukuna mai, "mo dou vakacegu ka kua ni rere, na nomudou kalou kei na kalou ni tamamudou sa solia nai yau ka biuta ena nomudou taga, sa tu vei au na nomudou i lavo. " sa sereki simione lesu vei iratou.
target_text: and he said, peace be to you, fear not: your god, and the god of your father, hath given you treasure in your sacks: i had your money. and he brought simeon out unto them.

source_text: na dauveiqaravi sa kauti iratou mai ki vale, solia na wai me ratou vuluvulu kina kei na yavadratou talega ka solia na ka me ra kania na asa.
target_text: and the man brought the men into joseph's house, and gave them water, and they washed their feet; and he gave their asses provender.

source_text: era sa vakarautaka sara nai solisoli, ni na basika mai o joseva ena siga levu “ni ra sa rogoca ni na mai kana madrai e kea.
target_text: and they made ready the present against joseph came at noon: for they heard that they should eat bread there.

source_text: ni sa lako mai i vale o joseva, era sa kauta mai nai solisoli loloma ena ligadra ki vale, ka era sa cuva sobu vua ki na qele.
target_text: and when joseph came home, they brought him the present which was in their hand into the house, and bowed themselves to him to the earth.

source_text: sa tarogi ira sara me baleta na nodra bula vinaka ka vaka: "e vinaka tiko beka o tamamudou, na qase dou a tukuna tiko? e se bula tiko o koya? "
target_text: and he asked them of their welfare, and said, is your father well, the old man of whom ye spake? is he yet alive?

source_text: e ratou sa sauma mai, "na nomuni tamata na tamai keitou e se bula vinaka tiko ka bulabula talega. " era sa cuva sobu ka vakarokoroko.
target_text: and they answered, thy servant our father is in good health, he is yet alive. and they bowed down their heads, and made obeisance.

source_text: sa rai cake ka raici penijamini, na luvei tinana ka taroga, "oqo beka na tacimudou gone dou a tukuna vei au? " sa tukuna tale, "me yalololoma vei iko na kalou na luvequ. "
target_text: and he lifted up his eyes, and saw his brother benjamin, his mother's son, and said, is this your younger brother, of whom ye spake unto me? and he said, god be gracious unto thee, my son.

source_text: sa luluvu na yalona ena vukui tacina, sa lako tani yani vakatotolo ka tagi e na nona rumu.
target_text: and joseph made haste; for his bowels did yearn upon his brother: and he sought where to weep; and he entered into his chamber, and wept there.

source_text: sa tavoya na matana ka lako tale mai, sa tauri koya vinaka ka tukuna, "me soli yani na madrai. "
target_text: and he washed his face, and went out, and refrained himself, and said, set on bread.

source_text: sa vakarautaki ga na teveli taudua nei joseva, na tikina ga me ra kana kina na tacina, na nodra tikina na ijipita era veiqaravi “ni o ira na ijipita era sega ni rawa ni kana vata kei ira na iperiu, ni oqo na ka toro sobu vei ira na kai ijipita.
target_text: and they set on for him by himself, and for them by themselves, and for the egyptians, which did eat with him, by themselves: because the egyptians might not eat bread with the hebrews; for that is an abomination unto the egyptians.

source_text: era dabe tuvai e matai joseva, mai vei koya e qaseduadua ki vei koya sara e gone duadua. e ratou sa veiraici mada ga ena kidroa na veitacini.
target_text: and they sat before him, the firstborn according to his birthright, and the youngest according to his youth: and the men marvelled one at another.

source_text: sa kauta yani o koya na veiqaravi vei ira, mai matana. sa vakalimataki na ka vei penijamini. era sa gunu ka marau vata tiko kei joseva.
